Title: 1. The Kerala Story
Content: A converted Muslim woman Fatima Ba narrates her ordeal of how she once wanted to become a nurse but was abducted from her home and manipulated by religious vanguards, turned into an ISIS terrorist and landed in Afghanistan jail.

Title: 2. Neru
Content: Sara, a blind sculptor, seeks justice after suffering trauma. She contends with the legal system and her own resilience to find resolution.

Title: 3. Kannur Squad
Content: The gripping saga of a police officer and his team, their challenging journey to nab a criminal gang across the country. Further, it shows how he leads his team towards triumph, amidst professional uncertainties in this gripping drama.

Title: 4. Bhoothakaalam
Content: Following the death of a family member, a mother and son experience mysterious events which distort their sense of reality and make them question their sanity.

Title: 5. Curry & Cyanide: The Jolly Joseph Case
Content: The real life case of Jolly Joseph, a lady suspected of planning the cyanide poisoning of six family members over more than ten years, including a two-year-old kid.

Title: 6. Kaathal - The Core
Content: Mathew, a retired bank secretary, reluctantly enters politics for a by-election. The movie delves into their marriage dynamics, justice, and personal fulfillment amidst a tight-knit village community.

Title: 7. Iratta
Content: After a cop is found dead, a policeman's investigation starts a chilling search for the truth connected to his estranged twin and their fraught past.

Title: 8. Romancham
Content: A game of Ouija board goes hilariously wrong when seven bachelors unexpectedly invite a spirit and try to make the best out of the situation.
A disaster film set during the 2018 Kerala Floods where people from all walks of life faced catastrophic consequences and put in collective efforts to survive the calamity.

Title: 10. Queen Elizabeth
Content: Impending death changes an arrogant, cold, self-centered person into a loving, friendly person - practically overnight - is what we see in this romantic comedy drama.

Title: 11. Cold Case
Content: The film tells the riveting story of a complex murder case, parallelly investigated by a police officer and an investigative journalist in their own way, who eventually cross paths to unravel secrets they never imagined.

Title: 12. Rorschach
Content: The Movie is about Luke Anthony who has a mysterious past and is out on a mission to seek revenge from someone who has destroyed him deeply

Title: 13. Aattam
Content: After a party amongst a theatre group, their sole actress, Anjali is subjected to a crime from one of the men in the group. A meeting is called for. In trying to reach a consensus, stories unravel, suspicions surface and clamour ensues.

Title: 14. Hridayam
Content: The emotional journey of Arun, his carefree bachelor days in engineering college, and how he matures through various phases of life.

Title: 15. Jana Gana Mana
Content: As a college professor's brutal murder sparks student unrest, a cop launches an investigation while a lawyer seeks justice in the the courtroom.

Title: 16. Antony
Content: An emotionally charged mass family entertainer that delves into the profound theme of relationships that run deeper than blood. The story revolves around the enigmatic character, Antony and his close-knit group of friends.

Title: 17. Falimy
Content: A family of self-centered individuals sets out on a journey to fulfill their grandfather's pilgrimage wish, partly to prevent his frequent escapes and partly to find a distraction from their personal problems.

Title: 18. Drishyam
Content: A man goes to extreme lengths to save his family from punishment after the family commits an accidental crime.

Title: 19. CBI 5: The Brain
Content: A series of murders is happening in the city. With the police failing to solve the case, a team of CBI Officers under CBI officer Sethurama Iyer take up the investigation to resolve the mystery.

Title: 20. Garudan
Content: Harish Madhav, a straightforward cop, and Nishanth, a college professor, get entangled in a crime and one has to fight for his integrity and other has to fight for justice.

Title: 21. Joji
Content: Joji, an engineering dropout and the youngest son of a rich family lives with his aspirations of becoming super wealthy. Driven by greed and blind ambition, he decides to execute his plans following an unexpected event in the family.

Title: 22. Nayattu
Content: Three police officers who are on a run for life, escaping the outbreak against them due to the unlawful arrest and torture of a civilian. It brings in a few shades of arrogant yet very much human police officers and their helplessness.

Title: 23. Chaver
Content: Political thugs commit an abhorrent crime, taking an innocent bystander on the run. The police chase them, and moral dilemmas arise among them. The bystander's fate remains ambiguous. Escaping justice, they face life-altering consequences.

Title: 24. Ponniyin Selvan: Part I
Content: Vandiyathevan crosses the Chola land to deliver a message from the Crown Prince Aditha Karikalan, while Kundavai attempts to establish political peace as vassals and petty chieftains plot against the throne.

Title: 25. Nanpakal Nerathu Mayakkam
Content: James wakes up irritable on a bus, believing he is Sundaram, a man who vanished from a quiet village years prior.

Title: 26. Anjaam Pathiraa
Content: The police are on the trail of a serial killer, but with the victims being fellow officers, will they be able to catch the killer and solve the case in time?

Title: 27. Monster
Content: On their first wedding anniversary, Lucky Singh, an entrepreneur from Punjab walks into the lives of Anil Chandra and Bhamini. Little do they know that this man will change their future

Title: 28. Kumbalangi Nights
Content: The film revolves around four brothers who share a love-hate relationship with each other. Their relationship progresses to another level when Saji, Boney, and Franky decide to help Bobby stand by his love.

Title: 29. Jan.E.Man
Content: Joy Mon plans his own birthday party to overcome sadness and loneliness, but things take an unpleasant turn when the man next to his friend's house become deceased. Can Joy Mon have a pleasant and cheerful birthday celebration ?

Title: 30. Thondi Muthalum Driksakshiyum
Content: Prasad and Sreeja enter wedlock and move to a new place to continue the rest of their lives. Unfortunate events begin to take place after Prasad, a small-time thief, robs Sreeja's gold chain during a bus journey.

Title: 31. Churuli
Content: Two undercover cops who go in search of a fugitive enter another dimension occupied by uncivilized residents who are crass and rude. There, the two men get stuck in an apparent time loop as inexplicable events begin to occur.

Title: 32. Kumari
Content: The world of Kumari, who is married off far away in Kanhirangat, a cursed land beyond Illymala, in the west. A naive Kumari arrives in the cursed land, where people are ready to sacrifice their lives to preserve tradition and power.

Title: 33. Malik
Content: A past ridden with crime, death and pain is recounted to Freddy, a juvenile criminal, who has been assigned to eliminate his estranged uncle Sulaiman, an aging patriarch, while behind bars.

Title: 34. Ponniyin Selvan: Part Two
Content: Arulmozhi Varman continues on his journey to become Rajaraja I, the greatest ruler of the historic Chola empire of south India.

Title: 35. Premam
Content: A young man has three opportunities to find love. Will the third time be the charm?

Title: 36. Thanneermathan Dinangal
Content: A rom-com based in a school where a schoolteacher named Ravi Padmanabhan comes into the lives of Jason and his friends.

Title: 37. Ela Veezha Poonchira
Content: Follows two police officers at a small wireless police station on the hilltop as they work to resolve the mystery about a woman's body parts that have been scattered all over Elaveezhapoonchira.

Title: 38. Bheeshma Parvam
Content: Michael helms his ancestral family in Kochi, inspiring fear and respect through his past. When a few younger members of the household find his power over their lives too aggravating, they join hands with foes to clamp down on him.

Title: 39. Super Sharanya
Content: Sharanya, a shy and introverted person, is a native of Kollengode, Palakkad who moves to Thrissur to pursue engineering. She finds it difficult to cope with her new surroundings in college and her hostel.

Title: 40. 12th Man
Content: Eleven friends get together for a bachelor party, but the celebrations go awry because of a phone call and a death. A drunk cop steps into unravel the mystery.

Title: 41. Red Rain
Content: Mysterious deaths of cattle and strange lights in the sky get a young scientist curious.

Title: 42. RDX: Robert Dony Xavier
Content: The life of three mysterious individuals take a turn as their faces gets exposed.

Title: 43. Kuruthi
Content: Conflicts started to happen in Moosa Khader's home after the entry of a police officer and a murder convict.

Title: 44. Jallikattu
Content: A portrait of a remote village where a buffalo escapes and causes a frenzy of ecstatic violence.

Title: 45. Kooman
Content: The story is about a strict police officer who relocates to a hilly village on the Kerala-Tamil Nadu border. Few normal incidents that take place suddenly appear to be abnormal.

Title: 46. Purusha Pretham
Content: Purusha Pretham, Krishand's third feature, is a police procedural story that has never been seen before in Malayalam cinema; an investigative thriller with interesting twists and turns.

Title: 47. Lucifer
Content: A political Godfather dies and a lot of thieves dressed up as politicians took over the rule. Question arises regarding the successor of the God, unfolding few names, along with the God's most beloved angel, Lucifer.

Title: 48. Minnal Murali
Content: A tailor gains special powers after being struck by lightning, but must take down an unexpected foe if he is to become the superhero his hometown needs.
When forces within and beyond this world conspire to snatch his son away, a father resolves to do whatever it takes to protect him.

Title: 50. Charlie
Content: A young, nonconforming woman named Tessa gets entangled in a cat-and-mouse chase in the by-lanes of Kerala, hunting for a mysterious artist who previously lived in her apartment.

Title: 51. The Great Indian Kitchen
Content: After marriage, a woman struggles to be the submissive wife that her husband and his family expect her to be. The story follows her journey, as she changes herself and, even more so, changes the household.

Title: 52. Udal
Content: Shiny is looking after her bedridden mother-in-law, living along with her father-in-law Kuttichan. Tensions arise pushing Shiny to the point where she cannot take anymore.

Title: 53. #Home
Content: Oliver Twist (Indrans) wants to be tech-savvy and become a better companion to his two sons, who spend more time on their phones than with their loved ones.

Title: 54. Kurup
Content: Kurup is a criminal who is on the run from police after murdering someone for life insurance fraud.

Title: 55. Four
Content: It is about a wronged teacher, who returns to the government school from where he lost his job to guide the students along the right path.

Title: 56. Mukundan Unni Associates
Content: Advocate Mukundan Unni, played by Vineeth Sreenivasan wants to be successful and leaves no stone unturned to achieve growth, prosperity, and respect. But this steadfast nature aided with an ample dose of greed comes with a cost.

Title: 57. Drishyam 2
Content: A gripping tale of an investigation and a family which is threatened by it. Will Georgekutty be able to protect his family this time?

Title: 58. A Ranjith Cinema
Content: It takes you on a roller coaster ride of events that happen in Ranjith's life and how it affects the people around him, forcing him to resolve the matter before he looses control.

Title: 59. Ayyappanum Koshiyum
Content: The story revolves around the clash between Ayyappan, a senior police officer who serves at the Attappadi Police Station and Havildar Koshi, who comes to the village with a motive.

Title: 60. Vallicheruppu
Content: Revolves around the affectionate bond between a man and his grandchild.

Title: 61. Thallumaala
Content: Follows a youngster ready to get married, but funny events happen and changes his plans.
Akhil and Athira, two youngsters who are deeply in love, and the implications their love has in the lives of their families and the society around them.

Title: 63. Angamaly Diaries
Content: Vincent Pepe who wanted to be a powerful leader of a righteous gang that ruled the city, like his seniors. And then there's the rival clan with the malicious gangsters of Angamaly a locale on which the film is based.

Title: 64. Jaya Jaya Jaya Jaya Hey
Content: Jaya, gets married. Her intention is to complete her education, but her partner mockingly asks her to try for Public Service Commission exams. Jaya tries to find the right balance managing her in-laws as she strives for her goal.

Title: 65. Sudani from Nigeria
Content: Story of an African football player and a local football club manager from Malappuram, Kerala.

Title: 66. The Great Escape
Content: The Great Escape tells the story of immigrant Mob King Bob who is involved in various illegal activities like arms dealing and money laundering. Bobs biggest enemy Lord Pavlov attacks Bobs family to seek revenge.

Title: 67. Joseph
Content: The story develops through the life of four retired policemen. It has the tone of a thriller investigation. An issue affecting the life of Joseph, the central character, and his family is being investigated.

Title: 68. Salute
Content: S.I Aravind Karunakaran, a police officer on voluntary leave, is haunted by an old case he investigated. How far will he go to unravel the mystery and bring the truth to light?

Title: 69. Bangalore Days
Content: A fun roller coaster ride about three young people, Aju, Divya and Kuttan who are cousins, reach Bangalore to dream, discover and explore.

Title: 70. Kaduva
Content: The film is set in the late 90s revolving around the life of a young high range rubber planter from Mundakayam and his rivalry with a high ranking officer in the Kerala Police.

Title: 71. Pada
Content: All the governments that have ruled the nation made laws that denied the indigenous people their way of life and their land often, protecting crony capitalist interests. The film revisits an episode of dissent in the 90s which brought up this question amongst us. A history forgotten!

Title: 72. Little Miss Rawther
Content: A short women who falls in love with a tall guy and is constantly reminded of their physical differences at each stage of their relationship.

Title: 73. Five First Dates
Content: Five First Dates follows the dating life of Shalini, a bisexual woman as she goes on five different dates over the course of her life, from college to her later years. Each date is at a different stage in her journey of self-discovery and sexual exploration.

Title: 74. Neelavelicham
Content: A young, enthusiastic and free-spirited writer arrives to stay in a desolate mansion, rumored to be haunted by the apparition of a young woman who committed suicide when she was betrayed in love.

Title: 75. Memories
Content: Sam Alex, a drunkard ex-cop, is forced to investigate a series of murders which are committed in the same pattern. His search leads to a serial killer, and something more than what he expected.

Title: 76. Phoenix
Content: John and his family relocate to a far away island village with hopes of rebuilding their lives. But destiny has other plans for them as a series of horrifying events begin to unfold.

Title: 77. Porinju Mariyam Jose
Content: Set against the backdrop of a church festival in Thrissur, is a story of friendship, love and revenge that revolves around the lives of a rowdy, an aristocratic and their mutual friend.

Title: 78. Trance
Content: A disheartened motivational speaker gets hired by a corporate to become a preacher until his live stint on television puts him and his service under the scanner.

Title: 79. Philip's
Content: Unforeseen events arose in Philips joyful family disrupting their happiness. They must tackle these hiccups and regain their life in a better way

Title: 80. Ezra
Content: A newly married woman brings an antique Jewish box into her home, unaware that the box contains the ghost of Abraham Ezra.

Title: 81. Kaapa
Content: The film explores the dark underbelly of Thiruvananthapuram where rival goondas clash in cold-blooded gang wars to gain dominion over the city's suburbs and slums.

Title: 82. Corona Papers
Content: Rahul, a newly appointed officer, accidentally loses his service pistol. What happens when it lands in the wrong hands?

Title: 83. Christopher
Content: A maverick cop is forced to work outside the limits of law, when the system fails.The story weaves across the past and present while revealing the motives that shape his actions.

Title: 84. Twenty One Grams
Content: An ingenious cop, Nanda Kishore, sets out to untangle a string of mysterious murders in Kochi. As the secrets unveil themselves, he finds himself in a dilemma.

Title: 85. City of God
Content: In the city of Cochin, a series of incidents connects the lives of a Tamil laborer couple, an actress, a builder, a criminal, and the wife of a businessman.

Title: 86. Family
Content: When a respected mentor reveals his evil nature, it brings a clash of family values and custom, enveloping a village in false normalcy.

Title: 87. Keedam
Content: Radhika Balan, a smart cyber-security expert, advocates the use of the technology for the good but her life is turned upside down when she falls prey to a cyber-stalking incident and her privacy gets compromised.

Title: 88. Love
Content: A family and the various situations navigated by a husband and wife.

Title: 89. Pulimurugan
Content: When a small village near a forest is under the threat of man eating tigers and a drug mafia, the villagers seek the help of an unstoppable force, a hunter invincible.

Title: 90. Rekha
Content: A young woman in love, ends up on a vindictive mission as a result of one unfortunate night that sends her spiralling into violence.

Title: 91. Christy
Content: Roy, a village boy who's a failure at studies, joins Christy's tuition. They become good friends, however later when Christy gets a job abroad, Roy's life changes.

Title: 92. Anandabhadram
Content: Following his mother's death, the protagonist returns from the US to his ancestral home to fulfill his mother's last wish. Upon arrival he understands that the world of black magic and sorcery he heard as stories were not far from real.

Title: 93. Panthrand
Content: While returning from a gang violence, twelve local gangsters are baffled to find a stranger in their van. His presence and actions evokes suspicion. What will happen next?

Title: 94. Padachone Ingalu Kaatholee
Content: Dineshan, Grace, Giri, KK and Gund Saji are involved in leftwing politics. Dineshan gets attracted to a girl who stays over at his house and she makes him consider all the occurrences that happen at home and take action for them.

Title: 95. Pendulum
Content: Dr. Mahesh, on trying to unravel the mystery of an unusual incident, concludes that lucid dreaming might help digging up his past. Will he be able to rectify the future by altering his past mistakes?

Title: 96. Nna, Thaan Case Kodu
Content: A reformed thief's fight for justice when an innocent act to defend himself places him in loggerheads with the high and mighty of society.

Title: 97. Y
Content: Some unexpected events on a street catch everybody present there by surprise. The movie is about how the characters there, react to the incidents taking place.

Title: 98. Forensic
Content: Samuel uses his forensic skills and discovers breakthroughs in a serial killing case as further victims are added to the list. Shikha teams up with Samuel and uncovers evidence that might lead to the killer's identity.

Title: 99. Blue Skies, Green Waters, Red Earth
Content: Kasi and Suni go for the ride from Kerala to Nagaland in search of Kasi's girlfriend. En route, they encounter different people who change their lives forever.

Title: 100. Ajagajantharam
Content: Aranjali is all set to celebrate the annual temple festival. Some unforeseen chain of events involving an elephant, a few young men, a notorious criminal, a drama troop and some trouble-loving villagers brings complete mayhem to the place.

Title: 101. Maheshinte Prathikaaram
Content: Mahesh, a studio photographer and studio owner gets into a fight and loses. He ends up taking revenge which leads to certain realizations in his life.

Title: 102. Chaayam Poosiya Veedu
Content: Gautam, a lonely old writer, comes face to face with the seductive Vishaya and the mysterious young man Rahul. A series of events are unleashed which make the old writer question every belief he has held about himself.

Title: 103. Third World Boys
Content: Third World Boys is woven around seven youngsters who set off on an impromptu trip over a weekend. There are no romantic female leads in the movie.

Title: 104. Irul
Content: When a car breakdown forces a couple to seek shelter in a nearby home, conversations with the stranger inside soon suggest there's a killer among them.

Title: 105. Android Kunjappan Ver 5.25
Content: Story of a conventional, conservative small town villager and his son who has to move away from home due to his profession. Their relationship gets an endearing twist when an AI humanoid enters their lives and fills in their emptiness.

Title: 106. C.I.D. Moosa
Content: The adventures of a private detective, Moosa, whose luck and wit help him to solve the cases.

Title: 107. Parole
Content: Alex is a comrade and an active communist leader. Due to some unfortunate events, Alex gets arrested and is imprisoned but is compelled to come out on Parole to solve a mystery he left behind.

Title: 108. Mea Culpa
Content: A trapped girl's life serves as the central focus of the story. With unknown motives, the dangerous man tries to attack her. Things take an unexpected turn because it includes hidden vengeance.

Title: 109. Ishq
Content: Two youngsters who try to find joy after they lose out on love and their need for a mutual trust to sustain love and happiness.

Title: 110. Varathan
Content: After losing his job Abin along with his wife Priya, who has suffered a miscarriage, decide to shift from Dubai to Priya's family estate in Kerala. However, peace eludes the couple as they run into a set of new troubles.

Title: 111. Amen
Content: Amen tells the story of people around an ancient Nasrani Church. The plot is set in a village, Kumarankary, where its inhabitants are always garbed in white - a motif which the film deftly employs to meld the elements of fantasy and spirituality. A young, handsome cleric (Indrajith Sukumaran) arrives as the Kathanar (Syrian priest) of the church, whose senior Kathanar is Fr. Abraham (Joy Mathew), a grumpy fellow. The village has a mix of issues, which range from the love between Solomon (Fahadh Faasil) and Sosanna (Swati Reddy) to the fate of a band crushed by frequent failures in contests. The movie sets itself a lot of targets like the fate of Solomon's love, his dazzling self-discovery of a trait not known to him before and some sober spiritual and religious conflicts. Amen promises a luxuriant plot replete with music, faith, fantasy and romance and an amazingly varied set of characters. As the parish seriously discusses whether to retain the church's band that had lost to the rival group in the earlier band competition, a young priest Fr. Vincent Vattoli (Indrajit) takes charge under Fr.Ottaplackan. He is stylish, dares to defy conventions and is in support of the romance between Solomon and Sosanna. His actions irk the senior priest and things take a serious turn after a while. The people agrees to a pact that sets the fate of Solomon's love with Sosanna, and the Kumarankary church band's future. The band goes on to win the competition, and the film ends on a truly surprising climax.

Title: 112. Ennalum Ente Aliya
Content: Two immigrant families who stay in the same building complex in Dubai inadvertently square up because of some misunderstandings. Things take a wild turn when the real culprits of the love affairs are revealed.

Title: 113. Godha
Content: Captain, a former wrestler, sends his son Das to Punjab for higher studies. Once there, Das falls in love with Aditi, a champion wrestler, who inspires him to pursue the sport.

Title: 114. Rajamanikyam
Content: The story of how a un-educated man Rajamanikyam, abandoned as a child, unites his step-father with the latter's children who are greedy for his wealth and possessions.

Title: 115. Paleri Manikyam: Oru Pathirakolapathakathinte Katha
Content: A woman is found dead in mysterious circumstances. Several discrepancies arise in the findings, which eventually leads to the closure of the case. Years later, Haridas decides to reopen the case.

Title: 116. 1001 Nunakal
Content: Close friends get together and have some good time over food and talks until one of them proposes a game: each of them has to reveal a lie that they have hidden from their partners.

Title: 117. Bandra
Content: Director Sakshi stumbles upon a tragedy: the suicide of a Bollywood icon. As she unravels the past, it unveils the tale of a man with a mysterious past whose life took a dramatic turn when the queen of Bollywood entered his world.

Title: 118. Antakshari
Content: A game that makes you reminisce the good old days of your life, suddenly takes a turn. Will it depend on a mere game of Antakshari?

Title: 119. 100 Days of Love
Content: A man, who just got dumped, falls in love with another girl who he bullied in his childhood.

Title: 120. Djinn
Content: A lady encounters a supernatural things during a tour and a horror experience with a sudden appearance of a man called jinn and the story goes on the horror path.

Title: 121. Puzhu
Content: A gripping thriller with focus on the relationship between a father and son, and the underlying family dynamics and trust issues that follow.

Title: 122. Ayalum Njanum Thammil...
Content: A story on how a brilliant and dedicated senior doctor molds an irresponsible amateur doctor into one much like him, and how a forbidden relationship comes in between.

Title: 123. Kurukkan
Content: A self deprecating police officer who is down on luck and hasn't had any career promotion's tries to frame an innocent to make fame, but it backfires on him.

Title: 124. Eka
Content: Based on true incidents , Referred as the most violent Indian movie of the year Eka is first Indian movie to discuss the Intersex gender, person born with both male and female genitals. The movie is banned in India because of nudity, violence and political sensitivity. The movie is a queer subject as it also deals with atrocities against transgenders, transsexuals, LGBT and all gender minorities. In India due to article 377 of penal code gender minorities are facing a huge social problem. Eka is the story of an intersex persons bike journey through three states of India with her female friend. This is of course, not the story of the them. This is the story of the society which cant accept them. It is the war of a society to itself, so it got banned The movie discuss wide range of LGBT politics and body politics. Surely , a tough to watch movie, with strong socio-political stand.

Title: 125. Action Hero Biju
Content: The life of an honest and determined police officer Biju and the various criminals he puts behind bars.

Title: 126. Jacob's Kingdom of Heaven
Content: The struggles faced by a business man and his family in Dubai to stabilize themselves after getting cheated by a fraudster.

Title: 127. Kappela
Content: Set in the village areas of Wayanad, Malappuram and Kannur, Kappela revolves around an ordinary, innocent girl who comes to Kozhikode city from a high range area called Poovarmala.

Title: 128. Thattathin Marayathu
Content: The struggles faced when a Hindu man falls in love with a Muslim woman and the disapproval of her family.

Title: 129. Oru Adaar Love
Content: The movie depicts the life and times of a group of schoolmates who are best buddies. As they journey through the most memorable times of their lives, lasting friendships are forged and extraordinary tales of romance blossom.

Title: 130. Mumbai Police
Content: ACP Antony is the only one who knows the truth behind ACP Aaryan's murder. Antony meets with an accident, losing his memory and is unable to reveal the killer. He is forced to investigate the murder again hoping that he remembers something.

Title: 131. Voice of Sathyanathan
Content: A man's life becomes increasingly complicated after his neighbor is injured in a dispute over a fence.

Title: 132. Unda
Content: The film narrates the events that occur when a unit of policemen from Kerala reach the Naxalite prone areas in North India for election duty.

Title: 133. Pranaya Vilasam
Content: Portrays love stories of different characters who are at different stages of their lives.

Title: 134. Pulimada
Content: After being left at the altar, an embittered police officer preys on a stranded tourist - while a deadly tiger in the area adds another layer of menace.

Title: 135. Vichitram
Content: It's the story of Jasmine and her five sons who get involved into a series of events when they start living in their ancestral home.

Title: 136. Sufiyum Sujatayum
Content: Sujata (mute) is in love with her neighbour, a sufi priest but her father gets her married off to a well-do-to NRI, in Dubai. Ten years have passed since and she thinks that she's left that love in her past - until, one day, she gets a call. Her husband (Rajeev) decides to bring her back to the village. What follows, forms the crux of Sufiyum Sujatayam, a musical love story.

Title: 137. Mahaveeryar
Content: Focuses on time travel, fantasy and court proceedings intertwined with emotional and funny moments.

Title: 138. My Name Is Azhakan
Content: Azhakan thinks his father named him purposely so that the people will mock him till his death. One day due to pressure from his parents he went to see a girl who likes him because he was an artist.

Title: 139. Mundrothuruth: Munroe Island
Content: The brief stay of a young man and his father to Munroe island, where his grandfather resides.

Title: 140. Ustad Hotel
Content: Faisi wants to go to UK to become a professional chef but circumstances force him to assist his grandfather in a small restaurant in Kozhikode city, changing his outlook on life forever.

Title: 141. Lonappante Mammodisa
Content: Lonappan happens to attend his school reunion, where he revisits his older self and starts to reflect on his potential. When he meets his friends who are doing really well in life and are happy, he starts thinking about his laid back life.

Title: 142. Big B
Content: Four brothers hunt for the killer and the truth behind their loving foster mother who was murdered in cold blood, .

Title: 143. North 24 Kaatham
Content: Harikrishan, a software engineer who suffers from obsessive-compulsive personality disorder is asked to go on an assignment to Trivandrum, as his colleagues are not able to stand his behavior.

Title: 144. Biriyaani
Content: The movie chronicles the life of Khadeeja, a married Muslim woman confined within the four walls of the household, forced to conceal her desires in the name of religious and societal norms.

Title: 145. Upacharapoorvam Gunda Jayan
Content: Former rowdy jayan is in a mission to conduct the marriage of his niece.Things got out of hands when things get worse

Title: 146. Achanoru Vazha Vechu
Content: A father and son struggle to understand each other as their opposing perspectives drive a wedge between them, impacting their family.

Title: 147. Kuttavum Shikshayum
Content: Real-life adaptation of the jewellery robbery that occurred in Kasargod. The case took a 5 member team from the Kerala Police to a dreaded village in Uttar Pradesh where they risked their lives to nab the culprits.

Title: 148. Pathemari
Content: Narrates both the hardships and happiness that Gulf life has provided to Malayalees. The period from 1960 to the present form the context of the story.

Title: 149. Theru
Content: Hari and his two friends who get embroiled in a murder case under unusual circumstances. They deal with the power-play, haplessness and trauma.

Title: 150. Janaki Jaane
Content: Struggling with panic disorder, Janaki is ecstatic when Unni Mukundan proposes to marry her. Things go south when Janaki's fears land her in serious trouble.

Title: 151. Theerppu
Content: Four friends, Ramkumar, Kalyan, Parameshwaran and Abdulla, who share a troubled history and familial strife, meet at Ramkumar's Hotel. This happenstance get-together ends up in fresh tension, leading to unforeseen consequences.

Title: 152. Poovan

Title: 153. Thaaram Theertha Koodaram

Title: 157. Oh My Darling

Title: 158. Thanmathra

Title: 159. Nadikalil Sundari Yamuna

Title: 160. Guppy

Title: 161. Odiyan

Title: 162. Ntikkakkakkoru Premondarnn

Title: 164. Gold
Content: The movie showcases the incidents that take place within four days of Joshi, a mobile shop owner, purchasing a new car owing to a marriage alliance that is almost fixed with a girl called Radha.

Title: 165. Holy Wound

Title: 166. Thrissur Pooram

Title: 167. Annayum Rasoolum

Title: 170. Pappachan Olivilaanu

Title: 171. Vettah

Title: 173. Koode

Title: 175. Bro Daddy

Title: 176. Pallotty 90's Kids

Title: 177. Missing Girl

Title: 180. ABCD: American-Born Confused Desi

Title: 181. Theeppori Benny
Content: It revolves around the lives of Benn and his father Vattakuttayil Chettayi who is a selfless communist.
The story of Rameshan who has a huge craze for Cricket, and his final attempt to realize his cricket dream through his son.

Title: 183. Live

Title: 186. Vamanan

Title: 187. Helen

Title: 189. Kirkkan

Title: 190. Bhramam

Title: 193. Padmini

Title: 196. Palthu Janwar

Title: 197. Paachuvum Albhuthavilakkum

Title: 198. Sasanasabha
Content: The movie's subject will be very apt to the present-day society and will carry an important message to the society but without being preachy anywhere. It will be a racy political Drama.

Title: 199. The Great Father

Title: 200. Picket 43

Title: 201. Meesha Madhavan

Content: The life of Mathan, a mule driver in a gang and Aparna an aspiring actress.

Title: 217. Santhosham

Title: 218. Jo and Jo

Title: 219. Twenty:20
Content: Devaraja Prathapa Varma, an underworld don and wealthy businessman wants payback for his brother Karthik Varma's murderers.

Title: 220. Ini Utharam
Content: The plot revolves around the girl who gets trapped in a fake case. Things take a turn as she decides to revolt.

Title: 221. Thrishanku

Title: 223. Mike

Title: 224. Rajni
Content: Siblings Naveen and Gowri find themselves entangled in a web of chaos and danger with a looming life threat, the story unravels a mysterious quest to uncover the enigmatic identity of Rajni

Title: 225. Dhoomam
Content: Avinash wants to quit his marketing job at a top cigarette company, but it comes with consequences.

Title: 226. Ottamandaram

Title: 227. Adi Kapyare Kootamani

Title: 229. Vaashi

Title: 230. Nalla Nilavulla Rathri

Title: 231. Big Brother

Title: 232. Oru Thathvika Avalokanam

Title: 233. Grandmaster

Title: 234. Rathinirvedam
Content: A man falls for an older woman, but their affair seems doomed.

Title: 235. Sofi

Title: 236. Kettiyollaanu Ente Maalakha

Title: 237. Pallimani

Title: 239. Chathuram
Content: Life of a woman Selena interacts and responds to the people and circumstances she meets. Either good or evil all are fighting what they think is right. There is a way a woman needs to be respected and treated be it mentally or physically

Content: The story of renowned psychologist Ravishankar, his wife Padmaja, and some amusing incidents with his clients. Ravishankar and Padmaja, although hailing from a remote village, are residing now in a city and part of the elite society.

Title: 241. Digital Village
Content: A group of three friends who try their best to spread digital literacy in their village. It is not an easy task for the three men as the villagers stick firmly to their traditional belief system.

Title: 242. Kaanekkaane
Content: Dpt. Tahsildar Paul Mathai arrives in town for some court matters. He is welcomed by his son-in-law Allen. But when Paul is leaving Allen's home, something catches his eye. There comes the shift in their lives...

Title: 243. Anuragam
Content: The idea of true love and hope shown through several characters and their slice of life.

Title: 244. The Teacher
Content: Follows Amala, whose seemingly perfect life is turned upside down after a scandalous video involving her goes viral, becoming a social pariah, but she fights on her own to try to get out of the hole.

Content: A ruthless moneylender must tackle a wicked man's plan to outsmart his way out of the debt to achieve what's rightfully his.

Title: 247. Gangs of 18

Title: 248. Seththumaan

When Vellaiyan, Poochi's beneficent but easily ruffled landlord, instructs him to find a choice pig-or "seththumaan", whose meat is fetishized among local gourmands, or denigrated by caste conservatives-Poochi and little Kumaresan get busy. However, once pork and drink go down, tempers flare up, and Poochi must avoid getting caught up in the acerbic hostilities that consume his dominant caste overlords.

Title: 249. Tholvi F.C.
Content: The Kurivila family is a bunch of failures in life. Career, money, love, life. They can't seem to win at anything. 'Tholvi FC' is a warm and funny story of a dysfunctional family try to not fail at life. And maybe even win.

Title: 250. Padavettu
Content: The coming of age drama portray the relentless pursuit of the layman, the oppressed section of society who is in a constant struggle and fight to reclaim their unique identity and rightful place in a world meant for all.

Title: 251. Kho Kho
Content: Malayalam Feature Film based on the Indian tag sport Kho-Kho. The film is written and directed by Rahul Riji Nair and is produced by First Print Studios. Rajisha Vijayan plays the central protagonist in the film.

Title: 252. Anuraga Karikkin Vellam
Content: The equation of Raghu and his son Abhi passes through various stages, and Raghu his son making the mistakes he did once. With a bit of help from someone new in their lives, the family passes through a turf of transformation.

Title: 253. Molly Aunty Rocks
Content: Molly is a strong-willed woman who has experienced a world outside India. Pranav, a highly-egoistic IRS officer, brings up a major issue with Molly that could destroy her life. Who will come out on top when these two clash?

Title: 254. C U Soon
Content: A software engineer, living in Kerala, is prompted by his family to look for his cousin's missing fiancee. As they stumble upon her video-based suicide note, he races against time to find her.

Title: 255. Jomon's Gospels
Content: The son of a wealthy man works through his relationships with his brother and sister.

Title: 256. Varane Avashyamund
Content: Neena is a French teacher and single parent to Nikitha, who is obsessed with the concept of arranged marriage. Their lives change when a retired army man and another young man come to stay at their apartment.

Title: 257. Otta
Content: The story of 'Otta' is inspired by the life of S Hariharan who has written the book 'Runaway Children', which was based on the life of S Hariharan.

Title: 258. Aravindante Athidhikal
Content: A five-year-old kid is found deserted on Navarathri at a 1200-year-old temple and is believed to have been blessed by with the presence of Mookambika Devi is found and raised by a lodge owner.

Title: 259. Adam Joan
Content: The story revolves around the life of a planter, Adam Joan Pothan from the village Mundakkayam. One day, he unexpectedly meets a girl named Emy and they go to Scotland together. The new people he meets on his journey changes his life.

Title: 260. The Elder One
Content: A transgender child from Lakshadweep sets off to Mumbai in pursuit of Akbar, an elder brother who left the island due to his sexual orientation.

Title: 261. Parava
Content: The story of Parava revolves around pigeon race, a game, which is prominent in Mattancherry, Kochi, Kerala.

Title: 262. Thankam
Content: Muthu (Biju Menon) and Kannan (Vineeth Sreenivasan) are Gold Agents from Thrissur, the Gold Capital of India. The movie portrays their travel to Mumbai to distribute gold and the following mishaps they face at their journey.

Title: 263. Enkilum Chandrike
Content: An imaginary rural place called Koodanthonda, a club in that village and and a series of incidents that revolve around the marriage of the Chandrika.

Title: 264. Kerala Varma Pazhassi Raja
Content: Kerala Varma Pazhassi Raja is a 2009 Malayalam historical drama film based on the life of Pazhassi Raja, a Hindu king who fought against the British in the 18th century.

Title: 265. Sethurama Iyer CBI
Content: Sethurama Iyer and the CBI re-open an old case upon hearing from a death-row criminal that he didn't commit one of the seven murders he was convicted of.

Title: 266. Theevandi
Content: Theevandi is a political satire depicted through light humor where the protagonist Bineesh hardly knows a thing even about himself.

Title: 267. Kallan D'Souza
Content: Kallan D'Souza and his friend, get by in life committing petty thefts. CI Manoj is a corrupt police officer who confiscates a huge amount of hawala money, and plans to pocket a big portion of it with his team, rather than turning it in.

Title: 268. Wolf
Content: When the police try to unravel the truth behind a series of mysterious crimes in a locality, they face an unexpected situation.

Title: 269. Vikruthi
Content: Mistaking the sleeping passenger on his train for a drunk, a young man posts a picture of him online, unaware of his impulsive act's ugly repercussions.

Title: 270. In
Content: An enthusiastic and diligent journalist follows a set of serial murders that rocks her city. She tries to solve the crime not knowing that the murderer could be very close to home.

Title: 271. Route Map
Content: The story is based on the events that took place in a flat during Covid-19.

Title: 272. In the Name of Love!
Content:
As per a recent report, since 2009 - more than 17 thousand girls from Kerala and more 15 thousand girls from Mangalore from Hindu and Christian communities has been converted to Islam and most of them ended up landing in Syria, Afghanistan and other ISIS and Taliban influential areas. In spite of accepting this facts and numbers of conversion and eloped girls, erstwhile Chief Ministers from CPM and Congress party and relentless claim by RSS - there is hardly any action is visible on ground zero. No specific data available... no confirmed evidences are being attended... Police & administration are muffled... 'Government' is in denial mode (clearly due to possible erosion of respective vote bank). As a result - rampant religious conversion through deep-rooted indoctrination network taken over Kerala like fire in hay... simply rescinding 'god's own country', silently and inevitably. Like light in the end of the tunnel, on Supreme Court's intervention, NIA started investigating 90 odd cases.

Whatever politics been brewing behind... whatever international conspiracy being hatched... there is no denial to the fact the thousands and thousands of daughters of India are getting eloped and getting vanished in to the blues of middle-eastern deserts.

We have seen the tears of the mothers of the eloped girls...we have heard the cry of their despair...! This important documentary have tried to hear the cry of mother earth... tried to feel the melancholy of a country - who is losing her daughters in thousands, every year.

Title: 273. Madhura Manohara Moham
Content: Town of Kumbazha, the lives of Manu and Meera's family are forever altered by an unexpected truth. As the unshakeable foundation crumbles, they embark on a tumultuous journey, challenging societal norms.

Title: 274. Vellam
Content: An alcoholic is left stranded by society, friends and family until he successfully completes his de-addiction. Will they accept him when he is clean and sober?

Title: 275. Attention Please
Content: An aspiring script writer narrating his plots over booze to his 4 flat-mates.

Title: 276. Kochaal
Content: Sreekuttan is irked and belittled by his townsfolk mockingly calling him Kochaal due to his short stature. His ambition is to become a police officer and decides to prove himself in uniform. Will his dream come true ?

Title: 277. Anarkali
Content: The story of a Naval officer who falls in love with the gorgeous daughter of a harsh and disapproving Vice Admiral.

Title: 278. Adi
Content: Nandu, has been earning a living in Saudi and is engaged to Geethika. They get married but while returning from the church they get in a fight with two men on a bike.

Title: 279. Mr. Fraud
Content: A prominent person from Delhi reach a palace,which is well known for its tradition and royalty to solve an issue. Consequently, instead of a solution, the issue becomes more and more complicated.

Title: 280. Thuramukham
Content: The famous protests against the 'chappa' system that was practiced in the Cochin harbor during the 1950s.

Title: 281. Malayankunju

Title: 282. Iyobinte Pusthakam

Title: 283. 4 Years

Title: 284. Kilometers and Kilometers

Title: 285. Paappan

Title: 286. Operation Java

Title: 287. Pookkaalam

Title: 288. Sesham Mikeil Fathima
Content: The journey of a Malabari Muslim woman who pursues a dream of becoming a football commentator.

Title: 289. Karnan Napoleon Bhagat Singh
Content: A larceny leads to murder and Roopesh Raghavan, a young man who has cleared police recruitment tests and awaits posting.

Title: 290. 19 (1) (a)

Title: 291. Anukoni Athidhi

Title: 292. Onnam Sakshi Parethan

Title: 293. Aadu - Oru Bheegara Jeevi Aanu 2
