Content: Rishi Ram and his sister Rithu Ram, both of whom are martial arts instructors settled in Rishikesh. Their peaceful life is turned chaotic when they cross paths with a notorious martial arts gang, leading to a spree of furious violence.

Title: 715. Oru Mexican Aparatha
Content: The film, set in a college campus, narrates how the students established the political party Students Federation of India.

Title: 716. The Arab, The Camel, and P. Madhavan Nair
Content: Madhavan finally falls in love and decides to marry his girl. But a late night incident forces Madhavan to take a crazy journey.

Title: 717. Thirike
Content: A young crafty man kidnaps his own brother, who has Down Syndrome, from his adoptive parents in an attempt to reclaim his past.

Title: 718. Vadakkum Nathan
Content: The film opens with a mother and son coming to Hardwar to perform last rites of her elder son who had run away from home and is believed to have died. But the mother sees her long lost son on the banks of River Ganga and takes him back to the family. He is Bharath Pisharody a brilliant Sanskrit professor who is respected and loved by everyone including his cousin and lover Meera. But on his day of marriage he runs away leaving behind a heart-broken Meera and her father. Now Pisharody is different man and his family and friends believes that he is on drugs. But actually, the man is mentally disturbed as he suffers from deep depression. Soon his brother discover papers relating to his treatment for mental illness from his locked suitcase. Now everyone starts seeing him in a different way, which leads to the final twist. How Meera helps him come out of this difficult situation in life forms the rest of the gripping tale.

Title: 719. Chandrettan Evideya
Content: Chandramohan keeps receiving calls from his wife asking for his whereabouts, much to his annoyance.

Title: 720. Chaappa Kurish
Content: A lost cellphone connects two men from the two extremes of the society and affects their life beyond which they could have imagined.

Title: 721. Thuruppu Gulan
Content: A kind-hearted street-rowdy manages his own problems while his fathers mate's daughter arrives. He promises to help her and succeeds in it.

Title: 722. Indian Rupee
Content: An unemployed youth Jayaprakash, dreams big fortunes in the field of real estate business, and therefore, faces a lot of obstacles in the path towards his goal.

Title: 723. No Way Out
Content: After investing Rs 1 crore in a business before the pandemic lockdown, David is neck deep in debts and under immense pressure. As his final hope fades, he decided to end his life. But does fate another trick up its sleeve?

Title: 724. Adrishyam
Content: Revolves around the case of a missing girl (Anandhi), and there are too many people looking for her in parallel investigations. Nandakumar (Narain) and his team are on the lookout for her, as directed by a top police officer Purushothaman (Prathap Pothen) who cannot get directly involved with the case.

Title: 725. Thadavu
Content: Geetha, a solitary play school teacher, grapples with a dire existence. Diagnosed with a life-threatening illnesses, she plots a crime to access medical aid available to jail inmates.

Title: 726. Kottayam
Content: A police officer is found raped and murdered but political machinations force the investigating team to act in a manner which denies justice to the family. The search for the culprits takes the team to the borderlands of India and China.

Title: 727. Daayam
Content: Amidst the patriarchal structures and cultural dogmas of Indian society, a teenage girl must navigate her way through the loss of a parent and discover her own path to adulthood in this poignant coming-of-age tale.

Title: 728. Aakashaganga II
Content: Arathi, accepts a challenge to test the authenticity of an 'Ashram' that claims to help its followers talk to the dead. To her surprise, she communicates with her dead mother who leads her to the dark and hidden secrets of her own family.

Title: 729. Kolambi
Content: An elderly couple are destined to live amidst these silenced loudspeakers called Kolaambi. But the onus of a dark secret disturbs them from time to time.

Title: 730. Makalkku
Content: A mentally ill woman gives birth to Manasi, who is raised in the mental asylum by Dr Warrier. However, despite his efforts to adopt Manasi, she is taken away by the state social welfare department.

Title: 731. Dear Vaappi
Content: Basheer, who is a tailor by profession, and his daughter Amira, who is a model and has big dreams about her future.

Title: 732. Prathi Poovankozhi
Content: Madhuri (Manju Warrier) an ordinary sales girl takes extra ordinary revenge against Antappn (Roshan Andrews) who misbehaved to her during a bus journey

Title: 733. Ivide
Content: Ivide is a crime-drama starring Prithviraj Sukumaran who plays an investigation officer named Varun Blake. Nivin Pauly who is Krish Hebbar, a CIO of a leading Techie company. A string of incidents in Atlanta, sets the pace of the film as the life of Varun and Krish gets entangled in the midst of it.

Title: 734. The Great Indian Road Movie
Content: On regaining his vision after a cornea transplant, a nine-year-old boy embarks on a journey to explore India along with his father.

Title: 735. Kuri
Content: A middle-aged man wins a lottery and a group of people aim at this prize money. The plot is unveiled through a lot of twists and turns giving an unexpected twist to the thrilling tale.

Title: 736. Chinthamani Kolacase
Content: Story of a highly successful criminal lawyer (Suresh Gopi) who brings his own version of street justice upon his clients after freeing them.

Title: 737. Bhagavan Dasante Ramrajyam
Content: A misperception that developed among Vannathikkavu locals over a young man who portrays Lord Srirama in a ballet drama that was performed at the temple festival.

Title: 738. Bonamy
Content: Bonamy is the journey of a stray puppy through 2 children's life. The 8-year-old girl's love and affection for the dog and her helplessness where she has to leave it alone at some point in her life, and the 10-year-old boy's struggle to find a shelter for the puppy and how he manages to achieve it. The film also conveys how true love and compassion can bring happiness to one's life.

Title: 739. Loham
Content: A gold-smuggling deal goes awry, and an array of characters becomes involved.

Title: 741. Mummy & Me
Content: The film revolves around a family of Jewel. She is a college student and likes independence. She has a very caring mother, who fears everything jewel do and a loving father. She hates her mother who criticize for everything. Meanwhile her family friend falls in love with her. Soon she met a guy through chat and he makes her to leave her worries and encourages her. She began to love her mother and brother. Thus the family feels happy. She fell in love with the chat friend and film ends with whom she decides to marry. Great family story.

Title: 742. Malarvaadi Arts Club
Content: Five friends are disappointed about the way their favorite hangout Malarvaadi Arts Club is headed. They take the responsibility of reviving the club in their own hands.

Title: 743. Baba Kalyani
Content: Very intelligent police officer comes to investigate in Kochi for terrorism and terrorist.

Title: 744. Abu, Son of Adam
Content: A poor aging couple struggle to fulfill their lifelong dream of going to Mecca for pilgrimage.

Title: 745. Chota Mumbai
Content: The daily lives of Vasco Da Gama and his friends in a fraction of Cochin, called Chota Mumbai is portrayed in this comedy.

Title: 746. Aadya Rathri
Content: Manoharan is the last word for the villagers of Mullakkara. The marriage broker has been finding ideal match for youth in his village for 22 years. Will his thoughts on love and marriage change when Ashwathy enters the scene?

Title: 747. Cousins
Content: Sam is stuck somewhere in the past, courtesy a mishap that occurred six years back, that had almost cost him his life. The psychiatrist suggests that he goes on a trip to Manipal where he was when the tragedy took place, so that his recent memories might be recovered. Off he goes on the journey with his cousins Georgy, Pauly and Tony hoping to find out what had actually transpired during his life at Manipal.

Title: 749. Pulival Kalyanam
Content: Hari's and Ganga's mobile phones got exchanged accidently and they started getting misleading calls....

Title: 750. Hello
Content: A drunkard, but intelligent advocate and his side-kick tries to protect a woman from the threats against her life.

Title: 751. The Address
Content: A single yet brilliant court martial session of a dalit soldier accused of killing a Captain and attempting to kill another captain

Title: 752. Kinavally
Content: Vivek is celebrating his wedding anniversary with his wife Ann, who decides to invite four of his friends to surprise her husband. But, their celebrations are short-lived as they start experiencing paranormal activities around them.

Title: 753. Kadal Kuthira
Content: Anirudh confused to murder for his best friend and was sentenced to life imprisonment. To celebrate the one month parole he was granted, Anirudh reached a resort and enjoyed the stay full spirit. All the financial support for his stay, was provided by the father of his friend for whom he went to the jail. A girl named Yamini, whom the father had arranged for him along with liquors, conquered his heart. They fell in love inseparably and got married finally. Mean while the family members of the murdered man knew about this. Totake revenge of the murder, the family members hired a team to kill Anirudh. The happy life of Anirudh and Yamini, turned to a risky one, the rest of trilling part is one the screen.

Title: 754. Marykkundoru Kunjaadu
Content: Solomon, a simple village man who is afraid of almost everything around him. His life changes when he becomes a good friend with a tough man.

Title: 755. Seniors
Content: Four 'not-so-young' friends re-join college to relive the awesome moments they had 12 years ago. But things are not what they seem.

Title: 756. Edakkad Battalion 06
Content: Shafeek's father wanted him to become a chef, but he chose to serve his country instead. On his annual leave from work, Shafeek, now a young soldier, must deal with his family, his bride to be and a gang involved in illegal activities.

Title: 757. Run Baby Run
Content: A reporter and a cameraman become try to uncover a political scam, but find themselves in trouble as they become involved in a grand political conspiracy.

Title: 758. God Bless You
Content: The plot revolves around what happens to Clara and Sam four hours a day. Sam's friend Vaishakh offers his owner the opportunity to work as a carrier for the smuggling gang. For the first time, Sam loses money and drugs. Knowing all this, Clara tries to find money for Sam.

Title: 760. Sherlock Toms
Content: An ardent fan of Sherlock Holmes from childhood, Thomas tries his best to solve issues like Sherlock Holmes. Thomas without losing his Sherlock Holmes instinct starts applying it in his line of work unveiling a major crime.

Title: 761. Lailaa O Lailaa
Content: Jayamohan is a business magnate who leads a hectic life. Things start going topsy-turvy when he gets married to Anjali. He begins facing problems that affect his business as well.

Title: 763. Sundari Gardens
Content: Suma, is a bold, quirky and geeky school librarian who lives with her mother. Suma meets Victor, the school's new English teacher, and as time passes, they get to know each other.

Title: 764. Mayavi
Content: Mahi is nicknamed Mayavi for his ability to beat up baddies stealthily without revealing his identity. He often ends up in jail. While serving time he develops a friendship with Balan, another convict. Balan's brother is seriously ill in hospital and is in need of an expensive operation. Meanwhile Mahi is picked as the lone lucky prisoner to be pardoned and released on Independence Day. With Balan unable to provide the funds from inside the jail and since his release is a long way off, Mahi promises to find a way to procure the money.

Title: 765. Praja
Content: Ex-don Zakkir Ali Hussein is living peacefully in the suburbs of Kochi and trying to begin a new life. However, due to the evil deeds of two dons and a corrupt politician, he is unable to live peacefully. Zakkir has to take the law into his hands and ultimately finish them off.

Title: 766. Salala Mobiles
Content: After his uncle helps Afsal to start a mobile shop, he gets happy and hopeful about future. However, things get complicated to him after he meets, Azhagarsamy, a creator of mobile applications.

Title: 767. Dakini
Content: Kuttan Pilla, Moly's long lost lover is kidnapped by the underworld king named Mayan. 4 grannies and Kuttappi with the help of Vikraman, a local gangster decide to go on a journey to fight the fierce don Mayan and bring back Kuttan Pilla.

Title: 768. Mask
Content: Mask tells the story of a police inspector who sets out to track down a thief.

Title: 769. Pattabhiraman
Content: It is the story of a warrior against food adulteration and challenges he faces because of that.

Title: 770. School Bus
Content: Joseph and Aparna are a couple with two children. Their son Aakash is a troublemaker and often rebuked for it. The intervention of certain characters makes their life highly complicated and the children too get affected.

Title: 771. Krishnam
Content: Akshay, a young and handsome college student and a talented dancer, enjoys a colorful college life. Although very popular among his peers, Akshay, who is smitten by Radhika, feels dejected after she neglects him.

Title: 772. Krishnankutty Pani Thudangi
Content: Unni, a male nurse, is known for reciting horror stories in a captivating manner. But one such recitation turns his life upside down.

Title: 773. Ee Adutha Kaalath
Content: The movie features the lives of six different persons from different strata of the social life of the city, interconnected due to unexpected events beyond their control.

Title: 774. Ayal Njanalla
Content: This film revolves around a businessman named Prakashan, whose family moved to Gujarat 15 years ago.

Title: 775. Daddy Cool
Content: A lazy police officer and his son passes through a set of incidents with a cricket player linked to betting and match fixing which later becomes serious as his son is kidnapped.

Title: 776. Ee Pattanathil Bhootham
Content: A great change occurs in life of poor children of a circus company when a spirit enters their life.But an evil megician wants spirit in his control and he is in search of it

Title: 777. Vimaanam
Content: The life of Venkateswaran, a differently-able man from Kerala. It showcases how Venkidi, who had hearing impairment, fought all odds and built a lightweight aircraft from recycled materials without any external support.

Title: 778. Ulta
Content: Story of a fictional town called Ponnapuram, where all the women are self-sufficient and trained to handle any situation. Their world is put to the test when a few men decide to take them down.

Title: 779. Vivaha Avahanam
Content: Political rivals Bhaskaran and Prabhakaran try to conduct the marriage of their children Swathi and Arun while they repeatedly misbehave.

Title: 781. Rasathanthram
Content: Premachandran, a carpenter by profession, dreams nothing but a lovely and peaceful life with his father. After taking an ill-treated maid, Kanmani, into care, he realizes the need of a woman in every man's life.

Title: 782. Kuttanpillayude Sivarathri
Content: Kuttan Pillai lives with his wife in a rural village and has an obsession with the jack fruit tree in his yard. During the Shivaratri festival, something strange happens that forms the main story.

Title: 783. Romans
Content: Two escaped convicts arrive at a remote village in Kerala near the border with Tamil Nadu. Villages mistake them as Catholic priests sent from Rome to reopen their long closed church.

Title: 784. Sharja To Sharja
Content: Nandhan comes to Kapithan family as Sheikh Jasim Khalidh Mehbani, their relative from Sharjah in order to save his brother's life.

Title: 785. Joyful Mystery
Content: A couple in Kerala, India, are on their way to a doctor's clinic to confirm a suspected pregnancy. Tension builds during the ride as the two discuss their future and how to handle the changes in their lives.

Title: 786. Kanal
Content: The film revolves around two families hailing from the South Indian state of Kerala who have spent some important years of their lives in the Middle East.

Title: 787. Iru
Content: During their campus life, classmates Rishi and Priya fall in love. Priya's father does not approve their relation based on caste differences. Ravindran, a friend of Priya's father, comes up with a plan to free Priya from Rishi.

Title: 788. Ullasam
Content: A fun-filled romantic movie in which two strangers from diverse backgrounds meet on a journey from Ooty to Kerala. The journey advances through different circumstances and coming across new people.

Title: 789. Thoppil Joppan
Content: Joppan's failed romance excuses him to be an alcoholic. Hoping to start a new life, he seeks out for some love but would fate favor him this time?

Title: 790. Ore Mukham
Content: An array of ex-college mates are being murdered by a common friend, Zachariah Pothen. Meanwhile, the police tries to stop the murders and a journalist tries to uncover the truth.

Title: 791. The Thriller
Content: Simon is the son of Joseph Palathinkal, a business multi millionaire. One night during the night patrol, Niranjan finds Simon stabbed and murdered on a highway. Who killed him? and why?

Title: 792. Nizhalkkuthu
Content: Kaliyappan, the last hangman of Travancore dynasty is dragging his remaining life by consuming alcohol and worshipping the Mother Goddess.

Title: 793. Ramante Edenthottam
Content: Raman lives a beautiful life in his forest resort. Malini visits Eden and the two meet and fall in love. The film travels through their relationship across a few years and how the two evolve as individuals.

Title: 794. Anwar
Content: The revenge of anwar against the terrorists who killed anwer's family in a bomb blast. After the Blast anwar plan a secrete mission to find the faces behind the Blast.

Title: 795. Immanuel
Content: Immanuel's life takes an odd turn when the publishing firm that he works for shuts down. He gets a job in an insurance company but faces severe hardships, which end up changing him as a person.

Title: 796. Isha
Content: The ghost of Isha, who was murdered by a few powerful men, possesses the body of a girl in a family that moves to a hill station bungalow. Isha is out there to take vengeance.

Title: 797. Kakshi: Amminippilla
Content: O.P.160/18 Kakshi: Amminippilla is an unusual court drama happening in Thalassery. This realistic court drama unveils interesting case from different layers with humor and emotions.

Title: 798. Madambi
Content: A loan shark in rural Kerala must face hurdles from corporate, enemies and his own family to keep his enterprise going.

Title: 799. Ennaalum Sarath..?
Content: Set in a college campus, the film deals with a riot started by the student community after a girl dies under mysterious circumstances. The probe into her death by the police forms the crux of the story.

Title: 800. Neermathalam Poothakaalam
Content: After her childhood friend Aami is hospitalised following a failed suicide attempt, a young woman named Merin sets out to find the reason behind the tragedy. Her search will lead Merin into the complex inner world of Aami and her various love affairs.

Title: 801. Panchavarnathatha
Content: The story of a bird charmer as he goes on to influence the lives of people while witnessing a change in his own.

Title: 802. Iblis
Content: The love of half-witted Vyshakh for the beautiful Fida and how it takes him places that are beyond reality.

Title: 803. Puthiya Mugham
Content: A simple college student suffering from a mild psychological disorder finds himself against a family of criminals.

Title: 804. Escape
Content: Pan Indian Thriller "Escape" which prioritizes the female character; Gayatri Suresh and Srividya Mullacheri in the lead roles will be released in five languages, The protagonist arrives at the relative's house with a pregnant friend due to some problems, and stays there without going back, suspecting some of the activities of the family members there. That night there was a psycho killer unexpectedly arriving at the house wearing a mask, the plot of the escape is the subsequent events happening in the night. Escape will be the first psycho-survival thriller Shot in Malayalam and dubbed in Kannada Tamil Telegu and Hindi.

Title: 805. Adithattu
Content: Adithattu denotes the 'lower strata in the society and the fishing community falls under this stratum. Adithattu will also explore the problems and livelihood of the fishermen community and will be a thriller subject.

Title: 806. Vegam
Content: VEGAM deals with the life of two youngsters played by Vineeth Kumar and Jacob Gregory who wants to make more money and lead a luxurious life. They decide to to do whatever it takes to make more money and end up getting into more and more trouble. By the time they realize the danger, it is too late to come out of it. Samskruthy Shenoy plays the love life of Vineeth Kumar. Prathap Pothen does the role of a Gulf returnee while Swapna Menon does the role of his daughter.

Title: 807. Lalbagh
Content: Sara's husband Tom gets food-poisoned after a birthday party, and police suspect it was a deliberate attempt to murder him. And they are after the culprit.

Title: 808. Neelathamara
Content: A woman, seduced by the legend of the blue lotus into believing that her lover truly cares for her, learns hard lessons from life and in the end blossoms as if she herself is the lotus of truth.

Title: 809. Akashvani
Content: Movie narrates the story of a couple, Akash and Vani. They go on a personal trip to spend some quality time with each other and the resulting incidents are plotted.

Title: 810. Kamuki
Content: Achaamma is forced to make a promise to her father; she would not elope and marry anyone like her elder sister. While she keeps her word for the longest time, she begins to stumble when she meets Hari, her fellow mate at her college.

Title: 811. The Train
Content: The lives and dreams of a few Keralaites in Mumbai who disappeared in the Mumbai train bombings of 11 July 2006. To add masala to the situation, the whole incident could have been stopped if the superiors had listened to Mamootty, a super cop who is a keen observer.

Title: 812. 101 Weddings
Content: 101 Weddings is a humor based story set against the backdrop of a mass marriage ceremony which are taking place together at one platform as part of a mass marriage ceremony.

Title: 813. Paapam Cheyyathavar Kalleriyatte
Content: Christians believe that marriages are made in heaven. It is a satirical take on the belief, which is reinforced through marriage rituals, about the Christian marriage and the reality of it as seen around us.

Title: 814. Arike
Content: Anuradha plays cupid and brings Shantanu and Kalpana together but a freak accident distances Kalpana and him. Shantanu then realizes that Anuradha is the one who truly loves him.

Title: 815. Goodalochana
Content: A group of four friends take the easy route to accomplish their dreams. Even when things go haywire, they try to find an easy way out but, fate has other plans for them and all hell breaks loose when their decisions go wrong.

Title: 816. Varsham
Content: Venu (Mammootty) leads a happy and contented middle class life with his family. He starts a small scale finance firm, as a service and soon his business flourishes well. This does not go well with his competitors and they join together against him.

Title: 817. Sarvopari Palakkaran
Content: Jose, a Circle Inspector of Police, Special Branch from Trissur, Kerala, who comes from a respected and well-known conservative christian family, is on the lookout for a suitable bride who fits within his idea of an ideal woman.

Title: 818. Ira
Content: Aryan is like every other lover, who finds the world a better place just because of that one person. Life takes a sudden twist when he is implicated of a serious crime which he didn't commit and Rajeev who comes as a savior in his life.

Title: 819. Beyond the 7 Seas
Content: The mysterious and dark forces spanning across distant continents, tactfully brought him to that Secret Island. Then, it became his mission to redeem his mother from the clutches of the evil who were camouflaged as guardian angels.

Title: 820. Thank You
Content: The film is shown to be a reflection of the current socio-political system, based on the violence against women.It revolves around a person who arrives in Trivandrum city who takes a ride from place to place in an Autorickshaw. His name or whereabouts are not revealed, and he just travels from place to place in the auto rickshaw. The questions about his whereabouts form the rest of the story.

Title: 821. Paavada
Content: Joy a young man who leads a carefree life. Joy acquaintance Babu Joseph, an English professor, and they reminiscence some seemingly forgotten memories.

Title: 822. Mayamohini
Content: Balakrishnan is cheated by his girlfriend, in order to make the family happy, he hires a girl, Mayamohini and pretends to be in love. Things take a turn when they realize that Mayamohini is a man.

Title: 823. Ellam Settanu
Content: The movie narrates the story of a film crew. The film presents their one day eventful life mixed with comedy. It is a feel-good family film laced with humor.

Title: 825. Sheela
Content: A young woman who travels to Kerala in search of answers to a serious situation that occurs in Bengaluru.

Title: 826. Achayans
Content: The Thottathil family set out on a journey to find extreme fun and enjoyment. Accidentally, two girls join their journey. The rest of the journey unfolds with lots of twists and turns.

Title: 827. No Man's Land
Content: Working as a housekeeper cum escort, Sumitra trudges along with her uneventful life in a resort at a hill station in Kerala. Haunted with self-pity, she finds solace in alcohol.

Title: 828. Trivandrum Lodge
Content: A small residential lodge at Kochi becomes the witness for many stories, of many people, their search for love, money, sex, and true meaning of life.

Title: 829. Khaddama
Content: The story of a woman who moves to Saudi Arabia as a maid.

Title: 830. Binary
Content: Five youngsters who are unexpectedly rendered jobless, fall prey to the Cyber Crimes masterminded by Sam Wilson. Following a probe into the murder of Sam's Henchwoman Sandra, will they nab Sam Wilson?

Title: 831. Photographer
Content: Dijo John, a wild-life photographer, has evidence against a corrupt police officer. His twin brother Joy John sets out to trace him when Dijo goes missing.

Title: 832. Parankimala
Content: When the owner finds out about the affair between his son and their maid, he throws her out of his house. Later, she sacrifices her life for her lover.

Title: 835. Uppumaavu
Content: Mistreated by the husband, a crippled mother with two kids fights for their betterment. One of the children grows up to become the District Collector. Can he prevail over the drug mafia by standing against those malpractices?

Title: 836. Bioscope
Content: Diwakaran meets DuPont who holds bioscope shows. He gets fascinated by the machine and buys it from DuPont in order to hold bioscope shows in his village. But later he gets superstitious about it.

Title: 837. Padam Onnu Oru Vilapam
Content: Shahina is studying in school but she can't go to school because she is pregnant. And she conceived from her divorced husband..

Title: 838. London Bridge
Content: A millionaire in London fall in love with two girls at the same time and finding the lifepartner

Title: 839. Vaanku
Content: Razia, who belongs from a conservative town of Kerala, lives happily with her family. During her final year semester, Razia and her friends discuss their desires where she unveils her one wish to fulfill before the end of her student life.

Title: 840. Kohinoor
Content: The story develops during the 1987-88 period. It was a time when Mohanlal's 'Rajavinte Makan' and Mammootty's 'Athirathram' were such a rage among youth. Louis wishes to be like Vincent Gomas and Tharadas, the heroes in these movies.

Title: 841. Gangster
Content: Akbar, a powerful man of Mangalore underworld, shares his business lead with Mani Menon and Uncle Sam. They share a good relationship until Anto, grandson of Uncle Sam, creates havoc.

Title: 842. Bhagyadevatha
Content: A cable operator pushes his wife out of his family when the required amount of dowry is not paid to him. Things change when she becomes winner of a lottery. Now he wants to pull her to his family by any means.

Title: 843. Adventures of Omanakuttan
Content: An introverted daydreamer and a ghost-hunter pair up.

Title: 844. Kadhavaseshan
Content: Renuka trying to find the reason for Gopi's suicude by going through his past.

Title: 845. Koothara
Content: Three engineering students whose life takes a twist after meeting a mysterious man who teaches them the real meaning of life.

Title: 846. The Proposal
Content: When all the hard but crookedly planned attempts to succeed in life hilariously fails, Davis ventures to arranged marriage plan with one tag line - "no dowry asked but get me a visa to settle in a foreign country". When Davis meets Sandra through a matrimonial website, his story takes a turn.

Title: 847. Kuttanadan Marpappa
Content: When John Paul, a wedding photographer, meets Jessy for the first time, he instantly finds himself attracted to her. His crush eventually turns into love, the feeling which is reciprocated from Jessy's end too.

Title: 848. Nishiddho
Content: In one of the bustling cities of Kerala, a migrant idol-maker from Bengal, desperately needing help with his uncle's cremation, and a tough Tamil midwife, who moonlights as a funeral priest, forge a fragile bond that is threatened when she is accused of a heinous crime.

Title: 849. Balettan
Content: Balettan (Mohanlal) is a man who sacrifices to help everyone he can , but when a time in need comes no one is there to help him.

Title: 850. Artist
Content: Gayatri meets Michael and starts living with him in spite of his arrogance. She avoids all the negatives and tries to deal with him but things change when Michael loses his eyesight in an accident.

Title: 851. IDI: Inspector Dawood Ibrahim
Content: Inspector Dawood Ibrahim who dreams of becoming a cop. His sole aim is to catch lawbreakers. The movie is all about how he fulfills his dreams.

Title: 852. Purple Poppins
Content: On 17 July 2001, Shirley committed suicide by jumping off a high-rise building while her younger brother Sherin witnessed it. Despite knowing the reason, Sherin feels helpless.

Title: 854. Kidu
Content: Kidu is the story of a class teacher, who becomes a great influence in the life of five naughty students when a dramatic incident turns their lives upside down. Will they be able to sustain the tough times?

Title: 855. Sathyam Paranja Viswasikuvo
Content: Geetha, Suni's wife, bears the brunt of his negligent lifestyle and often quarrels with him over it. After witnessing a gruesome accident, Suni and his friends find their lives taking some really unexpected turns.

Title: 856. Njan Steve Lopez
Content: A college student witnesses a gang attack and as his curiosity behind the encounter tries to get the better of him, he realizes that his dad and the police are involved.

Title: 857. Rasikan
Content: Shivankutty earns a living by selling tickets in black. One day, he witnesses a policeman's murder in broad daylight and stands up against the culprit alone.

Title: 858. Phantom
Content: Phantom Pailey (Mammootty) is a very mysterious stranger with that seems a shady background that arrives in a village , and helps the people fight against local goons.

Title: 859. The King and the Commissioner
Content: Two detectives investigate the death of an intelligence agent found in a river after she discovered a Pakistani plot for a terrorist attack.

Title: 860. Monsoon Mangoes
Content: D.P Pallickal, an amateur film maker who claims he is the next film legend. D.P has great passion, but lacks talent. His family and friends constantly make fun of his amateurishness of his masterpiece short films.

Title: 861. Chiri
Content: The film is based on the misdeeds of a friend who arrives at Mathew's uninvited wedding

Title: 862. Daivame Kaithozham K. Kumarakanam
Content: The movie is a comic take on gender role reversal between K Kumar and his wife to experience life of one another, with God's permission.

Title: 863. Life Is Beautiful
Content: Vinay and Sindhu are an ideal couple as they love each other a lot. Vinay takes up a job as a Malayalam teacher in a public school and teaches with a motive to instill values in his students.

Title: 864. Bus Conductor
Content: Kunjakka, a bus conductor, who is loved and admired by all faces a great problem.

Title: 865. 1921: Puzha Muthal Puzha Vare
Content: Based on the Malabar riots of 1921 and the Hindu genocide spearheaded by the Islamic extremist Variyankunnath Kunjahammad Haji.

Title: 866. Welcome to Central Jail
Content: Unnikuttan is a young man, who was born in the central jail. He considers jail as his second home. As a good Samaritan he takes on the punishments for petty crimes committed by others.

Title: 868. Mohanlal
Content: Meenu was born on the same day that Mollywood superstar Mohanlal first appeared on the silver screens across Kerala in the iconic movie Manjil Virinja Pookal.

Title: 869. Aby
Content: Aby is aspired to fly and make an aeroplane by his own without any formal engineering education. The movie depicts how the hero struggles to make his dream come true and the obstacles he faces on his way to success and achieve glory.

Title: 870. Rosapoo
Content: After suffering a loss in his brick-and-mortar duty-free shop, Shajahan finds it difficult to sustain his business. To make ends meet, he decides to take up odd jobs but to no avail.

Title: 871. Salaam Kashmier
Content: Sreekumar does all the domestic work in his family while his banker wife Suja is the breadwinner. All appears to be smooth until Tommy enters their life bringing back something which Sreekumar wants to run away from.

Title: 872. Ennodu Para I Love You Ennu
Content: Chandu, Azaad and Sanoop are friends at school and are trying hard to get girlfriends. At one point, one of their pursuits turn a lot more than a 'quest for girlfriend.'

Title: 874. Mera Naam Shaji
Content: The lives of three men sharing the same name intertwine, leading to a series of hilarious incidents.

Title: 875. Mr. Marumakan
Content: Ashok Raj, though a lawyer by profession has indeed dedicated his life to revive the lost glory that the drama troupe Bharatha Kalakshetram has once enjoyed.

Title: 876. Nayika
Content: Gracy is a leading star until she suddenly disappears from the silver screen. Now, Aleena has come to do a documentary and unravels her sudden disappearance from the silver screen.

Title: 877. Kadam Katha
Content: Two friends, Cleatus and Giri work together to repay their debts. As their life goes on, they meet Sreekumar who offers a solution to end their woes provided they agree to his one condition.

Title: 878. Yathrakarude Sradhakku
Content: Two strangers pretend to be husband and wife in order to use a pre-reserved ticket bought from a scalper to get on a train , because of last second plans ,find that their lives intersect and later fall in love.

Title: 879. Ividam Swargamanu
Content: a farmer's family fight against the land maffias

Title: 880. Kshanikam
Content: An irreversible moment - A mother loses her son..P. A desperate trial of fostering - Even motherhood goes under threat. - Finally realises no one can be replaced.

Title: 881. Calling Bell
Content: A lady monster kills a woman and takes her place. The husband learns it through a saint and contains her in the house abondoning it. The husband's younger brother comes to the house with a band of friends and faces the monster unknowingly. The story unfolds as the monster goes through a lot of trouble from people buzzing the calling bell and interrupting her mission to finish off the band of friends.

Title: 882. Zachariayude Garbhinikal
Content: The film narrates the incidents in the life of a gynaecologist and five women who come into his life each with unconventional/illegitimate pregnancies. Lal acts as the gynaecologist and Asha Sharreth does the role of doctor's wife. Sanusha plays the role of an eighteen-year-old girl who refuses to abort her child and reveal the child's father. In the end, she gives her baby to the gynaecologist and his wife who don't have children of their own. After some months, she visits the doctor's house and leaves him a book. And from reading one of the story in the book that she specially marked he figures out that she bore the child of her father. Rima's character is a nurse, while Geetha plays an elderly woman who gets pregnant through artificial insemination.[7] Aju Varghese appears as Ajmal who has strong feelings for Fatima. However, due to their height difference, he is unable to confide his love for her.

Title: 883. My Story
Content: Jay and Tara, fall in love on the sets of their film. However, Tara is set to marry David. Twenty years later, Jay is a big movie star but is still in love with Tara and decides to travel to Lisbon in search of her.

Title: 884. Paka (River of Blood)
Content: PAKA is a tale of a river that swells with the blood of two feuding families and a young couple that tries to overcome this hatred with their love.

Title: 885. And the Oskar Goes To..
Content: A real touching story of a movie maker who struggle to make his own movie passionately and sacrifice his life for his debut Movie, A must watch and inspiring narration.

Title: 886. Padayottam
Content: The story revolves around a local don Chenkal Raghu, from Thiruvananthapuram and how the society perceives him.

Title: 887. Rain Rain Come Again
Content: A professor who is a devotee of Satan tries to add his students into his religion

Title: 888. Jalam
Content: Jalam is about a widowed mother struggling to raise her child in the city alone. After losing her husband in an accident, the widow must face many challenges with her child in the city, for a piece of land to live.

Title: 889. Maya Bazar
Content: Rameshan, a business man, spends his income on the patients of a local hospital. However, things take a turn when Rameshan witnesses an accident in which the victim is his lookalike.

Title: 890. Angels
Content: Hameem Haider (Indrajith) is a police officer who meets with an accident while investigating a series of murders and is forced to take a break from his duties. Years later the unsolved murders are picked up by a reality TV show.

Title: 891. Goal
Content: Sam, a football player, gets admission in a prestigious international school under sports quota. His life changes for the better when he falls in love with a girl from the same school.

Title: 892. Oru Murai Vanthu Paarthaya
Content: Prakshan runs an electrical hardware shop and is known by all the people of that village. As the story progresses, the entry of a mysterious girl in Prakshan's life unfolds a lot of suspense and comical moments.

Title: 893. Mosayile Kuthira Meenukal
Content: An unusual friendship between two escaped convicts is formed during a cat and mouse chase, which leads them to the beautiful islands of Lakshadweep.

Title: 894. Oruvattam Koodi
Content: Erstwhile lovers have a chance meeting two decades later and they stay together a few days exploring the emotions hitherto not shared, the man proves to be the ideal friend to the lady in distress.

Title: 895. God's Own Country
Content: Several story lines intertwine, linked by cold hard cash and the quest for justice.

Title: 896. 1 by Two
Content: Hari and Ravi are identical twins who share a very delicate and special emotional bond. When Hari dies in an accident, Ravi goes into a strange state of psychosis. Yousuf, a cop tries to uncover the mystery involved in the case.

Title: 897. Ameera
Content: Ameera tells the story of an inter caste married couple and incidents happening to their children after they pass away.

Title: 898. Padmasree Bharat Dr. Saroj Kumar
Content: The movie is a satirical comedy which revolves around Saroj Kumar, a famous actor and his antics.

Title: 899. My God
Content: Sam Thottunkal, the younger son of Thomas Scaria and Zareena is a teenager, is an introvert. It is when Sam's life becomes more and more complicated, he gets acquainted with Adiraja. Movie narrates the resulting events in the life of Sam.

Title: 900. Signature
Content: While capturing the scenic beauty of Attappady, the film highlights the burning issues of the people living in the area.

Title: 901. Khali Purse of Billionaires
Content: The journey of Vijay and Das, their passion, struggles, friendship and the challenges they face to fulfill their dreams.

Title: 902. Koshichaayante Paramb
Content: An uninvited guest enters the lives of three ordinary friends like an angel of God. It is too late when they realize that the angel is Satan himself.

Title: 903. Lion
Content: An honest man neglected by his family members who are high grade officials wins the election as an independent candidate against his father and becomes high grade minister, rises in the political field.

Title: 904. Lakshyam
Content: This film focuses on two people, an IT professional and a person from the slums. The story progresses with their journey from Peermade to Eranakulam as convicts.

Title: 905. Janapriyan
Content: Priyadarshan is from a small village who lands at Kochi to join the temporary job in the Taluk Office, in the place of Vaishakhan, who is forced to go for a long leave. Vaishakhan doesn't care about completing pending works in the office, as he believes that his future is as a successful filmmaker.

Title: 906. The Gambinos
Content: The film revolves around a mother and her four sons, leading their criminal lives, until the arrival of a young man called Mustafa, who brings unexpected twists and turns to the tale.

Title: 907. Rani Chithira Marthanda
Content: A captivating family drama that explores the complex relationship between a father and son.

Title: 908. One-Man Show
Content: The fate of Jayakrishnan's (Jayaram) life depends on a TV game show. During the show the host pries into Jayakrishnan's past.

Title: 909. Keerthi Chakra
Content: Based on a real life incident that happened during the Kargil War.

Title: 910. Rasaleela
Content: Set in the backdrop of olden Kerala in India, a newly-wed women becomes widow the next day of her marriage. Later she gets attracted to the helper of a local god-man who arrives there to remove the bad omens that plague the ancient family.

Title: 911. Fireman
Content: The leakage of a massive LPG tank causes a group of brave firemen, police and local people to put their life on the line when a total city evacuation is impossible because a prison lies in the radius.

Title: 912. Bhayanakam
Content: A World War I veteran is sent to Kuttanad as a postman to deliver money orders and letters to the families of soldiers. Soon, the happiness that his visits brought to the families turns into sadness with the outbreak of the World War II.

Title: 913. Swami Ayyappan
Content: Swami Ayyappan, who was known as Manikandan during his lifetime, is a mythological super-hero. He is wise and well-versed in martial arts. He is soft and kind to the good and a nightmare to evil-doers. He had incarnated as the son of Lords Shiva and Vishnu to annihilate the demoness Mahishi and destroy evil.

Title: 914. Nannayikoode
Content: The film is in speculative family genre, in a world that is filled with prejudices, divided in the name of class, caste and creed, this film will be an eye opener as it narrates the tale of seven beings who come from different cultural backgrounds and live like a family sharing love, respect and care for one another. As mentioned already they are not bonded by blood relation but with love and trust for each other. They share their lives under the same roof and are in complete harmony. The society which is always critical of diversions from the established norms look at them with curiosity and uneasiness. They stand united against all the circumstances thrown to them by the harsh realities of life. They do not surrender to the turmoil that they have to confront in their existence and they stand united against all the odds that they are subjected to. The family members become the pillars of strength for each other during the time of crisis. They instill in each other courage and confidence to face all the hurdles thrown to them. This family mentioned in that film is an epitome of sincerity and commitment which is essential to row forward in film. The film includes dramatic situations which adds to the depth of the tale narrated in the film.

Title: 915. Chronic Bachelor
Content: Satyapratapan (Mammootty) and Kuruvila (Innocent) are chronic bachelors. Sp's sister Sandhya lives as a paying guest in their neighbourhood. Problems begin when Mukesh and Harishree Ashokan join Mammootty and Rambha joins Sandhya.

Title: 916. 14 February
Content: "14 February" revolves around a successful filmmaker in search of a new script for his upcoming project. Intriguingly, his wife, a radio station manager, suggests the fascinating life story of Anand aka RJ Anandu, an RJ working with her, as a potential inspiration for a romantic movie. Together with another female RJ Amaalu aka Amrita, they embark on a journey to unravel Anand's past.Anand's tale unfolds with intense passion, where he once had a lover falsely accuse him. Despite his innocence being proven by his own cop father, his lover abandons him midway through their relationship. As the story progresses, the filmmaker and Amrita work tirelessly to reunite Anand with his lost love, while simultaneously crafting an enchanting romantic movie based on his extraordinary life.

Title: 917. Arikil Oraal
Content: A creative executive at an advertising agency and his girlfriend try to solve the mystery of their friend Icha who seemingly starts to appear at two different places at the same time.

Title: 918. Deira Diaries
Content: It is the story about a man told through the viewpoints of various others. His name is Yosuf in the story. The man from Kerala, India lives in UAE for 30 years. He touches the lives of many through his simple words and actions.

Title: 920. Rappakal
Content: The story of a mom and her adopted son and how their life changes after a long-awaited reunion of the joint family.

Title: 921. Makeup Man
Content: Balu and Soorya, who get married and then realize that they have to start their dream life. As luck would have it, Soorya becomes an actress, and Balu pretends to be her makeup man.

Title: 923. Husbands in Goa
Content: Husbands in Goa is a story of three friends - Jerry Thomas (Advocate), Murali Govind (Chartered Accountant) and Arjun (Interior Designer). The three of them are faced with a common dilemma, as they are all harassed by certain behavioral traits of their wives. To get away from them, the three friends plan a pleasure trip to Goa. On their journey to Goa they meet Sunny who they befriend but fail to realize the trouble that he attracts due to his usual drunkenness. Theirshort holiday turns into a crazy ride as they keep trying to get themselves out of comedic situations.

Title: 924. Bannerghatta
Content: Storyline One night Ashiq, an acting driver comes to know that his sister,who went out of town for a job interview is in a dangerous situation.

Title: 925. Annan Thambi
Content: Appu and Achu are twin brothers who do not get along with each other since childhood. When their enemies create misunderstandings between them, they bay for each other's blood.

Title: 926. Fukri
Content: An aristocratic family welcomes a long-lost heir, but the young fellow may be leading his relatives down the garden path.

Title: 927. Ring Master
Content: Follows the relation between a canine film star and its trainer.

Title: 928. Chattambinadu
Content: A man having a dirty connection with a village in the past returns to proper the place which is ruled by a local gangster.

Title: 929. Pattam Pole
Content: A trad guy and a rad gal must make it work.

Title: 931. Thattum Purath Achuthan
Content: Achuthan lives in a village full of fun loving and vibrant people. One fine day he receives a letter addressed to Lord Krishna, which changes his life forever. The letter leads him into the world of Jayalakshmi and into her attic as well.

Title: 932. Akasham Kadann
Content: Every beautiful life can turn upside down anytime anywhere. Life is beautiful when we don't see the pain of those around us. But we should also know about those whose dreams have been shattered in the trials of life. That is when we become human. With such beautiful hope every parent waits for a baby. Think about the state of mind of such parents if a child is born with a mental or physical disability. The film is about the inner lives of many families with children with mental and physical conditions. The Rauf - Sajna couple (Vijayakumar - Priya Sreejith) started raising their second child (Russell) with great anticipation. But the child's illness at the age of five brings the family to tears. While passing the days in despair, Rauf - Sajna slowly begins to come to terms with reality when they hear a speech by Father Davis Chiramel at a regional gathering. Takes care of the baby as a challenge and lives for him. All of the painful and joyous experiences that this family faces from many, many times, go straight ahead together. Fazal (Maqbool Salman) who enters the family as a son-in-law as if for a reason, discovers the talent of the child and nurtures it through training and brings the child to a height. In the end, when the luck that a normal family can't even dream of reaches the family through that child, this movie becomes an inspiration for such families and a lot of messages for the society. Each and every scene in this movie is shot with a touch of comedy and is exciting for the audience.

Title: 933. Thanaha
Content: The story of two friends Vishnu and Roy who end up in the Police service after the death of their fathers. What follows is how Vishnu and Roy unravel the mystery behind the case of a missing culprit.

Title: 934. C/O Saira Banu
Content: In a bad turn of events, Joshua and Banu's life is shaken when Joshua becomes the convict in a court case. This is when Annie John Tharavadi, a reputed advocate becomes part of these happenings.

Title: 935. Bharathchandran I.P.S
Content: Bharatchandran IPS, a righteous City Police Commissioner who doesn't mind assaulting even his superior officers and powerful politicians while staging a one-man-fight against the corrupt political machinery prevailing in the state.

Title: 936. Oru Cinemakkaran
Content: Alby, who is a passionate and hardworking filmmaker, begins to face financial liabilities. Being stressed, he soon gets involved in a thoughtless act and finds himself in an unpredictable situation.

Title: 937. Kavi Uddheshichathu..?
Content: Kavalam Jimmy and Vattathil Bosco are rivals from their school days and Minnal Simon always tries to benefit from this situation.Three of them have their own intentions and they back stab each other to attain their own aims.

Title: 938. Masters
Content: A young police officer investigating a series of seemingly unrelated murders thinks that there is more than what meets the eye.

Title: 939. Manassinakkare
Content: Old Kochu Thresia's family is irked by her childlike behavior and does not comply with her bizarre demands. She finds an unusual friend in Reji, a down-to-earth young man, who fulfills her demands.

Title: 940. The Little God
Content: An ode to the age of innocence, Oru Kunju Daivam tells the story of a spirited boy and his little world full of miracles.

Title: 941. Roudram
Content: A dedicated police officer investigates the death of a drug baron in spite of pressures from above and corruption within his police force

Title: 942. Koodasha
Content: Kallookaran Joy is a single father who has left his gangster life behind to lead a peaceful life with his daughter. Things take an unexpected turn when his past comes knocking back to him.

Title: 943. Megamalhar
Content: Nandita is happily married to Mukundan. One day, she happens to meet her childhood sweetheart Rajeevan and they become intimate friends. However they decide to part ways as they're already married.

Title: 944. Chakram
Content: A lorry driver (Prithvi Raj) learns that gambling can bring big fortunes, as well as big losses in life.

Title: 946. Uppukandam Brothers Back in Action
Content: The members of the Uppukandam family led by Bobby (Srikanth) are in feud with Srambikkal Sathyanesan (Rajmohan Unnithan) and also with the son of an old rival, Ettuveettil Ganeshan (Richard).

Title: 948. Ordinary
Content: An accident interlinks the life of a driver and conductor of a KSRTC ordinary bus running from Pathanamthitta to Gavi with the lives of people of Gavi.

Title: 949. Chekkan
Content: The story of the survival of a tribal student singer. It discusses the neglect and resistance of our society.

Title: 950. Friday
Content: The messed up life stories of 5 different groups of people on Friday 11 November 2011 within the same town.

Title: 951. Sullu
Content: Sullu a survival thriller Revolves around Jithu the protagonist and his relationship with his parents. Jithu a 9 year old boy is very mischievous and couldn't tolerate his moms pamperings and his father's anger issues. One day while playing hide n seek games with his cousins he accidentally get stuck in wardobe which change the life of him and the people around him.

Title: 952. Love in Singapore
Content: Machu (Mammootty) was cheated by an Anglo-Indian (Nedumudi Venu) by promising him to marry their daughter. They escapes to Singapore and the plot forms when Machu also flies to Singapore to find out them.

Title: 953. Mudhugauv
Content: Movie is narrated through three different tracks. The romance between two students forms the first track, story of a villain forms the second track and third track played by two friends. Confluence of these three tracks completes the plot.

Title: 954. Best Actor
Content: A school teacher's journey to fulfill his long-time dream, to become a movie star.

Title: 955. Avarkkoppam
Content: Three families in the tri-state area (Connecticut, New York, New Jersey) go through trials and tribulations in search of the promised American Dream.

Title: 956. Ulsaha Committee
Content: Apoorvan, a school dropout, aspires to become a renowned scientist and tries various experiments. While his friends Babumon and Chopra help him, the three often land in trouble due to their behavior.

Title: 957. Achaneyanenikkishtam
Content: Bhaskaran, a poor lorry driver, goes through several obstacles to give his son a standard education by sending him to a reputed school.

Title: 958. Tamaar Padaar
Content: Tubelight Mani and Jumper Thambi, two harmless, self-employed circus performers, gets misunderstood as two terrorists by ACP Pouran. He later understands the truth and now wants them released at all costs.

Title: 959. Celluloid
Content: The story of J C Daniel, who made the first ever Malayalam film 'Vigathakumaran' in 1928, resulting in his exile and eventual downfall.

Title: 960. Ishtam
Content: A tale that narrates the healthy relationship between a father and his son.

Title: 961. Kaadu Pookkunna Neram
Content: A police group is deployed by the government to do away with Maoist menace (A banned Left organization) in a tribal village near forest. The police forcibly occupy a tribal primary school for their camp. A policeman follows a person deep into the forest and nabs the person. The person arrested happens to be a woman. He tries to come out of the forest with the arrested person, but he loses his way in the wild.

Title: 962. Mandharam
Content: It is a tale of romance in the life of Rajesh, who journeys through various stages of life filled with warmth and contentment from his relationships with the people around him.

Title: 963. Beautiful
Content: An extra-ordinary friendship between a physically paralyzed millionaire and a small time singer.

Title: 964. Chanakya Thanthram
Content: A fresh-out-of-college criminologist, finds himself pit against an evil mastermind, whom he can only outdo by using his wits and courage.

Title: 965. Paranormal Evil
Content: Karthik makes a documentary on Alzheimer's disease. His subject, Malathi Menon, lives in a small town outside Harippad with her daughter Athira. Karthik and his team arrives at Malathi's place and start noticing her inexplicable behavior.

Title: 966. Achuvinte Amma
Content: The film exhibits how an interception made by a good but male, changed the life of a caring mother, when her only daughter fell in love with him.

Title: 967. Black
Content: Shanmughan, a hitman, decides to lead a peaceful life when he finds his daughter. However, things turn worse when his friends start plotting against him.

Title: 968. Kammath & Kammath
Content: Raja Raja Kammath and Deva Raja Kammath are two brothers who owns a chain of restaurants that specializes in making Dosa. The story begins when they come to Palakkad to open a new restaurant.

Title: 969. Abhiyude Katha Anuvinteyum
Content: They fell in love and swore to always be together, until a strange twist of fate reveals them to be more than just lovers. To what extent will they go to protect their love?

Title: 970. Kaattu
Content: Set in the rustic terrains during the late 70s, movie is a slice-of-life tale with lead characters inspired from the short stories of veteran P. Padmarajan.

Title: 971. Ormayil Oru Shishiram
Content: Nithin, a struggling filmmaker is reminiscing his first and unrequited love, Varsha through the days of his plus two classes. This is their coming-of-age story of romance.

Title: 972. Four Friends
Content: Four cancer patients fly to Malaysia in order to fulfill their last dreams.

Title: 973. Nalpathiyonnu
Content: This socio-political satire unravels through hilarious incidents when two people - strong followers of Communist ideologies-set out on a pilgrimage to Sabarimala.

Title: 974. Dosth
Content: The film revolves around two college friends where one is a new student. The new student falls in love with his friend's sister without knowing she is his friend's sister. The plot forms when he realize the truth.

Title: 975. Hero
Content: A stuntman who falls in love with an actress gains the hatred and jealousy of a superstar.

Title: 976. Manglish
Content: A fish auctioner's life changes after meeting a mysterious Jewish girl and his struggle to communicate with her in English.

Title: 977. Janamaithri
Content: Cops of Paramedu Police Station encounter a series of events while they are on a mission to improve the image of Kerala Police, by making it people friendly. Will they become successful in their mission?

Title: 978. Njanum Pinnoru Njanum
Content: TK, an eminent person, had transformed himself into an enigmatic Sociopath, mainly due to his traumatic childhood and upbringing. A chain of events instigates a retired police official, Padakam, to initiate an independent probe against him that opens up a can of worms.

Title: 980. White
Content: A romantic story of a middle-aged billionaire and a younger woman in London.

Title: 981. Kakkakarumban
Content: Rameshan, who lost his mother at a very young age, is forced to discontinue his studies and bear the atrocities of his step-mother. When Meenakshi enters his life, things take a turn.

Title: 982. Nariman
Content: A police officer (Suresh Gopi) tries a different strategy to help a man facing death sentence.

Title: 983. Kaattu Vithachavar
Content: Movie is a political thriller based on the atrocities committed by the state of Kerala during the 21 months National Emergency, from 1975 to 1977.

Title: 984. Manushya Mrugam
Content: The movie features Baburaj, a lorry driver, with an unmanageable lust. He is nabbed by the police for rape and murder of the two young girls, including his daughter and also for stabbing his own wife to death. The stories are effectively cooked up by the police.

Title: 985. Thandavam
Content: Brothers Kasinathan and Swaminathan strive for the good of their village. But after Swaminathan dies mysteriously, Kasi investigates and eventually take his place as the new patriarch.

Title: 986. Peruchazhi
Content: The film is about how Jagannathan a young politician from India ends up being the chief political adviser to the California state Governor's election campaign and his use of tactics standard of Indian politics to win the election.

Title: 987. Overtake
Content: Based and inspired by a real-life incident, the movie depicts the events that take place after a family is trapped by a stranger.

Title: 988. Margamkali
Content: Unable to forget his first love, Sachi decides never to love anyone in his life. That's when Oormila enters his life. Will he reconsider his decision?

Title: 989. Who
Content: In Mercada, a mysterious valley that is spread across 200 km, strange events occur every year on the Christmas day. A young girl, a dream interpreter, a criminal psychologist and a team of two police officers try to solve the puzzles.

Title: 990. My Santa
Content: The life and challenges of a young girl and a secret Santa who comes into the little one's life on a Christmas eve to fulfill the dreams of the child.

Title: 991. Pretham Undu Sookshikkuka
Content: A haunted mansion amid Kingini Nagar Housing Colony is converted into a police station. Ghosts get provoked by the intrusion of the police. To overcome the horrible night duties, cops take the help of Babu, an outlaw yet sincere guy.

Title: 992. Casanovva
Content: An International businessman and playboy tries to avenge the death of his girlfriend, who was murdered by a gang of robbers, by entrapping them through a reality TV show.

Title: 993. Salt Mango Tree
Content: The struggles of a middle-class couple to admit their 4-year old kid into a reputed school, which involves huge monetary donations, parent interviews, and other activities.

Title: 994. Hotel California
Content: A mix of incidents such as a kidnapping,identity theft,counterfeit DVD exchange ,pimping out a TV actress etc happens at the time of the release of a much awaited movie.

Title: 995. Twenty One Hours
Content: When a woman goes missing, everyone is suspected of her disappearance. Twenty One Hours is an investigative thriller about what happens in the hours after. Is everything as it seems or is there be a darker truth?

Title: 996. Climax
Content: An actress gains popularity thanks to her sensuous roles in South Indian films which leads both a rich benefactor and his teenage son to become smitten with her.

Title: 997. Kaiyethum Doorath
Content: Sachin and Sushma meet at a hill resort. Sachin falls in love immediately but he is hesitated to tell his love to Sushma. Later he founds out that Sushma is engaged and her marriage is fixed with Kishore. But Sushma asks Sachin to act as her fiancee in front of her parents who are going to divorce after her marriage. The story takes a turn, when Advocate Gopinathan comes for the help of Sachin and Sushma.

Title: 998. Ennum Eppozhum
Content: An irresponsible journalist tries different way to interview a fiery lawyer who stood up for a social cause.

Title: 999. Nee Ko Nja Cha
Content: Three friends travel to Goa as one of them broke up with his girlfriend. They meet two girls there, become friends, but soon get into trouble.

Title: ﻿1001. Rani Padmini
Content: The story revolves around two women Rani and Padmini who are on a journey from Kochi to Himachal Pradesh with different purposes.

Title: 1002. Pramani

Title: 1148. Vajram
Content: Vajram is a 2004 Indian Malayalam Flim, directed by Pramod Pappan & produced by Haksar Syed.The flim star Mammootty, Kousalya & Vasundhara Das in lead roles.The music of the film was composed by Ouseppachan & S. P. Venkatesh.

Title: 1150. Thuruthu
Content: A family's journey for a shelter after being shunned by society.

Title: 1151. Mazhathullikkilukkam
Content: Solomon mysteriously shows up after many years and offers to take care of his teachers, Anna and Alice. Unfortunately, a sudden turn of events brings out the real reason behind his arrival.

Title: 1153. Nawal Enna Jewel
Content: The film recounts the lives of a mother and daughter who were the victims of an Arabi kalyanam.

Title: 1154. Viddikalude Maash
Content: Viddikalude Mashu is a family drama film about a boy who faces difficulties in life as a result of his inferiority complex. The film portrays how he overcomes numerous obstacles in his life and eventually achieves his life ambition.

Title: 1155. Doctor Love
Content: Vinayachandran is busy trying every trick of the trade to make both ends meet. He writes and publishes bland love stories that he sells off for a cheap price. One day, he meets a Professor who mistakes him to be an expert in resolving issues of love. Vinayachandran follows him to college, and in no time he is known on campus as Dr. Love.

Title: 1156. Chicken Kokkachi
Content: Kallu, who hails from a middle-class family, living in a village, is forced to abscond from his village given the problems his family and he starts facing following his sister's marriage.

Title: 1157. Palunku
Content: Monichan and Susamma migrate into town area with their children for the better education of their daughters

Title: 1159. Orayiram Kinakkalal
Content: Sreeram, an ex NRI, with few other people, gets involved in an easy money-making plan. In this unusual ride, each one ends up showing different shades of their personality, revealing how far they are willing to go to fulfill their dreams.

Title: 1160. Goa
Content: An aspiring model gets an offer to act in an advertisement. However, her life takes a turn when her father's old friend turns up, asking to repay his debt.

Title: 1161. Thappana
Content: A local petty thief is out from jail. On his journey back, he meets a girl who is also a convict coming out of jail. He decides to help her on his way back.

Title: 1162. Maarjaara Oru Kalluvacha Nuna
Content: Due to an unfortunate event, Shanthanu leaves home and resides in the outskirts of the city named Ashramam Veedu. During the stay period, there is a twist of fate in Shanthanu's life as he encounters a chain of mysterious events.

Title: 1163. Kakkipada
Content: An eight year-old girl is killed by a drug-addict who happens to be an influential personality. Will the girl get justice? Will the police be able to maintain law and order while handling a high profile case?

Title: 1165. Buddy
Content: Though Vishnu is born through artificial insemination and raised in a happy house with two mothers, he is curious about his father. So one fine day, he sets off to find his biological father.

Title: 1166. Sakala Kalasala
Content: Akbar is a brilliant engineering student. He makes everyone proud when he wins the first prize in a tech fest. However, things take a turn when one of his technical innovation backfires and leaves him into serious trouble.

Title: 1167. Aakasmikam
Content: A man in his forties tries to come to terms with his wife's pregnancy while their teenage son tries to deal with puberty besides preparing for a crucial examination.

Title: 1168. Autorickshawkarante Bharya
Content: Sajeevan is a lazy Auto Rickshaw driver who marries the determined Radhika. Circumstances force Radhika to take up driving the Auto Rickshaw for a living.

Title: 1169. Lucky Star
Content: An ambitious couples got in to trouble when a surrogate plan went wrong but luck comes when the baby comes to their life.

Title: 1170. Ivan Megharoopan
Content: Ivan Megharoopan is conceived as the eventful life journey of poet laureate K.P. Madhavan Nair, a character drawn from the life story of the great Malayalam poet P. Kunhiraman Nair.

Title: 1171. Thalappavu
Content: The movie is based on a true story about the confession of a police constable about gunning down a Naxalite (Arikkad Varghese) in a fake encounter as per the order of his superiors in 1970.

Title: 1172. Udalaazham
Content: Gulikan and Maathi were married as children, and live amongst a tribe in a deep jungle settlement. Like everyone else, Gulikan must go to town for work, where the rules are brutal.

Title: 1173. Bamboo Boys
Content: Several members of a forest tribe head out to city to find a doctor when the village elder gets sick , which leads to many funny events as they leave their primitive habitat and experience civilized life for first time.

Title: 1174. Ma Chu Ka
Content: While investigating a story, a journalist crosses path with an advocate. The investigation leads her to a series of complicated situations, unraveling secrets that can pose a threat to her life.

Title: 1175. College Kumaran
Content: Kumaran is running a canteen in a well-reputed college and is in good terms with the students. But, problems arise when he falsely accused of causing an accident which took the lives of many.

Title: 1176. Life
Content: The film is a birds eye view on the family issues. It reiterates the tale of a happy family which consists of Sudhi, Meenakshi and their son Pappoos. When all of a sudden Liya, a loving girl from an ordinary family enters their life, it disrupts the family life. Sudhi is attached to Liya but what repercussions it will have on the family forms the story of the film.

Title: 1177. Kadal Kadannu Oru Maathukutty
Content: Mathukutty, an unemployed man, lives in Germany with his bossy wife. He is given a chance to travel to Kerala to invite famous actors for an event, but all hell breaks loose after his arrival.

Title: 1178. Thakkol Pazhuthu
Content: The robbery attempt at Chacko Mappila's house goes wrong and Chacko gets murdered. S.I Gireesh, who was out jogging comes to the crime scene by chance and starts his investigation.

Title: 1179. Magic Love
Content: Karthik sees Sruthi at a friend's wedding and is instantly smitten. He asks his friend to get them in touch but through a misunderstanding, he's given the wrong phone number. Unknowingly Karthik begins to woo Sravani, who is well aware of the situation. Meanwhile, Sruthi falls in love with Karthik's colleague Madhu. What follows is a comedy of errors combined with a story about true love.

Title: 1180. D Company
Content: Different shades and motives of violence are manifested through completely dissimilar characters.

Title: 1181. Munthiri Monchan
Content: Munthiri Monchan is a feel good urban romantic comedy revolves around Vivek Viswanath, a young marketing guy working in an cinema advertising firm and his accidental meeting with Ima Rajiv, who runs an online lending library startup. Deepika enters their life as the third person on a train trip to Mumbai.

Title: 1182. A Violent Tale
Content: The lives of Hitman, two police officers, two brothers, a drug lord, a girl and a gang of three murderers are intertwined with violence and bloodshed.

Title: 1183. Red Chillies
Content: A group of nine girls are accused of a murder as well as an accident killing 10. They are working in Red Chellies, FM station which is owned by OMR. OMR, who is a Singapore based oil merchant, is forced to come down to Kochi to find the truth.

Title: 1184. Utopiayile Rajavu
Content: Swathanthran is an innocent, honest young man from the village of Kokrangara. This film depicts the current social and political scenarios of Kerala in a humorous way.

Title: 1185. La Tomatina
Content: A journalist who runs a YouTube channel is sketched, kidnapped and tortured by a four-member secret police team. While he is in secret detention, the Prime Minister announces a lock down for three weeks. Assigning only one person to look after the journalist the remaining three members of the police force are transferred to other responsibilities. A friendship develops between the journalist and the policeman. Taking advantage of this situation, the journalist tries to escape.

Title: 1186. Mizhi Randilum
Content: Bhadra, a nurse, has to look after her family. Due to her brother's debts, she sells her house to Krishnakumar but later, she meets Krishnakumar's sister who offers to help her get the house back.

Title: 1187. Class by a Soldier
Content: In "Class by a Soldier," Major Kishore's return to his old school sets the stage for a compelling exploration of the intertwined lives of four school girls.

Title: 1189. Son of Alibaba Nalpathonnaman
Content: Set in Kunnamkulam, a series of thefts takes place and the Police department is confused over the culprit and the mode of execution. Will they catch the real culprit?

Title: 1190. Varnnakazhchakal
Content: Kunju, a young man, suffers from a mental illness. However, his life changes when he comes across Sridevi, who tries her best to help him recover from his illness.

Title: 1191. Pullipulikalum Aattinkuttiyum
Content: The film tackles social issues in Kuttanad through the tale of a hapless youth.

Title: 1192. Pranayakalam
Content: Lovers Renjith and Maria face several trials and tribulations under their strict parents as they struggle to be together.

Title: 1193. Chathurangam
Content: After learning about Jimmy's talents, a minister makes him the secretary of his political party. However, things turn upside down when his own party member tries to plot against him.

Title: 1194. Ooha
Content: Lilly and Albert, a newly married couple, go to their farm house but unusual things begin to happen once they get there.

Title: 1195. Evidey
Content: Evidey unveils the mystery of a man missing through the story of a woman and her family in an intense search.

Title: 1196. Praise the Lord
Content: An immensely rich farmer lives a peacefully with his family in Pala and has no idea about the hectic metro life. He gets introduced to it when he hides a love-stricken couple in his house.

Title: 1197. The Fire
Content: The Fire is a 2003 Malayalam-language Indian feature film directed by Shankar Krishna for Venus Combines starring Shankar and Murali in lead roles, supported by Aishwarya, Mohan Raj, Jagadeesh and Salim Kumar playing other important roles. Watch the full movie The Fire online, only on Eros Now.

Title: 1198. Kaaliyan
Content: Kaaliyan is a Malayalam movie starring Kulappulli Leela, Meghanathan Nair and Tini Tom in prominent roles. It is an action drama directed by Jijo Pangode.

Title: 1199. Honey Bee 2.5
Content: Vishnu aspires to be an actor and his passion and perseverance take him to the sets of Honey Bee 2 (2017).

The movie "28" revolves around an overnight meeting between 5 friends.One of the friends has come to payback his long standing debt. The friend settles his debts and leaves for abroad .Later a Policeman friend comes in and finds out that the entire currency was fake .This triggers rift between all of them. Each one takes stands and argues their point differently. Twists and turns follow (like the game of 28) and towards the end of the movie the mysterious sides of the characters unfold.

Title: 1201. Oru Desa Visesham
Content: A drama revolving around the life of percussion artists in Kerala.

Title: 1202. Finals
Content: The film revolves around the struggles faced by Alice, a cyclist.

Title: 1203. Sringaravelan
Content: Kannan falls in love with Radhu, the daughter of a ruthless city gangster who is responsible for many deaths. In order to marry her, Kannan must face danger and overcome many challenges.

Title: 1204. Kuberan
Content: Sidharthan, a part-time actor who pretends to be a rich man in order to rent a house, faces several challenges when he tries to help Pooja deal with her tragic past.

Title: 1205. Bhayam
Content: A man wins an apartment in a contest and moves in, but soon the ghost of a murdered woman starts appearing in the flat every night.

Title: 1206. Good Bad & Ugly
Content: Three boys come to a big city and find that it changes them in dark ways.

Title: 1207. Sevenes
Content: A team of seven young sevens football players gets involved in crime as a means to quick money.

Title: 1208. Charminar
Content: Fashion designer Sethu gets acquainted to Anand when they start working together on a project. Sethu introduces him to his love interest Nanda and the trio soon become friends, only to eventually change the equation between themselves.

Title: 1209. Confessions of a Cuckoo
Content: Sherin is pursuing a journey through lives of many children's who went through brutal abuses in past. She meets with many stories for her documentary including story of Naseema and Anna which makes U Turn to Sherin's past.

Title: 1210. King Fish
Content: Something seems mysterious when Bhaskara Varma, who enjoys the joys of his bachelor life, gets a call from his long-estranged uncle with the promise of a fortune. The story drives through his arrival at the ancestral home.

Title: 1211. Sayanna Varthakal
Content: Dennis, an independent journalist, interviews whistleblower Ravi Kumar. As the interview progresses, it becomes clear that the situation is significantly more complicated than it appears to be, and it will forever alter their lives.

Title: 1212. Mission C
Content: In Munnar, understudies are seized by transport gangsters who come on visit and snatch understudies on the vehicle and move towards the Munnar forest. Police are endeavoring to get the lawbreakers by getting the understudies preceding entering the boondocks.

Title: 1213. Louis
Content: Shaji Divakar, a Crime Branch officer, is certain that there is a hidden cause behind the suicides happening in his town and he sets out to solve the puzzle.

Title: 1214. Bavuttiyude Namathil
Content: Bavootty is a man of limited dreams and has not attained anything in his life.

Title: 1215. Oronnonnara Pranayakadha
Content: The fun-filled yet audacious love story of two youngsters, Amina and Ramanan. Will they end up together or does fate have other plans for the young couple?

Title: 1216. Shakespeare M.A. Malayalam
Content: Pavithran, a renowned playwright famous for writing real life incidences, writes a play about a real-life girl and somehow, he also becomes one of the characters in the play.

Title: 1217. Shavam
Content: Thomas Ittikkora is dead. Family and friends gather at his home for the pre-funeral ceremonies.

Title: 1218. Oru Second Class Yathra
Content: Two Police Constables with a prisoner in search of an escaped prisoner while conveying from Kannur to Trivandrum.

Title: 1219. The Campus
Content: Rajeev, who is from a broken family, tries to find happiness in his college life. But Vishnu, Rajeev's opponent in college, plots against him.

Title: 1220. Chithrasalabhangalude Veedu
Content: Muththu is one of the naughtiest boys in his school and is always caught red-handed by the teachers. Things become worse when he gets arrested for bringing liquor to school.

Title: 1221. T.D. Dasan Std: VI. B
Content: The story of a mother and a son in a village. Chndrika, the mother, and Dasan is her son who is eleven years old. Chandrika's husband Divakaran had deserted her and her son, when Dasan was merely an year old. Ever since Chandrika had lost contact with her husband, and had over the years learned to fend for herself and her son. Dasan on the other hand, is never able to stop dreaming about his father.
