So, when he accidentally comes across Divakaran's address in Chandrika's cloth box, Dasan writes a letter to his father, without letting his mother know about it. Does the letter reach Divakaran?

Title: 1222. Crime Story
Content: Hari and Meera are close friends who work in an IT company. Their life takes a turn when one of their close friends gets murdered.

Title: 1223. Face 2 Face
Content: A suspended cop finds himself entangled in the murder of a youth and is drawn towards the case

Title: 1224. Alice in Panchalinadu
Content: The movie revolves around the life of Alice, a resident of Delhi, after she visits her ancestral home in Pachalinadu, an infamous village in Idukki known as the hub for robberies.

Title: 1226. Daivathinte Swantham Cleetus
Content: A skit on Jesus Christ brings out a change in good-hearted rowdy Cleetus along with revealing few surprises of his nature and his relationship with a neighborhood tailor.

Title: 1227. Ayal Jeevichiruppundu
Content: Murugan is a poor illiterate fisherman residing in a small coastal village whose biggest dream is to visit Goa. John Mathew Mathan, a renowned writer catches his attention and together they go on a journey through Goa.

Title: 1228. Clint
Content: The movie is based on the real-life story of Edmund Thomas Clint, the child prodigy who left the world at age 7, leaving behind about 25,000 drawings and paintings.

Title: 1229. Sathya
Content: The protagonist from Kerala who goes to Pondicherry and becomes very successful in life by gambling. However, he also makes enemies because of this. The story further progresses through the various incidents that happen due to gambling.

Title: 1230. Madhuranombarakattu
Content: Vishnu, a teacher gets transferred to a distant village. Vishnu's son passes away in an accident. Vishnu decides to hide this news from his wife, who is in prison, till she's released.

Title: 1231. Karumadikkuttan
Content: Kuttan, a thirty-year-old innocent man, has the mind of a ten-year-old, which enables him to enjoy the positives of life. He develops feelings for Nandini, but she makes fun of him.

Title: 1233. Money Ratnam
Content: Neil comes across an unexpected incident, while returning after the New Year party. He tries to escape from the scene by getting into a bus where he gets a bag containing money left by someone else.

Title: 1235. Pakida
Content: Aadi meets a mysterious and concealing traveler George Koshy Anthrapper and travels with him from Kochi to Madurai. On their way, they come across Sunny and Kani who change their lives.

Title: 1236. Naan Petta Makan
Content: Young leader Abhimanyu from Maharaja's College in Kochi was one among millions, and the testimonials of his friends and well-wishers about him spoke volumes about his inner worth and the visionary that he was.

Title: 1237. Neeyum Njanum
Content: A newly married couple moves into a small town hoping to start a new life. But odds are against them and their life takes a roller coaster ride.

Title: 1238. Bhoomiyile Manohara Swakaryam
Content: Ahammed and Anna are friends from childhood and their parents are also good friends. Both of them who loved each other belonged to extremely religious families. One day, all of a sudden Ahammed decides to leave his native place without revealing many details and he asked Anna to forget him and move on. What happens post this incident is the main content of Bhoomiyile Manohara Swakaryam.

Title: 1240. Ottam
Content: Set in Trivandrum, the story of Ottam unfolds in a day, and progresses through the lives of two youngsters - Abhi and Vinay. What does destiny have in store for these young men?

Title: 1241. Alibhai
Content: An notorious business man comes to eliminate alibhai and his people from palayam market science he has childhood enemies.

Title: 1242. Bobby
Content: A 21-year old boy, who gives up his Seminary Studies and falls in love with a lady who is 7 years elder to him. The movie showcases the funny events, romance and the love life of the couple.

Title: 1243. Villali Veeran
Content: Siddharthan is a noble-hearted merchant who is burdened with lot of responsibilities in his life. His pursuit for money lands him in trouble and the film traces as to how he deals with his adversaries.

Title: 1244. The Voiding Soul
Content: The rhythm of life, even for a master drummer, can be disrupted as well as harmonised by love, passion, jealousy, hate and spite. Unni, a masterful chenda (a drum) player, is drawn to dancer Nalini by an intense force that transcends their devotion to the arts. However, their passion cannot hold up against the tumults in Unni's life, all of which hasten a mental imbalance, rooted in Unni's childhood, to an inevitable dark end.

Title: 1245. Satyam, Shivam, Sundaram
Content: Vijayalakshmi, a pauper, struggles for a living with her two brothers, who are visually impaired. However, her life changes when she finds out that she is actually a princess.

Title: 1246. Headmaster
Content: Headmaster, is an inspired adaptation from POTHICHORU, a short story which portrayed the miserable lives of school teachers in Kerala, during the mid twentieth century. Joseph Mundassery the education minister, read POTHICHORU in the Kerala Legislative Assembly, to reveal the pitiable condition of teachers. Pothichoru pave the way for the revolutionary Education Bill, which was introduced to the assembly in 1958.Though the Bill Failed to get the approval, it inspired a number laws and amendments that substantially improved the salary and ultimately the living standards of school teachers.

Title: 1247. Kalachakram
Content: To destroy the country, a businessman with the help of a doctor creates a clone of Adolf Hitler. However, a group of youngsters are determined to expose him to the public.

Title: 1248. Chattakkari
Content: Julie, an Anglo-Indian girl, falls in love with her best friend's brother Sasi, a Hindu boy. She has a passionate encounter with him, the consequences of which she must face alone.

Title: 1249. Kili Poyi
Content: Chacko and Hari, tired of their advertising jobs, take a trip to Goa. They return with a mysterious bag which change the life of both .

Title: 1251. Natholi Oru Cheriya Meenalla
Content: Preman faces strange and unexpected events in his flat and decides to write a story about his flatmates. His life changes when the characters in his book develop personalities of their own.

Title: 1252. Kalippu
Content: The story of five youngsters hailing from a slum, who band together to tackle the problems by the villagers.

Title: 1253. Ben Johnson
Content: Son of a notorious criminal becomes a police officer to erase the bad image of his father but things are not easy as he seems.

Title: 1255. Mere Pyare Deshvasiyom
Content: A group of spirited elderly citizens who rediscover their passion for life, hailing from a village where the literacy rate is pretty low, this motley group of elders will fight against the odds to achieve their graduation dreams.

Title: 1256. Kshanam
Content: Four film school students as part of their project goes for location hunting.There they meet a person with a weird personality, an academic in parapsychology. The students gets into the world of Ouija board and an entity through this man.

Title: 1257. Enpathukalile Ebhyamar
Content: ENPATHUKALILE EBHYANMAR is a film set in the eighties. Shajahan, the protagonist leaves his native place due to a problem caused by his father. Later his life takes on a whole new dimension in a way that he never thought possible.

Title: 1258. Bombay March 12
Content: Mammootty in Bombay March 12 Bombay March 12, which is Babu Janardhanan's debut directorial venture, has Mammootty in the lead and goes back in time, to the early 1990's. The film zooms in on the Mumbai riots of 1993 and strives to talk about the sufferings of the common people during those turbulent times.

Title: 1259. KL 10 Patthu
Content: The story of 'KL 10 Pathu' basically revolves around too many incidents like a Panchayath Election, a local football tournament final, and an eloping of the hero and heroine. What makes things all the more complicated is the repercussion of the eloping which eventually affects the results of the football tournament and the election result. Because the hero is the son of the candidate in the panchayath election and a player of the football team which plays in the final.

Title: 1260. Nee-Na
Content: A married couple finds tension in their relation and life due to the intervention of an alcoholic and impulsive young woman.

Title: 1261. Thelivu
Content: Gouri, an orphan who marries truck driver Khalid and seems to have meaning in her life. However, she is forced to kill the owner of the orphanage she works in after realising that he was trying to rape one of the inmates. The story takes off from there with Gouri and Khalid lives changing overnight.

Title: 1262. Seconds
Content: Four strangers gets involved in a murder which took place inside an elevator.

Title: 1263. Ammakilikkoodu
Content: Saranalayam is an old-age home run by Eradi. He appoints Vivek as the new manager to help him evict the inmates as he wants to sell it.

Title: 1264. Puzhikkadakan
Content: After his return from army protagonist decides to bring desirable changes in his society through his protest against the greedy government employees

Title: 1266. Darling Darling
Content: Kochu Kurup and Aniyankutty fall in love with the same girl. When Aniyankutty comes to know that she loves his friend, he plans to sabotage their relationship, resulting in hilarious events.

Title: 1267. Apoorvaragam
Content: Apoorvaragam is the story of three youngsters Roopesh (Nishan), Nancy (Nithya) and Tommy (Asif Ali). Roopesh has always been in love with Nancy, but has never had the nerve to express it. For Nancy, love is something that is beyond words. Tommy is the perfect Cupid, who would make things happen for these two. After a lot of unexpected happenings and dramatic twists, it is proven that only true love can endure.

Title: 1268. Kanyaka Talkies
Content: While weaving a gripping story around the transformation of an old movie theater into a church, Kanyaka Talkies (Virgin Talkies) delves deep into the matrix of body, desire, pleasure and guilt.

Title: 1269. Sahasram
Content: During the shoot of a film, the hero gets killed under mysterious circumstances. However, IPS Officer Sahasranamam, who is assigned to investigate the case, comes across some startling facts.

Title: 1270. Ottamuri Velicham
Content: Set against the backdrop of a beautiful hilltop village surrounded by dense forest and a decaying tea plantation is the story of Sudha, an under privileged woman who reaches this village after her marriage with Chandran. They stay along with Chandran's brother and aging mother in a confined single room house with a make shift separation to create space for the couple. The room has a strange light without a switch which changes its colors often. While Chandran calls the light his invention of a lifetime, it deprives Sudha of her privacy and begins to haunt her. Adding to her woes, Chandran engages in acts to physically exert his dominance over Sudha. Amidst deep trauma, Sudha realizes that she doesn't have any support and decides to fight for her survival and seeks revenge against Chandran. Will Sudha succeed in her fight for freedom forms the crux of this emotional thriller.

Title: 1271. Koppayile Kodumkattu
Content: A taxi driver from Alleppey who always tries to keep his wife happy by taking her to very materialistic trips. She becomes more greedy and in order to keep her happy, he knowingly or unknowingly undertakes few tasks that gets him trapped.

Title: 1272. Kaipola
Content: The tale of Eby and Jeny, and how they handled life's highs and lows, as well as the events that motivated them to form the Wheelchair Cricket Team.

Title: 1273. Vasanthi
Content: It is a journey that traverses through stage plays, storytelling and a host of male domains in Vasanthi's life.

Title: 1274. French Viplavam
Content: On 1st April 1996, the Kerala government had taken an initiative to prohibit arrack shops, which had led many alcoholics in awful situations. What follows, is how they prevailed over this change.

Title: 1275. Aabhaasam
Content: The story of Aabhaasam is about an overnight bus journey from Bangalore to Kerala where the travelers analyze the schizophrenic society and how it has evolved through different times.

Title: 1277. Aana Alaralodalaral
Content: Accused of stealing an elephant's "elassu", Hashim and family are and forced to leave the village. Hashim returns to the village to settle the score.

Title: 1278. Vellaripravinte Changathi
Content: A man tries to release a stalled movie made by his father 35 years ago, and find the actors worked in it.

Title: 1279. Three Kings
Content: Three unemployed men discover the map to an unearthed treasure... And thus begins a funny description of how they reach their destiny

Title: 1280. 2 Penkuttikal
Content: 2 Penkuttikal or 2 girls discuss about the problems faced by women in our society in a bizarre way through the viewpoint of two small girls. This movie portraits the issues of the women all over the world through the thoughts of two 6th grade students named Achu and Anagha. They have already passed through a lot of restrictions that are only meant for girls.

Title: 1281. Khedda
Content: Khedda probes into the delicate aspects of a changing chemistry between a mother and a daughter.

Title: 1282. Antharam
Content: The inner conflicts, warmth, trauma and joyous moments in the lives of a transwoman, a teenage girl and a man living under the same roof.

Title: 1283. Vakkalathu Narayanankutty
Content: Narayanankutty aspires to become a lawyer, but ends up being a clerk in a government office. Although Narayanankutty does not become a lawyer, he fights when the law is broken.

Title: 1285. The Don
Content: Kasim is a mafia boss and Unnikrishnan becomes his most trusted man. Later, when Kasim is found murdered, Unnikrishnan is charged with the crime and must prove his innocence.

Title: 1286. Thakkol
Content: Fr. Monsignor exerts an iron grip of authority and control over Ambrose, making his life miserable. Ambrose is appointed as the priest of another church. When Ambrose happens to get a mysterious key, the story takes a new turn.

Title: 1287. War & Love
Content: Captain Gopinath, along with Serina, the daughter of a Pakistani army general, must derail Pakistan's plans of using a nuclear bomb against India in the wake of their lost war.

Title: 1288. Vesham
Content: When businessman Appu's younger brother Hari is accused in a murder case, the former takes the blame to protect his sibling and also avenges the wrongdoing of his trade rival, Sivan.

Title: 1289. Diana
Content: Diana is a 2001 Indian Malayalam film, directed by Nagesh Narayan. The film stars Hema and Kamal Roy in lead roles.

Title: 1290. Mahasamudram
Content: Isahak, a fisherman and football player, falls in love with Devi. But their married life is shattered when Devi gets arrested for murder on their wedding night.

Title: 1291. Radio Madhav
Content: Mathai's kindness and simplicity endeared him to everyone around him. When an unfortunate turn of events land Mathai in trouble, the people whose life he touched with his kindness rally around to help him.

Title: 1292. My Daughter
Content: A story about a careless mother and her lonely, insecure daughter. Eighteen year old Faye is always on the edge because of her mother's boyfriends. Her mother survives by running a beauty shop. Since there are only the two of them, they are very close and are at times like friends or sisters, but to Faye, her carefree mother is also like a child she needs to watch after. She is also plagued by rumors about her and her mother. Her anger reaches its limit when she learns that her mother is pregnant. Sadly, she can't do anything but endure reality and hope to escape her dull and depressing life.

Title: 1294. Sound Thoma
Content: Thomas is a smart and eligible bachelor. But anyone who hears him speak will dislike him. Because of his disability in speech, he suffers much from his villagers and even near and dear ones.

Title: 1296. Best College Days (2010)
Content: The lives of a group of young medical students take a sudden turn when one of them kills Rohit, a classmate, and the entire event gets recorded on camera.

Title: 1297. Asha Black
Content: The movie is all about romantic relationship between two youngsters.

Title: 1298. Mazhayathu
Content: A bizarre incident shakes the family of 3 and the father finds himself becomes the victim of people's anger.

Title: 1299. Megasandesam
Content: A young singer fall in love with a ghost that is visible only to his eyes. The movie shows the aftereffects of this love.

Title: 1300. Kunjananthante Kada
Content: The movie focuses on the marital relationship of a grocery store owner.

Title: 1301. Housefull
Content: Housefull is a family entertainer, showing the life of a Police Constable Ananthan, who continues to be a bachelor after 36. All marriage proposals are utter failures, many times due to minor reasons. At a crucial situation Ananthan marries Emily who works in a textile shop. Both families were against the marriage. Ananthan and Emily hopes that the birth of a baby may change the situation. But they were not blessed with a baby for a long time. At last when god blessed them, it was not one but 4 kids at a time. What happens after this weaves the humorous plot of the movie.

Title: 1302. Nalla Vishesham
Content: 'Water is the Basis of Life' - based on this fact, Nalla Vishesham revolves around the lives of people on the banks of river Njavaroorkadavu. With the help of Ajayan, businessman Divakara Panicker is building up wealth by exploiting the natural resources of the village area and are polluting the river by irresponsible farming using harmful chemicals and pesticides. The villagers decide to fight against these people and start protesting against any misuse in the name of development especially when it was risking the river water and immediate environment. Meanwhile, a college group visits the village to study on the environmental aspects. Things take a turn when a mishap happens and the story goes through an emotional turmoil. The question is whether Panicker and Ajayan realize the bad effects of their deeds and change. And whether the villagers will win in protecting their natural environment which is core to their living.

Title: 1303. Oru Pakka Nadan Premam
Content: The entire village of Manimala wishes Kannan and Tulasi to get married but due to unseen circumstances, they part ways. What happens when faith conspires to bring them together again.

Title: 1304. Swa Le
Content: From 1984 to 2009 it revolves around a news reporter,how he survived all these years

Title: 1305. Gramavrikshathile Kuyil
Content: Kumaran, an avid student, is influenced by the reformer Narayana Guru. Grown up, he is an established poet. He marries his former student Bhanumathi despite certain objections. He rises as a great poet before his accidental death.

Title: 1306. Achante Kochumolu
Content: A priest's granddaughter falls in love with a rich man, Prince. But problems arise when his father is against this relationship.

Title: 1307. Nadiya Kollappetta Rathri
Content: Railway Anti-Criminal Task Force (RATs) investigates three unrelated murders happened in a train.

Title: 1308. Sandwich
Content: Engineer Sai accidentally kills the brother of a criminal. However, things take an interesting turn after the criminal's rival, offers protection to Sai on the condition that he marries his daughter.

Title: 1309. Ente Veedu Appuvinteyum
Content: Vasu is brought up with love and care by his stepmother.However, when his stepmother gives birth to a boy, he feels insecure as the baby gets more attention than him.

Title: 1310. Papilio Buddha
Content: A band of displaced untouchables in Western Ghats of India embrace Buddhism in order to escape from caste oppression.

Title: 1312. Akam
Content: sreenivasan is an engineer. he meets with an accident and his friend leaves him. he married new women and suspects her for her loving him even after his disfigurement.

Title: 1313. Pakal Nakshatrangal
Content: It is about the lives of a group of intellectuals in Kerala in the latter half of the 1990s.

Title: 1314. Colors
Content: Dr Rajalakshmi lives happily with her two daughters, Pinki and Pooja. However, when she detects fraudulent activities regarding the sales of medicines, she earns some enemies who want to destroy her.

Title: 1315. Sleeplessly Yours
Content: Jessy wakes up one morning with a splitting headache and a vague memory of the bygone week to realize that his partner, Maanu, is missing. A frantic search follows. Jessy and Maanu, an eccentric couple, had decided to experiment on sleep deprivation in an attempt to liven up their relationship. What began as a joke turned serious in a couple of days. Their initial phases of creativity, fun, and frolic slowly gave way to lack of judgment, agitation, and temperamental issues. At the end of 4 days of turmoil, they crack and have an altercation about the state of their relationship. Things turn violent and soon Jessy passes out. The movie, structured in a non-linear narrative, is an attempt by Jessy to recollect what went down in the last four days. We go back and forth between his present search for her and the bursts of memories that he has about her. With the help of his friend Venu, he attempts to discover her past that she'd refused to ever reveal.

Title: 1316. You Too Brutus
Content: Arun, Tovino and Vicky are bachelors who lead a carefree life. However, their lives are turned upside down when they fall in love with three young women.

Title: 1317. The Image Threads
Content: A computer teacher, his black-magician grandfather and a female cyber-creature -- a series of pre-destined rendezvous, both on line and offline, over the shreds of mnemonic time and space, at the cleavages of various parlors of subculture -- finally the narrative images of the computer screen are drained off from the color and the texture, the images collapse down to a mere pulsating pixel, potentially to start another cycle of the story once again.

Title: 1318. Ilayaraja
Content: Vanajan is a middle-aged who lives in a modest house with his ailing father, wife and children. When a moneylender he is indebted makes Vanajan a strange offer one day, his life takes an unexpected turn.

Title: 1319. Uddharani (Allusion)
Content: A Man, a Gatekeeper who guards the mighty garden, Shangri-La which is said to be a healing place for the one with sorrows. His existence is suddenly questioned when he encounters an old man with so many mysteries.

Title: 1320. Mark Antony
Content: Warring rivals Pappu and Chackappan unite when the former's nephew Antony and the latter's daughter Nimmy fall in love. After a sniper shoots Pappu, Antony embarks on a mission to find the killer.

Title: 1321. Orkut Oru Ormakoot
Content: Orkut Oru Ormakoot is the story about the friendship between four boys who live together in a posh apartment. They have absolutely no values and morals and believe in having nothing but fun but their lives take a U turn when they befriend Crystal (Rima Kallingal), a Malayali girl living in Germany, through Orkut. Crystal coming to India to meet the four friends forms the rest of the story.

Title: 1322. Alli
Content: Story of an innocent village girl ( Alli ) and her father, portrayed in a beautiful forest backdrop. Their peaceful life goes on a toss and when she takes refuge in the forest and mother nature had her own plans to rescue her.

Title: 1323. Ulakam Chuttum Valiban
Content: As Jayashankar has huge debts, he seeks training under his uncle and becomes a smart thief. However, situations get tricky and hilarity ensues when he lands up becoming a sub-inspector.

Title: 1324. Kachi
Content: Daughter of separated parents comes to her fathers home and some incidents happen there.

Title: 1325. Rebecca Uthup Kizhakemala
Content: Movie narrates the story of an athlete Rebecca whom her village Kizhakkemala is proud of. In an interesting way the movie plots family relationships through the life of Rebecca.

Title: 1326. Maanasaandarapetta Yezdi
Content: Mechanic brothers Pappi and Chethanappi runs competing shops and frequently quarrel with each other. Their favorite Yezdi bike, used in the bike race to settle their fights comes in the possession of Philipose.

Title: 1327. Karma Yodha
Content: A mumbai based investigating officer set out to find a group of kidnapped teenege girls in a sex racketing and one among is his own daughter

Title: 1329. Musical Chair
Content: Martin, a writer has a severe fear of death. The fact that he has several borderline health issues and unhealthy indiscretions magnifies the enormity of the situation. An evening with several acquaintances and booze, throws new light in his expedition widening his horizon of thoughts. The tragedies in his life hold a light to his present dilemma. In a run for solace and peace of mind, he decides to find out the reason behind death which leads him to an eventful voyage. Thereafter he sets a journey of what he assumes to give him answers.

Title: 1330. Happy Husbands
Content: A bar singer impacts the lives of three people, and through a series of mishaps, they all come together during a vacation in Malaysia.

Title: 1332. Sadrishavakyam 24:29
Content: The deceit of her father's personal manager had left a young Anna Wilfred orphaned and penniless years ago. Now, the time has come for her to avenge the untimely demise of her family, and win back all the fortune that is rightfully hers.

Title: 1333. Parunthu
Content: Purushothaman is a heartless financier who behaves in a rude and insulting way towards the people who owe him money. But his life changes when he faces many unexpected turn of events.

Title: 1334. 101 Chodhyangal?
Content: Story of a 12 year old boy given a task of framing 101 questions by his teacher, without worrying about the answers. The story moves around his life and the questions that are intertwined together. He successfully completes the task but wants the answer for only the 101st question.

Title: 1335. Aamayum Muyalum
Content: The people living in a poverty-stricken village become suspicious of one another after a man is found dead in the village.
Set in the small town of Kanhangad in Northern Kerala, 0-41* is a story of real people with dramatized re-enactments of actual events in their lives intertwined with director's observations of life.

Title: 1337. Lavender
Content: A tragic love triangle involving a young painter, an Interpol detective, and a professional hit-man.

Title: 1338. Manjupoloru Penkutti
Content: Nidhi a 16 year old teenager secretly tries to kill her abusive stepfather with the help of her friends.

Title: 1339. Mr. Brahmachari
Content: Ananthan Thampy (Mohanlal) is a middle aged who has decided never to marry because he thinks he will loose all his youthfulness and pleasing looks though marriage.

Title: 1340. Bhagavan
Content: When a group of terrorists kidnap the home minister of Kerala and three newborn babies from his hospital, Dr Balagopal takes it upon himself to rescue them.

Title: 1341. Everything Is Cinema
Content: Chris, a young, independent filmmaker moves to Kolkata with his wife Anita, who is also a movie actress, to work on his documentary.

Title: 1343. Thallumpidi
Content: Three college-going friends land into trouble when a simple issue that could have been reconciled in a peaceful manner ends up in a fight.

Title: 1344. A'hr
Content: In Sanskrit, Maya means magic or illusion upon which the universe is woven. Protagonist, Maya refers to the wider mystery of the universe and its masterful manipulation with the human minds. The mystic story unravels in a Himalayan climb.

Title: 1345. The Reporter
Content: When 6 people from different society are kidnapped, back to back, the police is mystified.

Title: 1346. Tournament - Play & Replay
Content: Tournament is a road movie in which the story progresses as the main characters embark on a journey. Viswam, Usman, Balu, Bobby, Chilambu and Subu start from Kochi for a Cricket match selection. Lekshmi, their friend, also joins them. Since they miss the flight from Cochin, they decide to travel by road.

Title: 1347. Soothrakkaran
Content: The lives of three friends and their families are compromised as they become victim to a series of murders.

Title: 1348. Moz & Cat
Content: Two orphans share a strong bond and hatch mischievous plans to earn their livelihood. However, their life takes an unexpected turn when they meet Nandana.

Title: 1349. Doubles
Content: Giri and Gowri are twins who set up an accident rescue unit. Their lives change when they rescue a mysterious girl named Saira.

Title: 1350. Ladies and Gentleman
Content: Chandrabose becomes an alcoholic after his wife's death. His life, however, takes an interesting turn after he dissuades a young IT professional from committing suicide.

Title: 1351. Avarude Raavukal
Content: Aashiq, Siddharth, Vijay, and Vinod stay together in the house of an old man named Skobo Johnson. The unexpected events in their life form the plot of the movie.

Title: 1352. Heylassa
Content: Unnikrishnan, who is raised by Madhavan, is forced to go to the city after he beats up some thugs. There he begins working for a wheelchair bound man who is seeking his lost love.

Title: 1355. Ole Kanda Naal
Content: A campus full of stupid students. The film is about the story of a Muslim girl coming from an Orthodox family and then an eventful event.

Title: 1356. Rock N' Roll
Content: Story of a world renowned bassist Chandramauli trying to impress a singer named Daya by composing music.

Title: 1357. David and Goliath
Content: David, an orphan, shows prodigious talent with respect to machines. Sunny, an unsuccessful businessman, finds out about his talent and takes advantage of him to make a fortune.

Title: 1358. Kalikkoottukar
Content: The lives of childhood friends, who fly to Goa for a fun trip during their college break. However, events take a dangerous turn when they come in contact with a couple at a local bar.

Title: 1359. Kuttymama
Content: After retiring from military service kuttymama has became a nuisance to the all the people of his village by his gimmick and blunder6

Title: 1360. Black Stallion
Content: Bar dancer Laura Singh stabs Black, a goon, and escapes with her sister to Kochi when he tries to force her into marriage. She meets Ameer there, but is she safe?

Title: 1361. Aanachandam
Content: After an elephant saves him from an accident in childhood, Krishna becomes fond of elephants. His life changes when he decides to adopt Arjunan, a severely injured elephant.

Title: 1362. Velikku Veluppankalam
Content: A story of an introvert guy who comes from a Brahmin family in Kerala and how he finds courage to tell his parents he is gay a day before his wedding.

Title: 1363. Sathyam
Content: Sanjiv Kumar's selection to police force is delayed by then Police Commissioner under grudge against Sanjiv's father. All options out, Sanjiv locks up the Commissioner to get his job. Trouble begins when Commissioner breaks out.

Title: 1364. Nakshathrakkannulla Rajakumaran Avanundoru Rajakumari
Content: Two lovers seperated by fueding families.

Title: 1365. Martin
Content: Chambakkara is a village situated in center Kerala, Martin who is 12 years old kills a police officer who killed Martins father. This is a story of a person who stands against corruption and crimes and stands for the goodness and wellbeing.

Title: 1368. Arayannangalude Veedu
Content: Teenage boy Ravindranath leaves his house after a quarrel. Eighteen years later, circumstances make him return home, but he finds that matters are not like what he had expected.

Title: 1369. Uthara
Content: On her mother's insistence, God woman Uthara borrows money from the village landlord. But she is accused of stealing the money and arrested.

Title: 1370. The Last Two Days
Content: Two months have passed since three youngsters belonging to a political outfit have gone missing. C.I Srikanth aided by C.P Aby Mathew are given a final two days to solve the mystery.

Title: 1372. Sesham
Content: Meera, a film school student, makes a film on Lonappan, an inmate of a mental asylum. Feeling sorry for him, she manages to get him out and give him a normal life.

Title: 1373. Chandragiri
Content: The film centers on Chandragiri, a village locality in Kasaragod, Kerala. It focuses on how a school was forced to give up their identity to anti-social thoughts and how a teacher fights against this.

Title: 1374. Vishudhan
Content: A priest and nun face the consequences of their action against a corrupt business man.

Title: 1375. Joshua
Content: Portraying the impact of the medium of cinema on the minds of children.

Title: 1376. Beware of Dogs
Content: Four friends rent a house and always manage to get in trouble with their landlord. One day, the group is forced to leave this rented house and flee to Pondicherry where a new journey awaits them.

Title: 1377. Mariyam
Content: A village girl who reaches out to her dream surviving a rape.

Title: 1378. Polytechnic
Content: A Communist party member tries to start a new factory after the death of his father in the army

Title: 1379. Chewing Gum
Content: An encounter with a city girl broadens a country guy's horizons.

Title: 1380. For Sale
Content: The story of two sisters Diana and Liza who work in the advertising industry shedding light on how women come to be viewed as commodities in society.

Title: 1381. Jo and the Boy
Content: An aspiring animation creator's dreams start coming true when she is met with a charismatic young boy.

Title: 1382. Careful
Content: A journalist, investigating traffic violations in a city, comes across mysterious happenings and lands herself in a dangerous situation.

Title: 1383. Love 24x7
Content: A love story set in the backdrop of media.

Title: 1384. Gramaphone
Content: Jennifer is the only hope of her family to reach Israel. But for her family she should sacrifice her own love and friendship.

Title: 1386. Olappeeppi
Content: Malayali family's ordinary life in Kerala from 1970s-2000s told through young Unni and grandmother's perspectives, recalling past eras.

Title: 1387. Mariyam Mukku
Content: Felix lost his parents at a young age. Salomi, daughter of a white man from Portugese arrives with her father at Mariyam Mukku falls in love with Felix.

Title: 1388. Nayakan Prithvi
Content: Ratheesh, who arrives at a rural village named Kuyilimala to work on a hill highway project. But, the villagers refuse the idea of the project, protesting against its construction. From then onwards,unexpected events occur.

Title: 1389. Cinema Company
Content: Cinema Company is a 2012 Malayalam romantic comedy drama film written and directed by Mamas, and starring mainly newcomers. Basil, Sanjeev, Shruthi Hariharan and Badri play the roles of four close friends who dream of making a film.

Title: 1390. Hello Dubaikkaran
Content: Follows the roller-coaster ride of Prakashan (Adil Ibrahim), a rustic lad who tries to secure a dream job in Dubai.

Title: 1391. Cold
Content: A promising artist learns about her brutal past, suffers a stroke and is trapped in her body with her worst nightmares coming true.

Title: 1392. Oru Naal Varum
Content: Nandhakumar, an honest police officer, lays a trap to capture Gopi Krishnan, a corrupt town planner. Though his attempts fail, Nandhakumar is not ready to give up.

Title: 1393. Eelam
Content: Shivan revolves around a couple who are very much in love but one day the woman is found dead and the man is found guilty and imprisoned. But once he is in jail he recollects certain memories that change everything.

Title: 1394. Lal Bahadur & Shastri
Content: Lal (Jayasurya) is a young man who is in search for a job, Bahadhur (Nedumudi Venu) who have an obsession towards liquor and women, and Shasthri(Aju Varghese) is a young farmer who struggles to get some document approved from a Government sector. The three men, who are total strangers travels to Ernakulam in a KSRTC bus. Bahadhur buys a lottery ticket from a boy and the boy gives another ticket to Lal as he doesn't have change. The trio part ways after reaching Ernakulam; but later come to know that the lottery ticket which Lal got has won one crore rupees. Then Lal, Bahadhur and Shasthri join hands and goes in search of the missing ticket. This forms the crux of the story.

Title: 1396. Rasam
Content: Menon decides to have a grand traditional Kerala sadya for his daughter's marriage. During the days of marriage arrangements, some unexpected events happened and the rest is plotted in the movie.

Title: 1397. Mazha
Content: Bhadra is married off to an engineer by her parents after they find out that she is infatuated with her music teacher. Her life goes through a tough phase when her husband becomes aware of her past.

Title: 1398. Sadanandante Samayam
Content: Story of a man (Dileep) who depends on astrology for everything in his life.

Title: 1399. Dance Dance
Content: Michael goes on to become a great dancer, winning a reality show title. Owing to this, he becomes very famous in his college as well. However, one day he mysteriously goes missing from college, leading to a string of unexpected incidents.

Title: 1400. The False Eye
Content: Two boys steal a Camera kept for surveillance in a store aspiring to make a cinema. But their plans go astray and their attempts to abandon the Camera fails. They end up on wrong side of their actions leading to an irrecoverable loss.

Title: 1402. Bhargavacharitham Moonnam Khandam
Content: Bhargavan is a dangerous criminal who gets anxiety attacks that prevent him from attacking anyone. However, when he meets a psychiatrist, Shantharam, his life gets transformed while he treats him.

Title: 1403. Chapters
Content: Different people who are in serious crisis see a ray of hope when their lives get interlinked in an unexpected turn of events

Title: 1404. Calcutta News
Content: Krishna priya (Meera Jasmine) get married to Harikumar (Indrajith sukumaran) and move to Culcutta with him.From there she understand that she was cheaten by his husband

Title: 1405. Police Maman
Content: DSP Shankunni, a laid-back police officer, gets married to the daughter of a minister. However, his life turns around when he is assigned a tricky homicide case.

Title: 1406. Jungle.com
Content: Jungle com is a Malayalam movie starring Sreejith Ravi and Gaurav Menon in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Arun Nischal with Rajesh Raghavan as the producer, forming part of the crew.

Title: 1407. Ezhu Sundara Rathrikal
Content: Ezhu Sundara Rathrikal is the story of Eby , an ad-film maker. He decided to tie the knot, Suddenly some problem occur on Eby before seven days of his marriage. So he has to solve the problem before his marriage.

Title: 1408. Vellithira
Content: Raj and his friends go to a remote village and start a touring talkie that shows scenes from Rajinikanth's movies. He falls in love with a local girl, but his past surfaces and changes their lives.

Title: 1409. Rajamma @ Yahoo
Content: 2 brothers, Michael Rajamma aka Rajamma and Vishnu Yohannan aka Yahoo are born to an inter caste couple. After sudden demise of their parents they live in a bungalow and later the duo plans to rent out their bungalow to different families.

Title: 1410. Poyi Maranju Parayathe
Content: The film tells the story of a household where several murders have happened. The plot picks up from a point many years after the killings, and what happens next.

Title: 1411. Thilothama
Content: Rosy is a woman of enchanting beauty who sings and dances in a 5 star hotel in the town. She happens to be an eyewitness to a murder that happens in the hotel.

Title: 1413. Angel John
Content: Maradonna is an aimless youngster who likes to waste his time doing practically nothing .His life is turned upside down when an angel decides to teach him a lesson.

Title: 1414. Angane Njanum Premichu
Content: A group of college students befriend a tomboyish girl out of the blue from the street, and over time, she becomes an integral part of their gang. Upon discovering more about her, their attitudes change with time.

Title: 1415. White Nights
Content: Velutha Rathrikal (White Nights) is an independent cinematic adaptation of the eponymous novel by Fyodor Dostoyevsky. Manu is an artist in search of a new sky, from his troubled past, in a forest settlement. He meets Chelly, a tribal girl from a nearby settlement who bears the burnt from her own share of life. As she awaits the return of her beloved friend Jyothi, Manu gets closer to her. Despite their diverse upbringings, Manu and Chelly strike a serene and beautiful chord with each other. Their brief but intense encounter during the five nights makes the plot of the film set against the deep woods of Attappadi and surroundings.

Title: 1416. Namaste Bali
Content: A woman gets cheated by a man after their arranged engagement. The woman finds that the man had travelled to Bali and sets off to it.

Title: 1417. Suvarna Purushan
Content: Story about the ardent fans and loyal followers of the Malayalam megastar, Mohanlal. It revolves around a lady, the owner of the Mary Martha theatre and her struggles and fights with other theatre owners.

Title: 1418. Medulla Oblongata
Content: Medulla Oblongata is a Malayalam movie produced by S. Madhan and directed by Suresh Nair. It is a remake of Tamil film Naduvula Konjam Pakkatha Kaanom. The remake stars Rahul Madhav and newcomer Avaana.

Title: 1419. Elsamma Enna Aankutty
Content: The difficulties of a young girl who tries to raise her family.

Title: 1420. Karutha Joothan
Content: Aaron Eliyahu, a Jewish man, travels to a small village called Mala, Kerala in search of his Jewish heritage. Unfortunately, Aaron meets with a fatal motor accident that lands him in a state of coma in a hermitage.

Title: 1421. Choran
Content: Smita is in a position where she has no choice but to commit suicide. While tying the rope around her neck to hang herself, two thieves break into her house. What will happen next?

Title: 1422. 10:30 A.M. Local Call
Content: When a happily married Alby is confronted by his old love for help, things go wrong and a string of serial murders form the rest of the plot.

Title: 1423. Pattanathil Sundaran
Content: Shows the difficulties of a family in which the wife (Navya) works and the husband (Dileep) is left to take care of the house.

Title: 1424. Ms. Lekha Tharoor Kaanunnathu
Content: Ms. Lekha Tharoor is so intelligent and smart who is the anchor of a game show. Her encounters with some of the guests and some events that follow change their life in a totally unexpected way.

Title: 1425. Vith
Content: A son returns home to his father. The film revolves around the conflicts in values of the two.

Title: 1426. Nocturnal Times
Content: Hussain is a renowned researcher and one fine day he goes missing. Jahanara, his daughter, returns from Berlin and tries to find him for three months with no luck.

Title: 1428. Vamanapuram Bus Route
Content: Johnny, a bus conductor, is sent to Vamanapuram to clear a bus route, where he falls in love with his boss' daughter, who is already engaged. Johnny is now at cross roads.

Title: 1429. Pathinonnil Vyazham
Content: Appu works as a bearer in a five star hotel at Palakkad. He meets Chandran Pillai, a millionaire and begs to give him a job. Chandran refuses, but Appu tries to blackmail him with a secret.

Title: 1430. Mothathi Kozhappa
Content: Movie portrays a collection of odd characters and their lives taking an unexpected turn when an innocent character arrives and involves in their personal matters that embarks on the intricate web of myths along with a cross-border journey.

Title: 1431. Parayam
Content: Raju's father leaves no stone unturned in helping him find true love. Things go awry when he falls in love with Sudha, a young woman in love with someone else.

Title: 1432. Valathottu Thirinjal Nalamathe Veedu
Content: Aji, who buys old buildings, demolishes them and sells the scrap, goes ahead to demolish a building for which his father had taken a contract. But he faces objection from the owner's daughter.

Title: 1433. My 3
Content: Revolves around the bond between a group of friends who try their best to save one of their close buddies suffering from cancer.

Title: 1434. Cheraathukal
Content: There are six short films in this movie, each painting different shades of love.

Title: 1435. Kottarathil Kutty Bhootham
Content: Three children befriend a spirit and take him home. The spirit helps the children to overcome their problems but things get tough for the spirit when an evil sorcerer tries to hunt him down.

Title: 1436. John Honai
Content: John has an accident with a rich merchant named Devanarayanan and walks away with a blank cheque. John and his friends Jaffer and Janardhanan use the cheque to take a holiday trip in Dubai.

Title: 1437. Sasneham Sumithra
Content: Balan, a businessman and widower, marries another woman after his first wife dies under mysterious circumstances. However, things get complicated for him when her body is found in his home.

Title: 1438. Nithyaharitha Nayakan
Content: A heartwarming romantic comedy that follows a man as he goes through various stages of love - from the first crush to final break-up.

Title: 1439. Basheerinte Premalekhanam
Content: The story evolves around Basheer and Suhra's love and it's influence over the whole Chakkarakadav village.

Title: 1440. Onnam Loka Mahayudham
Content: A doctor, a police officer and a bunch of gangsters are involved in a deal worth 40 million, which goes awry.

Title: 1441. Nasrani
Content: David and Sara's marriage gets canceled due to an unexpected tragic event. Years later, they continue to love each other and strive to protect an innocent girl from an ambitious politician.

Title: 1442. Living Together
Content: Shyama falls in love with Hemachandran. However, she is not willing to marry him as she believes that either she or he will die soon after their marriage.

Title: 1444. Kannaki
Content: Villagers Manickan and Choman are very close friends. Manickan is in love with Kannaki and wants to marry her but Choman wants him to marry his sister.

Title: 1445. The Last Supper
Content: Three friends in quest for a documentary production in a haunted jungle as part of a 'Adventure Competition'.

Title: 1448. 100 Degree Celsius
Content: 100 Degree Celsius is a Malayalam Thriller, written and directed by Rakesh Gopan. A women-centric movie, starring Shwetha Menon, Meghna Raj, Bhama, Ananya and Haritha. Based on a real-life incident, the movie revolves around the lives of five women - a housewife, banker, IT professional, TV reporter and a college student. The movie takes a turn when the lives of all the 5 women turn upside down.

Title: 1449. Ithu Pathiramanal
Content: Eldho is waiting to take revenge on Shauriyar, who killed his father and mother when he was a young boy.

Title: 1450. Vasudha
Content: Vasudha works as a feature writer and an in-house photographer for a fashion magazine in the city of Mumbai. Like the millions in the city, she too shuttles between life and her family. A woman who despite being in the city of machines, has a caring heart that dreams and wishes for all the love in the world. Gautam, her husband, is a businessman and her only daughter, Nilanjana is on the verge of finishing her college. Both are the life and soul of Vasudha. She lives for them Suddenly destiny plays a trick on her when she perchance discovers that her husband is having an affair with Nikita, his colleague from work. A girl who is all that which Vasudha is not; a smart city girl, much younger in age and far more attractive than her. When Vasudha tries to win her husband back, Gautam snaps and tells her to go out, make friends, have an affair and enjoy the freedom of being in a city like Mumbai where anything goes and no one really cares to notice or criticize. Little did Gautam know that his insistence would result in Vasudha befriending a much younger man- Nihar, her daughter's close friend, who is a typical Mumbai bred Malayali boy, a street artist and an aspiring photographer, with a fresh perspective of life.

Title: 1451. Thobama
Content: Story and friendship of three childhood friends

Title: 1452. Ladoo
Content: Vinu and Angeline, a couple in love, decide to elope and get married. But when a bunch of friends gets involved, the plan itself starts spiraling out of control. The chaos that ensues forms the crux of Ladoo.

Title: 1453. Kolumittayi
Content: Unni and his friends move to the 6th grade after the new academic year begins. He loves his school life mainly because of his crush Riya and feels threatened by the newcomer in his class - Roney. Soon they lock horns and are in competition.

Title: 1454. The Way Home
Content: The plot revolves around a doctor with a haunting past. Now working at a Prison Hospital, the Doctor is assigned the case of a woman a surviving member from a notorious terrorist group. .Before dying she entrusts him to find her five-year-old son and unite him with his father who is the head of terrorist group. Finding the boy from a village the Doctor and child set out on a journey to find his father.The journey is happening through the contemporary and mysterious path of the terrorist network in the vast country with many incidents.

Title: 1455. Marathon Aarum pedikanda odikko
Content: Story of a small village called Aala in 2000s and the people over there. Vinod is a young lover struggling to make his love happen ,meanwhile a few incidents happening in the village turns everything upside down. Vinod in his run for love, meets with new people from his village who are on another mission. When these two meet each other there starts a series of events which in no way is under their control.

Title: 1456. Kilukkam Kilukilukkam
Content: After witnessing her father's murder at the hands of enemies, Chandni escapes to Ooty. Soon, Joji and a group of friends decide to trace her and save her life.

Title: 1457. Swapnarajyam
Content: A youngster hailing from a middle-class family must face off against overwhelming odds to succeed in life.

Title: 1459. Flash
Content: Dr. Mithun Madhavan uncovering the murder mystery in a joint family and how he helps Dhwani overcome from some disturbing experiences.

Title: 1460. Kesari
Content: A journey into the intellectual life of Kesari Balakrishna Pillai, who played a pivotal role in the making of Modern Kerala.

Title: 1462. 24 Days
Content: Stephen is a selfish, least bothered young unemployed graduate who sets out for a ride to the Himalayas along with an elite ride group and ends updifferent world of realization.

Title: 1463. Cover Story
Content: An engineer witnesses her neighbor, a judge, being murdered. Her poor eyesight, however, stands in the way of her identifying the killer, which makes her a prime suspect in the eyes of the police.

Title: 1464. Makante Achan
Content: Viswanathan, an honest village officer, wishes this son, Manu, to become an engineer. However, Manu has no interest in pursuing his studies and aspires to make a name for himself as a singer.

Title: 1466. Madhirashi
Content: Chandran Pillai, a widower who travels to Tamil Nadu to buy a cycle for his son but, drawn into a vicious circle when he goes on to probe the disappearance of Johny, a police constable.

Title: 1467. Gold Coins
Content: Achu and Kichu, hailing from a hamlet in Kumarakom live by their dream of owning a geared bicycle. In their journey towards their dream, the boys gets separated in the city and face unseen challenges.

Title: 1468. Thinkal Muthal Velli Vare
Content: Jayadevan is a most-wanted writer in the Malayalam Television industry, who pens the scripts for all major soap operas. Marriage brings a lot of changes to Jayadevan's life, and this forms the crux of the story.

Title: 1469. Patham Classile Pranayam
Content: Vivek and Sambhu are rival classmates. Both are infatuated with Meera but Meera is only interested in studies. Will Meera choose anyone? Their final exams are approaching fast.

Title: 1470. Aalolam Kili
Content: When Aishwarya is cheated by Sriram, a dance master in the film industry, she kills him. However, she soon lands into trouble, when she unknowingly marries Sriram's elder brother, a police officer.

Title: 1471. Team 5
Content: Akhil who is the back bone of his gang participates in racing tournaments all around the city along with his gang mates. Akhil's life takes a dramatic turn when he falls in love with an event manager Irene.

Title: 1472. Oru Pennu Kaanal Kadha
Content: Prasanth and his family come to Chitra's house with a marriage proposal. They realize that they aren't meant to be together, so he embarks on a journey to find his soulmate.

Title: 1473. Thavalam
Content: Thavalam is a real life story of Muthu who lived around the Ernakulam bus stand. Sivan (Suresh Gopi) is a member of the gypsy group who roams around the cities to make a living. Sivan lives with his only daughter Meenakshi (Baby Diya) in a village named Mayilpetty. Dasan Menon and his wife Usha are regular visitors to the temple of the village. According to the local sayings, they also believe that if they come over to this temple three times in a month, they will be blessed with a child. In one of the visits, some of their money gets stolen and the blame falls on Meenakshi who passes around the temple. Both Sivan and his daughter are arrested for the robbery but in little time local tea shop owner, Panicker, arrives at the station with the actual culprit. Sivan and his little daughter are set free but the family finds an excessive interest in the father and his daughter and starts asking them about their life.

Title: 1474. 5il Oral Thaskaran
Content: The film unveils attitude of new generation who values friendship rather than parents. The tragedy of this thought is depicted in the movie and establishes that family values are above all. Computer engineer Vishnu, son of a Brigadier Rajasekhar Menon, brought up in a very strict environment is fond of freedom and exploring beauty and the beast. He leaves the house and joins a group of thieves lead by Swamy. Due to circumstances, the group of five leaves the town and happen to join a Cyber criminal Dharmarajan who is looting money from bank accounts in a fraud activity. Vishnu falls in love with a girl , daughter of Dharmarajan's sister, whose husband was killed by Dharmarajan and she was sent to forest. Dharmarajan traps Vishnu in a murder case but disposed victim's body without any proof. Inspector Shajahan helps Dharmarajan in all these, but when a new lady DYSP come to the village Narasimhapuram, all the case comes up. Vishnu and group are arrested and tortured to bring out the truth. Dharmarajan is arrested for his brother in law's murder. There the twist happens to the movie and unexpected incidents lead to climax.

Title: 1475. Ankarajyathe Jimmanmar
Content: A group of people happened to be meddled in a group of events because of a bag coming into their life

Title: 1476. Alice in Wonderland
Content: Alby and his mentally challenged sister, Alice, adore each other. But when two strangers, Sophia and Victor, enter their lives forming strong bonds with them, it leads to tension between the siblings.

Title: 1477. Kanmashi
Content: Vishnu brings about a change in the life of Sethulakshmi, who keeps avoiding marriage, and they begin to deal with the adverse situations in their lives together.

Title: 1478. Akasha Gopuram
Content: Albert Samson, a successful architect, and Alice are leading an unhappy married life because of Samson's ambitious and egoistic nature. Hilda Varghese enters Samson's life and changes it completely.

Title: 1479. Ottakkoru Kaamukan
Content: When a vengeful lover goes out seeking his revenge. It takes the audience through a fascinating ride of romantic sequences and relationships of families.

Title: 1481. Mullamottum Munthiricharum
Content: Churatta Jose, a local goon and an expert snake catcher is stabbed on his stomach by someone at night. A flash back reveals his early life.

Title: 1482. Currency
Content: A mentally disabled man along with an outsider makes fake currency refering some old damaged books,replace it with real money.They tries to transport it.anywhay a police force is behind to tackle them.

Title: 1483. Fathers Day
Content: Seetha, a tutor in a government college, is unmarried and lives with her brother--but a criminology student is spying on her and uncovers the dark, hidden secrets of her past.

Title: 1484. Millennium Stars
Content: Shiva and Shankar are wrongfully sent to prison as children where they meet a bully, Karunan. They escape and grow up to become popular singers. When the singing duo separates due to petty misunderstandings, Karunan tries to unite them.

Title: 1486. Marupadi
Content: The movie revolves around the family of Aby, his wife Sara, and their daughter Riya. When Aby gets a transfer to Kolkata, the family shifts to Kolkata where they have to encounter certain unexpected tragedies.

Title: 1487. Pakalpooram
Content: After the death of Gouridasan's father, he and his family are thrown out of their home. When he plans to steal the property papers, he realizes the house is really haunted by an evil spirit.

Title: 1488. Rakshasa Rajavu
Content: Police officer Ramanathan exposes the criminal activities of the state's finance minister and faces his wrath. However, things get complicated when the state CM's daughter falls in love with Naidu.

Title: 1489. Chirakodinja Kinavukal
Content: After 18 years, Ambujakshan decides to make hear his 'Thayyalkaran-Sumathi' love story to a director and producer after amending and modifying it, in order to make it a 'New Generation Film'.

Title: 1490. Theekuchiyum Panithulliyum
Content: Crime branch officer, Hari reopens a murder case that happened five years ago. The case was initially closed by the local police officials as a case of natural death but Hari smells a foul play and digs deep to find the truth.

Title: 1491. Garbhasreeman
Content: Sudeendran becomes a scapegoat to the famous gynecologist and scientist Dr Roy Mathew who is in search of a man to try his experiment on. He has made the male ones of animals pregnant and has to do the experiment on a man.

Title: 1492. Sooryakireedam
Content: Four friends end up staying in an ancestral house which is haunted by the spirit of Urmila. By the time they realize the truth about the house, things start getting worse.

Title: 1493. Doctor Innocentanu
Content: Doctor Bhargavan Pillai does not earn much as he is always helping the poor. However, when his wife demands ornaments to attend a wedding, he borrows a necklace from a pawnbroker, but she loses it.

Title: 1494. Ithinumappuram
Content: The story focuses on a woman who marries a man against the wishes of her family only to have him leave her. Will she succeed in bringing up her family all by herself while working at the same factory as her husband?

Title: 1495. Niraye Thathakalulla Maram
Content: An 8-year-old boy tries to help a blind man reach his home.

Title: 1496. Madhura Naranga
Content: Jeevan (Kunchacko Boban) and Salim (Biju Menon) are taxi drivers in Gulf.They live in a small apartment which they share with Kumar (Neeraj Madhav). A Sri Lanka Native Thamara Enters their life and they are forced to accommodate her in their apartment . The events happened in their life is the plot of Madhura Naranga. The Major locations of the film is UAE and Sri Lanka.

Title: 1497. Puthiya Theerangal
Content: The story is about an orphan girl, Thamara, who lives on the shores of a sea with her 3 best friends who are boys. One day, they chance upon a man drowning in the sea, (suicide attempt) and they set out on a journey to find out who he really is... This movie is of a different type - it portrays the simple life of fishermen family and is pretty funny and enjoyable watch.

Title: 1498. Oru Pazhaya Bomb Kadha
Content: Sreekuttan, a physically challenged young man, meets Shruthi after which he finds himself in the most challenging situation he has ever faced. Will he be able to come out of the situation or be overwhelmed by his physical inabilities?

Title: 1500. Daivanamathil
Content: The lives of Anwar and Sameera face many threats when Anwar goes in a wrong way.

Title: ﻿1501. Joker
Content: Babu has learned and perfected the art of being a clown and is promised the hand of Kamala, the circus owner's daughter. He loves Kamala, but Sudheer Mishra's arrival in the troupe changes everything.

Title: 1502. Kantharam
Content: Due to the restless sentiments Siddhartha books a honeymoon package from aditi dot com but the hopeful journey end up being dangerous for them.

Title: 1503. Hawk's Muffin
Content: Final Week of a Dystopian Hoax-Tale.

Title: 1504. Oru Visheshapetta Biriyani Kissa
Content: Tara, a blessed cook in a southern village, and the funny series of events related to a suspended biriyani offering that the villagers attempt to restart.

Title: 1505. Shajahanum Pareekuttiyum
Content: Jiya is a rich girl who has a distinctive personality and has great hopes and dreams. An unfortunate incident shook her life. At this juncture two guys Pranav and Prince enter Jiya's life with definite intentions.

Title: 1506. Shubhadinam
Content: Zithin, an ordinary man, chose a path as a solution to many problems in life. He has great faith in time and finds a good day to implement it. He embarks on that adventure with complete confidence.

Title: 1508. St. Marysile Kolapathakam
Content: Pooja and Meera stay at St Mary's Working Women's Hostel. One day when they reach the hostel after work, they are welcomed with the shocking news of a murder.

Title: 1509. 3 Dots
Content: Three ex-convicts live together and try to start their lives afresh, but in vain. They reach out to their prison counselor; as per his advice they start their own work with his support until his true intentions are revealed.

Title: 1510. Eliyammachiyude Adhyathe Christmas
Content: Aliyamma, a lonely old woman whose children live abroad, lives in an old-age home and forms a special bond with Geo Mariam, a nun.

Title: 1511. Dum
Content: Dum is the story of a goon named Xavier and his henchman Antony and the struggle they face to achieve their goals. The film revolves around the life of a goon who regrets his past and seeks redemption through his lover Sherin.

Title: 1512. Karingunnam 6's
Content: Vandana and Aby are outstanding volleyball players. An accident changed Aby's life forever. Aby is so disheartened that his dream will never come true. Vandana sets off to Central Jail to select efficient players to fulfill Aby's wish.

Title: 1513. Homely Meals
Content: There are lot of people who are waiting for a chance in Television and film industry. Homely Meals is the story of one such character Alan. The movie is all about the life, dreams and passion of current generation.

Title: 1514. Again Kasargod Khader Bhai
Content: A troupe of artists perform in a prison where Kasim Bhai, a criminal who has a vendetta against them, is locked up. When Kasim Bhai is found murdered the next day, the troupe comes under suspicion.

Title: 1515. Isakkinte Ithihasam
Content: The parishioners decide to construct a new church leaving Fr. Isahak to temporarily move into Margi, a parishioner's house. In the meantime Margi's son Gregory and George Washington's daughter Clara elope.

Title: 1516. A Night A Day
Content: Daytime. A pair of lovers enter a house deserted by a flood. She has run away from home. He is not in a condition to start a life with her. The wind blows heavy in the fields of long grass.

Title: 1517. Ghost Villa
Content: Businessman Ravuthar, who owns a haunted bungalow, tries several ways to exorcise the ghosts in the bungalow. With Ravuthar's permission, a young man named Anand sets his mind on defeating the invisible power in the bungalow.

Title: 1519. English: An Autumn in London
Content: English is a Malayalam film written by Ajayan Venugopalan and directed by Shyamaprasad. A drama with slight tinges of black humour and satire. The film tells the story of the lives of the Malayalees living in London.

Title: 1520. Gila
Content: Gila is a romantic techno thriller Film happening on an imaginary magical island called Gila. The protagonist is an IT professional, Unni who is survived by his jovial father' Mr. Narayanan is working in a startup where he falls in love with his colleague Ann. Meanwhile, a nexus is trying to tap a million-dollar patented mobile game idea and for that, a series of murders happen, finally, Unni becomes their target since that idea was his brainchild. An investigation team led by officer Rishi and Abey from the cyber cell and their colleague Sruthy saves Unni from the nexus and with his help, they break the nexus and capture the killer Alex. Through this, Gila tells the story of the war between information technology and man.

Title: 1521. Swarnam
Content: Divakaran is a selfish, stingy man who dislikes his wife Radha and her orphaned niece. When he fails to buy a truck himself, he decides to try his luck by looking for mythical gold buried in a river.

Title: 1522. Paviyettante Madhurachooral
Content: Pavithran master and Annie teacher who teach at a high school. Popular for their farming and nature-friendly life, the couple is highly respected in the village. One fine morning, a fifteen-year-old boy named Anandu enters their lives.

Title: 1523. Pengalila
Content: An unusual bond between a sixty year old Dalit worker Azhagan and an eight year old middle class girl Radha. Within no time their bond grows stronger. However, his proximity to Radha and her mother doesn't go down well with Radha's father.

Title: 1524. Swapna Sanchari
Content: Ajayachandran immigrates to the Gulf and he makes his fortune and returns to Kerala for a holiday. Ajayachandran flaunts his wealth to gain social acceptance. Rashmi, Ajayachandrans wife, a grounded young woman who is not too comfortable with her husbands new, flashy lifestyle. However, soon, all of Ajayachandrans calculations about life go wrong. An incident occurs and changes his life forever.

Title: 1525. Samrajyam II: Son of Alexander
Content: The film is a sequel to evergreen Mammooty's gangster film Samrajyam that came out in 1990. The film plots the eventful life of Jordan who is forced to take charge of his father's empire after 23 years.

Title: 1526. Maalgudi Days
Content: The movie is set in the backdrop of an imaginary school named Malgudi Residential School. The movie revolves around a mysterious man Zephan Solomon and two students of this school.

Title: 1527. Adiyaan
Content: The movie deals with the experience of a backward class person who falls in love with the daughter of the Police Superintendent.

Title: 1528. Uru
Content: The movie chronicles the lives of people connected to Uru manufacturing in Beypore.

Title: 1529. Love FM
Content: Love FM revolves around a radio that plays a crucial role in the love story. It is a romantic movie where it touches upon the love stories of two generations.

Title: 1530. Nerchappetty
Content: A Love Story Between a Nun and a Village Boy and Its Consequenses on the Community

Title: 1531. Law Point
Content: Sathya is a leading criminal advocate. After successfully winning a rape case against the victim Sainnabam he is now consulted to handle a compromising situation regarding the suicide attempt of Maya. Dealing with her and her father. Sathya comes to the conclusion that Maya is very intelligent and bold and it's not easy to convince her or her father. He keeps calm and asks her father to take her on a long drive.

Title: 1532. Oru Canadian Diary
Content: Sara migrates to Canada and keeps in touch with Surya. However, a few days later, the calls stop. Once Surya reaches Toronto, he begins his search to locate Sara.

Title: 1533. Meezan
Content: An enigmatic story of an innocent friendship between Koyakutty, an orphan devout Muslim and his childhood friend Jamaal who values his friend more than himself.

Title: 1535. Abode
Content: A 70-year-old widowed woman on the verge of being sent to an old age home makes a decision that shocks her family.

Title: 1536. My Great Grandfather
Content: A 54 year old young looking grand dad is planning to marry a girl of his daughters age

Title: 1537. July 4
Content: Gokul Das, an ex-gangster tries to make a living by becoming the driver of a millionaire, whose daughter, Priya is the target of some killers. Das tries to save Priya, but things are not what they seem to appear.

Title: 1538. Ivar
Content: Raghava Menon, an undercover cop, enters a mafia gang led by Jose and becomes his private henchmen with the intention of exposing and destroying their entire illegitimate business.

Title: 1539. Bhoopadathil Illatha Oridam
Content: Madhavankutty (Sreenivasan) is a school teacher in a small interior village where nothing much happens. The village is identity-less as the title suggests. So, when a theft happens in a moneylender's shop, everyone around is baffled. It gives sleepless nights to the panchayat president (Nedumudi Venu) and the police officer in charge of the area (Innocent). As they have no inkling about who the culprit may be, they device a plan to catch someone with a previous record. Madhavankutty is the sole eye witness as the shop is visible from the place where he lives. A major part of the story is devoted to showing how Madhavankutty dodges the pressure tactics of the police and counters their arguments. Parallel to this, we have the typical life and politics of a village: people discussing issues in the teashop, the ruling coalition bringing in modernisation by buying a coconut tree climbing machine that even women can use, the opposition taking out marches and walking out of panchayat meetings.

Title: 1540. Yamam
Content: Yamam is a 2002 Indian Malayalam film, directed by Shree and produced by D. Sajith. The film stars Maria, Reshma and Roshni in lead roles. The music of the film was composed by S.P. Bhoopathi.

Title: 1541. Kaitholachathan
Content: It showcases the journey of Prakashan through different mysterious elements and his encounters with Kaitholachathan and Iruttu Gulikan.

Title: 1542. Spanish Masala
Content: Charlie works at an Indian restaurant in Spain. Skilled in imitating voices, he becomes close to his employer's blind daughter by imitating her lost boyfriend's voice and tries to reunite them.

Title: 1544. Kala Viplavam Pranayam
Content: Kala Viplavam Pranayam is a story of four school friends trying to figure out their interests and options after school.

Title: 1546. Korappan the Great
Content: A group of friends head out into the jungle to capture a wanted deadly fugitive, Korappan to get a cash reward offered.

Title: 1549. Nadodi Mannan
Content: Padmanabhan is a youth who earns by participating in any protest by any political party. After a work in Trivandrum, he became a popular figure there and became the Mayor of Trivandrum.

Title: 1550. Snehapoorvam Anna
Content: Anna's father dreams of getting her married to the person of his choice. But the relationship between Anna and her father worsens when she falls in love with a guy of her choice.

Title: 1552. The Filmstaar
Content: Nandagopan writes his life story and meets a superstar with the dream of making it into a movie. But, he abandons his idea when the star behaves rudely. Things change when the star reads his script.

Title: 1553. August Club
Content: 'August Club' is a Malayalam romantic drama directed by K. B. Venu. Rima Kallingal stars in the story about the nuances in marital life. Savithri is a happily-married young homemaker and an uncrowned chess champion in a nearby local club. Surprisingly, she is defeated in a game of chess by a newcomer at the club. They get engaged in an emotional game of music and poetry while playing chess.

Title: 1554. Kumbasaaram
Content: Alby is an autorickshaw driver andis wife is Meera (Honey Rose). They pin all their hopes on their only son Jerry whose close friends are Rasool, Tinu, and Malu. The movie narrates the deep friendship shared between these friends and the unexpected events in the life of Alby.

Title: 1555. Bharya Athra Pora
Content: Satyanathan is a school teacher and his wife Priya is a bank employee, lead a happy life together until he becomes an alcoholic and ends up completely avoiding his family.

Title: 1556. Pathinaram Prayathil
Content: Pathinaram Prayathil is a 2002 Indian Malayalam film, directed and produced by Baboos. The film stars Bhavana, Hema, Lekha Pande and Roshan in lead roles. The music of the film was composed by Baboos. The story revolves around a teenage girl and her sexual escapades.

Title: 1557. Matinee
Content: Najeeb, a young man and Savithri, a poor woman dream to become movie stars. Luckily, they receive an opportunity to work as lead actors in a film, but it cause problems in their lives.

Title: 1558. Paachuvum kovalanum
Content: Pachu, a successful television director, is troubled by the interference of his cousin Kovalan, an assistant director. Mayhem ensues when they are framed for a murder.

Title: 1559. Hariharan Pillai Happy Aanu
Content: Hariharan, a construction company owner, builds a house for Satyapalan, who refuses to pay him. However, things take an unexpected turn when Satyapalan's daughter falls in love with Hariharan.

Title: 1560. Sexy Durga
Content: Durga, a north Indian migrant and a Keralite youth named Kabeer are running away on a midnight. The hapless Durga encounters a cross section of the society through the rest of the night.

Title: 1561. Theyya Theyyam
Content: THEYYA THEYYAM - 'Theyyam' can roughly be treated as there-incarnation of a soul. In the folk rituals of North Malabar dead war heroes are sometimes raised to the status of Theyyam. Thus Theyya Theyyam is the double incarnation of a soul.When Theyyam is being performed, the dead hero is usually elevated to the status of a God in the eyes of the villagers.

Title: 1562. Fort Kochi
Content: An efficient police officer goes in search of a criminal who murdered a cop. She seeks the help of her husband who is an advocate, unaware that he is the murderer.

Title: 1563. Kolamass
Content: Shyam and Vandana head to a bigger city to start a new life and business.

Title: 1564. Kanaka Simhasanam
Content: Kanakambaran(Jayaram) owner/actor of a failing theatrical company gets a chance to enact a real-life drama.

Title: 1565. Kaanchi
Content: Madhavan, a grocery shop owner, witnesses the murder of Thomas, the Son of an influential man in the city. He is hell-bent on getting the murderer behind bars.

Title: 1567. Monayi Angane Aanayi
Content: Monayi goes to stay with his friends in an unknown habitat. He happens to face a few problems, but he comes up with ridiculous ideas to deal with his problems.

Title: 1568. Aayirathil Oruvan
Content: Aravindan borrows a huge sum of money for his sister's marriage. Soon, as he strives hard to repay the moneylender, he finds himself in the middle of a vicious debt trap.

Title: 1569. Poovalliyum Kunjadum
Content: Poovalliyum Kunjadum is a Malayalam movie starring Arya Manikandan and Basil George in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Farookh Ahamadali.

Title: 1572. Popcorn
Content: Kinder comes in search of his love to Kerala from his hometown. He comes across Joy and they jointly try to track the lady. He meets Sharon who is in pursuit of her absconding boyfriend and she offers him wealth if he assists her.

Title: 1573. The Metro
Content: Harikrishnan who has arrived from Saudi Arabia to take part in his sisters wedding. He decides to run an errand for a friend in Saudi and is on his way to Pala to deliver a parcel. After the job is done, Harikrishnan along with five friends travel to Kochi, where the unexpected awaits for them.

Title: 1574. Moonamghattam
Content: The protagonist identifies two phases in his present life after meeting his soul. Unknowingly, he is living his present life to fulfill the karma from his past life. This mystery later unfolds the truth behind the case of a missing person.

Title: 1575. Chembarathipoo
Content: Vinod, a young guy who is nursing a broken heart after a failed first love is helped by his friends to recover from despair, only to fall head over heels in love with another girl.

Title: 1576. Innumuthal
Content: The life of Abhinandhan, an ardent devotee of Lord Krishna, turns upside down after a stranger arrives to meet him.

Title: 1577. Unmadiyude Maranam
Content: A man named Unmadi's dreams causes disturbances in the society as his fellow citizens also start watching his dreams. Authorities insist him to censor his dreams before he start seeing them and when he denies the same they ban him from dreaming. But People of his country start watching his dreams illegally and start spreading it.

Title: 1578. Kerala House Udan Vilpanakku
Content: Trouble starts for Dinesh (Jayasurya) when he sells a house located on the Kerala-Tamil Nadu border.

Title: 1579. Payum Puli
Content: A recovery agent for loan sharks manages to find a house in the city but the landlady dislikes him. However, he comes to her rescue when an eviction notice is served on her house.

Title: 1584. Ithu Nammude Katha
Content: The story revolves around a girl with many problems. She enters the life of a group of three youngsters.

Title: 1585. Pigman
Content: A son of an idealistic political activist, is determined to get a doctorate in linguistics. Although mired in poverty, he works hard on his thesis. But his life is made difficult by his research guide and his thesis gets rejected. He decides to abandon his studies and find a job. That's when his friend, helps him get a job at a pig farm. When he opposes some unhealthy practices at his workplace, he is relegated to a menial job at the pig sty. Eventually, the travails that he has to undergo shatter his youthful idealism.

Title: 1586. Aakaashathinu Thazhe
Content: The upper caste bureaucrats look down upon people based on caste, and creed. It has worsened in today's world where these bureaucrats find it rebellious to shut them down, whenever a downtrodden raises their voice against the injustice.

Title: 1587. Kaanthi
Content: Neelamma, a tribal lady and single mother struggles to safeguard her blind daughter Kaanthi. In an attempt to donate eyes to Kaanthi, Neelamma plots to take her own life. Will such a sacrifice help Kaanthi to see the world?

Title: 1588. Aanakkallan
Content: A Police Officer seeks a conman's help to solve a murder conspiracy.

Title: 1589. Inspector Garud
Content: A corrupt police officer takes bribes to make up the amount that he paid to get the job.

Title: 1592. Njangalude Veettile Athidhikal
Content: After their daughter's tragic death, Advocate Manoj and Bhavana become depressed, and their marriage hits a rough patch when Bhavana suspects that Manoj is having an extramarital affair.

Title: 1593. Daffedar
Content: Daffedar Ayyappan is a genuine human being who has retired from government service but can't escape from the job as a daffedar even after his retirement. He continues to serve the common people.

Title: 1594. Susanna
Content: Susanna, a sex worker, earns money by being with five different men at the same time. Fortunately, the people around her do not judge her actions and find solace in her presence.

Title: 1595. Panth
