Content: Eight-year-old Amina is crazy about the game of football to an extent that her friends and family are fed up with it. To pursue her passion, she wants to have a football.

Title: 1596. Kambhoji
Content: The plot revolves around the real-life incident of the hanging of an artist in his Kathakali costume a first of its kind in the country and that too in Kerala, perhaps one of the most tragic and rarest of incidents.

Title: 1597. Entry
Content: The plot revolves around two parallel stories in the film, of which the first involves ACP Shreya and ACP Rishikesh who are married for long, but at the moment are on the brink of a divorce and live separately. The second story has Arjun, a student who loves his bike and is a bike mechanic. The duo ACP lead the investigation into the theft of bikes which take place in Kochi metro.

Title: 1598. Lechmi
Content: The main theme of the movie revolves around four bachelors. The story follows an incident that leads to unforeseen and dramatic changes in their lives.

Title: 1600. Ezhamathe Varavu
Content: A wild tiger causes havoc in a remote village and all hope rests on a brave hunter. An archaeologist and old crush of the hunter's wife comes into the mix to further the chaos.

Title: 1601. Aalorukkam
Content: Pappu Pisharadi, an aging man, is on a constant hunt for his son, who left him 16 years back, which is when he is brought to a hospital where he meets Dr. Seetha and Priyan, who promise to help him find his son.

Title: 1602. Karinkannan
Content: The superstition of an entire village has cast a shadow on Dasan's life since his childhood. The villagers are convinced that he has the evil eye, and they believe that being around Karinkannan Dasan is the recipe for disaster.

Title: 1603. Premasoothram
Content: A tale of two men falling for the same girl Ammukuty, who is completely oblivious of their love. While Prakashan and Suku fight amongst themselves for her love, a third man vying for it enters her life.

Title: 1605. Highway Police
Content: Two young men Mammad (Babu Antony) and Circle Inspector Jayachandran (Riyaz Khan) team up in their war against an underground mafia and smuggling ring while also avenging the deaths of their loved ones.

Title: 1606. Sukhamano Daveede
Content: Sughamano Daveede is a Malayalam movie starring Bhagath Manuel, Chethan Jayalal and Priyanka Nair in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Anup Chandran and Raja Mohan.

Title: 1607. Thudakkam
Content: Kalivardhanan, a valiant is brought up by a slum lord, Sulaiman. Soon, he becomes fond of a lady advocate whom Sulaiman dislikes. How will Kalivardhanan deal under these circumstances?

Title: 1608. Velakkariyayirunnalum Neeyen Mohavalli
Content: The movie highlights the issues of attachment and detachment in human relationships through the events that occur in the life of a girl before and after her romantic affair.

Title: 1609. Vedham
Content: A young college student reluctantly goes on a pilgrimage to Sabarimala on the insistence of his parents.

Title: 1610. Varkey
Content: Varky is a quotation Goon who does the dirty work for his Boss and when need be, even for cops. But chaos ensues when his Boss assigns him to kidnap a bride-to-be on the eve of her wedding.

Title: 1611. Ninam
Content: Monichan is having a peaceful and happiness life with his family includes wife Annamma and daughter Annie. After the entering of three medical students sent by Monichan's boss Mamballi Mamachan, Monichans life turned into a nightmare.

Title: 1613. Nadan
Content: Nadan is the story of a popular drama troupe owned by Devadas Sargavedi (Jayaram), which was previously possessed by his father and grandfather in the past, and speaks about the problems faced by the owner and his survival. The revival of this mighty art through the sustained effort of the talented theater artists form the crux of the narrative.

Title: 1614. Black Coffee
Content: Will cook Babu who shares a deep bond with Kalidasan return to the latter's house after their misunderstanding?

Title: 1615. Acha Dhin
Content: Set in the backdrop of God's own country, Kerala, Acha Din is the story of a family from Jharkhand who is now settled in Ernakulam, the buzzing business hub of Kerala.

Title: 1616. Ormayundo Ee Mukham
Content: A young businessman falls for a girl with short-term memory loss.

Title: 1617. I.G.
Content: A police officer fights against terrorism.

Title: 1619. Black Cat
Content: A police inspector gets beaten by the goons and loses his sanity and is taken care of by the village headman's daughter. But the inspector's girlfriend arrives from another village to take him back.

Title: 1620. Prabhuvinte Makkal
Content: The movie revolves around two brothers. One of them is an atheist (Mani) and the other is a spiritualist ( Siddharthan). Tension arises after Siddharthan leaves home in search of his spiritual needs.

Title: 1621. Swarna Malsyangal
Content: Four friends are all set to celebrate their vacation when they find out that their neighbor Jyothi is leaving for her home town. Curiosity leads the friends to do unexpected things, which in turn leads them into trouble.

Title: 1622. Quotation
Content: Arun sets out to take revenge on Maya, a street thug, for murdering his sister.

Title: 1623. Duplicate
Content: Shivan Kutty, a jobless youth, is unable to repay his mounting debts. However, his life turns upside down when he is mistaken for Jeevan, a wealthy businessman and his lookalike.

Title: 1624. Jamna Pyari
Content: Vasoottan an auto driver by profession, who is very good at heart and meanwhile he is an impetuous person. Once a MBA student happens to travel his auto with some hidden purposes.

Title: 1625. Ardhanaari
Content: The life and struggles of Manjula/Vinayan, a transgender person in Kerala.

Title: 1626. Sir C. P.
Content: Sir CP is a story about a fraud college owner who specializes in providing any degree, which is available in any university across the world, to his students. His work lands him in deep trouble and how he comes out of it forms the plot.

Title: 1627. Kaattum Mazhayum
Content: Kaattum Mazhayum is a Malayalam film directed by Hari Kumar and starring Lal and Unni Mukundan in lead roles. The rest of the cast includes Meera Nandan, Irshad, Praveena, Mamukoya, Sudheesh, Balachandran Chulllikad and Swasika,Kashi [Tapan]. Cinematography is done by M J Radhakrishanan. Kaattum Mazhayum was selected for 20th International Film Festival of Kerala. It was also screened at Bangalore International Film Festival and Delhi Habitat Film Festival. The film also won the Kerala State Award 2015 for Best Story and Film Critics Award for Second Best Film.

Title: 1628. Ningal Camera Nireekshanathilaanu
Content: The film revolves around a veteran photographer who is faced with an unexpected incident in his life. What follows is a series of thrilling investigations that take place while getting to the root of the incident.

Title: 1629. Krithyam
Content: Watch the full movie, Krithyam, only on Eros Now. Krithyam is a 2005 Indian Malayalam film, directed by Viji Thampi and produced by Sasi Ayyanchira. The film stars Prithviraj, Pavithra and Jagathy Sreekumar in lead roles. The film had musical score by Udayakumar.

Title: 1630. Ikkayude Shakadam
Content: Story of an ikka (actor mammootty) fan.

Title: 1631. 1000: Oru Note Paranja Katha
Content: An autistic youngster is sent to the ATM by his dad with the Pin number written on a 1000 rupee currency note. The currency note, that has started a voyage of its own, starts telling us its story, as it moves from one hand to the next.

Title: 1633. My Big Father
Content: The film exhibits a deep bonding between a son, Alby (Jayaram), and his father, Kunjumon (Ajaykumar), a dwarf. Things changes after Kunjumon faces a critical accident , which affects Alby's marriage-life.

Title: 1634. Innanu Aa Kalyanam
Content: Neelima and Aisha are engineering students. Their life takes a turn when they befriend Karthik, who studies in the same college, and his pal Kunjumon.

Title: 1635. Kinnara Thumbikal
Content: A young boy falls in love with his older cousin sister. Meanwhile, his lusty neighbor is also trying to seduce him.

Title: 1637. Pramukhan
Content: Pramukhan is a 2009 Indian Malayalam Flim,directed by Salim Baba and produced by Priyesh George & Biju John.The flim star Kalabhavan Mani, Sajith Raj & Vinutha Lal in lead roles.The music of the film was composed by Shyam Dharman.

Title: 1638. Mulla
Content: An orphaned baby brings a middle-class woman (Meera Nandan) closer to a goon (Dilip) and his people.

Title: 1639. Thureeyam
Content: An attempted suicide ends up a man who identifies himself as Ravunni in the care of a therapist to whom he narrates a story. But the story he narrates gets stranger as it goes.

Title: 1640. Jimmy Ee Veedinte Aiswaryam
Content: Jancy Vetilakaran and her family's entire life revolves around her pet dog Jimmy. So when she gets married, her relationship with her husband - also named Jimmy - takes a back seat. Dejected, Jimmy tries everything he can to become the object of her affections.

Title: 1641. Samarpanam
Content: The murder of a young girl brings together the three central characters that develop an inexplicable bond with the victim and amongst them. Consequences beyond their expectations await them.

Title: 1642. Locked In
Content: Richard Martin is a wealthy businessman and an Indo American writer. His daughter Jenifer, a college going girl who is known for having a positive outlook in life. But what was going well, took a turn for the worse.

Title: 1643. Ivar Vivahitharayal...?
Content: A youngly married couple cannot attach themselves.but will they join finally?

Title: 1644. Crossroad
Content: Crossroad is a first -of-its-kind portmanteau movie celebrating womanhood and tells the story of ten women, facing ten different life situations and explores how they tackle it.

Title: 1645. Mannamkattayum Kariyilayum: The clod and the dry leaf
Content: The movie is based on the fact that- there should be some hidden pieces of evidence in every human crime. The movie progresses with this concept, revealing some unexpected facts.

Title: 1646. Ee Mazha Then Mazha
Content: Rekha, a sales girl, struggles to earn a living. Narendran, a businessman, insults her in front of several people and she decides to take revenge against him.

Title: 1647. Nagaravaridhi Naduvil Njan
Content: The movie shows the life of Venu, who is a victim of treachery by his own family members. Venu's only aim in life is to get a MBBS admission for his daughter. For fulfilling his dream he decides to sell his property in town but fails miserably due to the intrusion of his family members. The resulting events are plotted in Nagara Varidhi Naduvil Njan.

Title: 1649. Satyameva Jayate
Content: Chandrachoodan, a righteous police officer, gets into trouble with his seniors because of his values. Despite being surrounded by corrupt officials, he vows to bring an underworld gangster to justice.

Title: 1650. Mullavalliyum Thenmavum
Content: Shelly and Rajasree, who are sculptors, fall in love. While they wait for their parents' approval to get married, Shelly falls down from a sculpture while working and gets paralyzed.

Title: 1651. Swapnam Kondu Thulabharam
Content: Aniyankuttan falls in love with Ammu, who wishes to marry his elder brother, Vishnu. When Aniyankuttan learns the truth about Ammu's love, he is enraged.

Title: 1652. Mangalathu Vasundhara
Content: Mangalathu Vasundhara is a Malayalam movie starring Shanthi Krishna and Krishna Ganesh in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by KS Sivakumar.

Title: 1653. Kadha Paranja Kadha
Content: Ebi, an architect from Dubai, comes to India in search of Jennifer, a blogger, and a storyteller. Whilst in India, Ebi joins Jennifer in her pursuit to help Arun, a violinist, who is going through a crisis.

Title: 1655. Nammal Thammil
Content: The movie narrates the story of two brothers and a friend and the ordeals that they have to face in their relationships due to vicious act of a student in the same college.

Title: 1656. Pothan Vava
Content: To proselytize to Christianity, Pothan Vava (Mammootty) visits his father by the advise of his mother. His father and mother were divorced before.

Title: 1657. Iratta Jeevitham
Content: A girl who ran away from home returns years later as a man and confronts his childhood sweetheart and his village.

Title: 1658. Ginger
Content: 'Ginger' is a humorous tale, set against the backdrop of a village. Two scheming thieves Jayaram and Sudheesh plan to rob Suresh Krishna and his wife Mallika's house, but in a quirk of fate, becomes a part of their life. .

Title: 1659. Kaashh
Content: Four friends kidnap a rich industrialist's daughter to make money. However, things take a turn when they are forced to break into a house and hold everyone inside hostage.

Title: 1660. Ziel
Content: Protagonist wakes up in his room with parts of his memory wiped out. He wanders the whole house in search of answers.

Title: 1662. Premanjaly
Content: Movie talks about the various issues faced by children, teenagers, and youth in the society, through the forbidden love of Hari and Mythili, which creates a rift between their respective families.

Title: 1665. Dreaming of Words
Content: Njattyela Sreedharan, a fourth standard drop-out, compiles a dictionary connecting four major Dravidian languages. Travelling across four states and doing extensive research, he spent twenty five years making the multilingual dictionary. This unique dictionary offers a comparative study of Malayalam, Kannada, Tamil and Telugu. 'Dreaming of Words' traces Sreedharan's life, work, love for languages and the struggles to get the dictionary published. The film also explores the linguistic and cultural diversity in India.

Title: 1666. Urumbukal Urangarilla
Content: Kelu and Benny, who are thieves, meet accidentally in their walks of life. They face many challenges as they go around to steal.

Title: 1667. Oru Avadhikaalam
Content: Four kids spending their vacation in a small village find a wounded dog and decide to keep it. But the village has this strange superstition that dogs bring bad luck. What can they do?

Title: 1668. Nayana
Content: Nayana is a seven-year old artist. While she displays sparks of talent as a sketcher, her parents discover that she cannot identify colours because of colour blindness. While in a hospital for the treatment, Nayana befriends a septuagenarian who shares similar vision issues. The film progresses on their treatment tracks and results.

Title: 1669. Savaari
Content: A man, Savari, does odd jobs in the town of Thrissur until, an incident happens that changes his life forever.

Title: 1670. Gulumaal: The Escape
Content: Jerry is a con man whose actions have led to separate from his family. One day, he helps Ravi, an escaped convict, evade the law and soon teams up with him to carry out a big heist.

Title: 1671. History of Joy
Content: History of Joy is a coming of age drama that narrates the story of Joy, a law student, and his tryst with destiny.

Title: 1672. One Way Ticket
Content: The story of crazy fans of superstars who go to any extent to promote their screen idols and their movies. They even sacrifice their own career trying to promote their favorite stars.

Title: 1673. Sufi Paranja Katha
Content: Our tale begins towards the end of the 19th century, when the British ruled Malabar, after the invasion of Tippu Sultan. The story explores the myth of the land, the history of its people, the love and passion of the protagonists and the mystical spirituality of tolerance. The plot revolves around the love and marriage of Karthi, the Hindu heiress of a wealthy Nair Tharavaadu, with Maamootty, a wandering Muslim trader in coconuts and spices. On another plane, the film is about the transformation of Karthi to a Biwi, a local Goddess worshipped by the Hindus and the Muslims alike.

Title: 1676. Ente Mazha
Content: The journey of Balu, a boy with speech difficulties, who is part of a musical family grows up to conquer his problems. The movie is a nostalgic musical family entertainer.

Title: 1677. Savithriyute Aranjanam
Content: Ramunni is an innocent money lender. He lends some money to Neelakantan after taking the gold aranjanam (waist band) as security. After that, all the problems start in Ramunni's life.

Title: 1678. Anyarku Praveshanamilla
Content: This Movie explains the critical issues, when friends and outsiders are given undue importance and involvement in a family's personal space. Every issue is shared meaningfully and with humor touch throughout this film. Title Anyarku Praveshanamilla is thus given appropriately to safeguard family's personal space

Title: 1679. Bharathan
Content: A science enthusiast making an extraordinary discovery is considered lunatic by the society. He has to prove them wrong.

Title: 1680. Mayilattam
Content: Devan an honest farmer and recipient of karshaka sree award is in a run for his life after getting into fight with local rowdy.His life changes when he finds out he has a doppelganger with exact opposite character of him and interchange their lives with eachother.

Title: 1681. Gowri
Content: The story is about a group of youngsters who got a passion for filmmaking. It is upon Joy, Gouri, and Ajay who visits a bungalow for the sake of a film and their fearful and dangerous circumstances. Gouri is missing from the next day of their arrival. The bungalow house is said to be haunted. What might'v happened to her? Can Ajay and Joy rescue her? Did the spirits attack Gouri? The plot thickens with such questions. The movie got a good script including a lot of twists and turns to keep up suspense till the end. Archana Sushilan is the protagonist in Gouri. The movie was produced for AStar creations by Kannan Shekharen and been written and directed by Sujith Vinayak. The story is about a group of youngsters who got a passion for filmmaking. It is upon Joy, Gouri, and Ajay who visits a bungalow for the sake of a film and their fearful and dangerous circumstances. Gouri is missing from the next day of their arrival. The bungalow house is said to be haunted. What might'v happened to her? Can Ajay and Joy rescue her? Did the spirits attack Gouri? The plot thickens with such questions. The movie got a good script including a lot of twists and turns to keep up suspense till the end. Archana Sushilan is the protagonist in Gouri. The movie was produced for AStar creations by Kannan Shekharen and been written and directed by Sujith Vinayak. The story is about a group of youngsters who got a passion for filmmaking. The bungalow house is said to be haunted. What might'v happened to her? Can Ajay and Joy rescue her? Did the spirits attack Gouri? The plot thickens with such questions. The movie got a good script including a lot of twists and turns to keep up suspense till the end. Archana Sushilan is the protagonist in Gouri. The movie was produced for AStar creations by Kannan Shekharen and been written and directed by Sujith Vinayak.

Title: 1682. Kunthapura
Content: In 1928, Kunthapura, a remote village in central Karnataka was excavated by the Archeological survey. The Excavation brings a lot of troubles to the village which forces them to take arms against the British. The memories of an Eighty nine year old man, Krishnappa Narasimha Shashtri brings it to the notice of public in 2011.

Title: 1683. The Living Gods
Content: The Living Gods- Can an artist dare to break the social code by performing a religious ritual as a pure art form? 'Living Gods' follows the journey of Rajesh, a phenomenal Theyyam artist, and his playful seven year old son Gokul, from a small village in Kerala to the city of Wroclaw in Poland. Will Rajesh be able to mesmerize the western audience with his world of mythological gods, colors, fire, drumming and dance? Or will Gokul be the last generation of Theyyam artists?

Title: 1684. Rockstar
Content: Ananth is very passionate about music in his life. Quite unexpectedly, in one of his music trips, he comes across fashion stylist Athira. They have varied perspective, attitude, and vision about life.

Title: 1685. Fancy Dress
Content: Two guys think a big-time crime will turn things around for them in life. Will it?

Title: 1686. Ave Maria
Content: Rex, a diffident, pervasive man who works as a driver in the holy town of Velankanni meets Maria Gomez, a catholic devotee with strong religious beliefs, in a peculiar situation during one of his debaucheries. Maria later takes the help of Rex for completing couple of her errands, gets acquainted with him further and it ends up changing both their lives in the most unexpected of ways.

Title: 1687. Aala
Content: Radha, the daughter of blacksmith, Narayanan, falls in love with Unnikrishnan, the new postman in town. Their love is however opposed by the evil moneylender, Kaalimuthu.

Title: 1689. Banking Hours 10 to 4
Content: A busy bank branch is under observation by a group of police officers during the banking hours under information of a possible bank robbery. However, they are in for a surprise.

Title: 1690. Nimisham
Content: An army officer takes early retirement to protect his teenage daughter from the dangers of the world. However, despite providing extraordinary protection, his worst nightmare comes true and his daughter goes missing.

Title: 1691. Valkannadi
Content: Appunni is a blacksmith who has a history of mental health problems in his family. He is sent to an Ayurvedic asylum, after which a sea change begins to take place in his life.

Title: 1692. Karma Cartel
Content: A multi-award winning, avant-garde Indian Indie set In a southern city of India, following a reporters search for a missing actor, leads to revelation of multiple lives connected to it through greed and bad choices.

Title: 1694. Bolivia
Content: A female activist and her friends are trying to solve the mystery behind the death of a housewife and her missing son. However, during the course of the investigation, they are presented with many facts which make the case more complicated.

Title: 1695. Zacharia Pothen Jeevichirippundu
Content: Zacharia Pothen is a 40-year-old retired Major. He got married only after his retirement and was living happily with his wife. Suddenly one fine day, some of his old friends came there with hidden intentions.

Title: 1696. I Love Me
Content: Ram Mohan, an eminent businessman in Bangkok, has discovered that his business empire and personal life are in danger. To save himself, he hires two small-time crooks from India to murder a person.

Title: 1697. Contessa
Content: The film narrates the story of 2 friends Chandu and Saddam Hussein and the way everything changes once a Contessa comes into their lives.

Title: 1698. Thaskara Veeran
Content: Arakkalam Kochu Baby takes revenge on Eapen who murdered his father and vows to destroy his immense wealth

Title: 1699. Appuram Bengal Ippuram Thiruvithamkoor
Content: Three friends live in a room in a rented house owned by a politician. In another part of this rented house, comes a Bengali family. The arrival of the Bengali family disrupts the happy life of the three friends.

Title: 1701. Mythily Veendum Varunnu
Content: After losing her father, a girl takes up the responsibility of her mother. She then moves to the city in search of a job. Upon getting the job, her job takes her to a bungalow, where she is subject to a series of horrible situations.

Title: 1702. Sheelabathi
Content: Sheelabhati along with her mother visits a remote village where she starts working as a computer teacher. When some students mysteriously disappear, the villagers start blaming her educational course.

Title: 1703. Hadiyya
Content: A story of a man and two women from different parts of India. Some interesting common elements, coupled with a few twists and turns in their life bring them together.

Title: 1704. Orapara Kalyana Vishesham
Content: The movie revolves around a group of young men who are struggling to find a marital match due to a lack of government jobs.

Title: 1705. 168 Hours
Content: This horror thriller revolves around the 168 hours of a married couple. Many scary events creep into their life and this forms the crux of the movie.

Title: 1706. Mylanchi Monjulla Veedu
Content: Kasim's daughter Vahida elopes with her boyfriend Madhavan on the day of her wedding. Years later, Madhavan, in the disguise of a Muslim man, goes to treat the paralysed Kasim.

Title: 1707. Moral Nights
Content: Vishudha Rathrikal (Moral Nights) is an anthology of five stories. These stories, with a touch of satire, projects caste system, pseudo moral values, gender inequality prevalent in the contemporary society.

Title: 1708. Kancheepurathe Kalyanam
Content: Kalarikkal Achuthankutty and Pattarumatathil Najeeb are best friends and run an event management company. But soon they part ways because Najeeb secretly marries Achuthankutty's sister Athira.

Title: 1709. Out of Range
Content: Jerin (Ajayaghosh), at crossroads with his stagnant love life; Subru Vishnu Unnikrishnan), fed up with his mom's argumentative nature; Sanjay (Sumith Samudra), all against his reckless job schedule; Aashiq (Askar Ali), annoyed with unending family obligations - are four friends with instability in their lives. On one decisive night, the four friends take an unusual oath, to quit using their mobile phones forever. From the next daybreak, the world around them turns upside down. Sacking, break-up, and resentment follows. After the initial chaos, they seem to enjoy the peace, ease, and all the joys. However, this is just the beginning of another story. A steely resolve for more adventure, more determination, more drama, and more blows. Will they live to tell the tale?

Title: 1710. Malabar Wedding
Content: Maanukkuttan and Smitha lead a happy life after getting married to each other. But their marital life is put at stake due to their friends playing pranks on them.

Title: 1711. Vallikkettu
Content: Boy and girl fell in love but seems she have some issues with his attitudes. A bullying boy with bad friends.

Title: 1712. Junior Senior
Content: A rich man is a well known flirt who lures women by making them fall into his trap. His employee is forced to fight when he sees that his boss is trying the same to woo his girl.

Title: 1715. Little Superman
Content: Willy Wilson, a 12 year old comic book aficionado. Willy falls into a manhole and gets trapped inside it for days and soon figures out that he has the ability to fly and lift things up with the help of telekinesis.

Title: 1716. Ente
Content: Provocative, shocking and surprisingly tender amidst an explosion of unbridled emotions, "ENTE..."(Mine...) explores the consequences of sex trafficking, testing the vulnerability of trust in human relations. Srinivas(Siddiq) is a wonderful and devoted father to Durga(Anjali Patil), and he provides her the best. Working in the city and maintaining his family in a small town works well for him for years. One day everything is shattered when Durga comes unannounced to the city to appear for an interview concerning her college admission. Durga's life is brutally torn apart as Srinivas wrestles with grief, remorse, self pity and guilt. Prathyayam marks the telugu debut feature for both Siddiq and Anjali Patil. The filmmaker Rajesh Touchriver of the "In the name of Buddha" fame has specialized in innovative pictures that takes challenging risks. The film stars Siddiq, Anjali Patil, Lakshmi Men on, Ratnashekhar, Anup Arvindan, Nina Kurup, Warren Joseph and Sunil Kudvattoor. The cinematography is by the very talented Ramathulasi with Rajiv Nair as the art director. Don Max is the editor. The fantastic music and Music is done by Shantanu Moitra of the 'Three Idiots' fame and Shareeth did 3 wonderful songs too

Title: 1717. Sachin
Content: Sachin's father named him after the great Sachin Tendulkar. So, just like Tendulkar when he falls for a girl older than him, the youngster starts believing that perhaps he shares a lot more in common with his idol than just a name.

Title: 1718. Raktharakshassu
Content: The plot revolves around a renowned writer, his wife who is a fashion designer and their 7-year-old daughter. Upon being insisted by his young and fun-loving wife, he plans a family vacation at an island called Bungalow.

Title: 1719. CR No: 89
Content: A Jeep breaks down over the road through an old Forest road... Two men get out and look for a mechanic... They find one.. but when he reached at the spot he finds something fishy.. and the story revolves around these men...

Title: 1720. Shivam
Content: Bhadran, an efficient police officer, fights against all the injustice in the society. He faces many challenges when he encounters Devarajan, a smuggler.

Title: 1721. Jalolsavam
Content: With his father's death, Chandran takes the responsibility of his family along with the debts that his father has left behind. He also has to save his love from getting married to someone else.

Title: 1722. Best of Luck
Content: Four youngsters, Surya, Manu, Neethu and Dia, who have no-one but each other in life. As luck would have it, some rich Nayikar in some distant village reveals a secret on his death bed that Surya is his son.

Title: 1723. Anan
Content: Anan is a Malayalam drama movie, directed by Praveen Rana. The cast of Anan includes Indrans,Manikandan Achari.

Title: 1724. Stop Violence
Content: Saathan, a thug, rapes Angelina who later becomes pregnant. Over time he falls in love with her but his gang leader does not approve of their relationship.

Title: 1725. Yathra Chodikkathe
Content: Yathra Chothikathe is a movie with a social message and focuses on the problem faced by women in today's society.

Title: 1726. Vanyam
Content: The film revolves around the reckless life of three youngsters who maliciously plan a heinous act of violence and the aftermath of their act.

Title: 1727. Romeo
Content: The life of a male nurse Manu takes a turn when a doctor, a reality show contestant and a village girl fall in love with him. He must look for ways to untangle the cobwebs that form as a result.

Title: 1844. Amoeba
Content: Kerala famously known as Gods own country is, endowed with natural beauty with its lush green landscapes and rivers crisscrossing the length and breadth of the state. At the northernmost part of Kerala, is the Kasargod district, once bestowed with greenery, is now a haunted place. The use of endosulfan, a highly dangerous pesticide, had catapulted the entire area, a land of diseases and trauma. Widespread use of Endosulfan at cashew plantations, had not only killed pests, but affected the ecological balance of the area and severely affected humans and animals alike and resulted in diseases ranging from physical deformity to genetic problems, thus making the entire district a symbol of morbidity. Following widespread agitation against the usage of endosulfan, its use has been stopped by the government, but neverthless decades of widespread usage had killed thousands and made many more living victims. Having seen and experienced this atrocious use of chemicals and its side effects at Kasargod which is nearby my native, I though of a film on this issue, through which I could bring into limelight and make people aware, the tragedy of unethical use of chemicals and other pesticides.

Title: 1869. Vattamesha Sammelanam
Content: It feels like that old psychological trick. Lower expectations by suggesting that something is the pits and then, people will feel that, 'hey, actually it is not bad in the least'. That conceit doesn't quite work with Vattamesha Sammelanam, an anthology of six shorts, surprisingly featuring some big names like filmmakers Jibu Jacob, Jude Anthany Joseph and Major Ravi, who makes a jibe on himself. While the slogan boldly suggests it is 'The Flop Film', the film ends (and don't worry about the spoiler alert) saying that actually it is a hit and much enjoyed by audiences. The film is about an underworld don from Mumbai named Jaggubhai Khurana Saheb (Shashi Kalinga) who is in Kerala to produce a flop film to write off his black money. Based on the advice of a famous astrologer, he sets out to produce an anthology of shorts, with the worst scripts, cast and crew. Humour based on stomach upset is funny in general, but it is also the last resort of a comedian. Atley uses the trope in two of the short films here, one that he directed and another that he wrote. And both of them were unfunny and devoid of any deeper meaning. Known for his meta humour, Atley uses a lot of movie references, mostly to dismal effect. And since the film is made by the Kochi fraternity, they also make snide remarks about southern districts in Kerala. The attempt to satirise Kannada and Telugu films misses the mark. The makers could have easily kept it under 120 minutes and spared the audience the torture-the supposed comical pursuit of Jaggubhai by Major Ravi playing a police officer.

Thampy antony, Sreenivasan, Jagathy Sreekumar and Shweta Menon are playing leading characters in 'Parudeesa'. The film Parudeesa is produced under the banner of Kayal films by producer Thampy Antony. Screen play and dialogues are written by Vinu Abraham, the young writer. R Sarath handles the megaphone of this film titled as Parudeesa, Parudeesa is the malayalam word used for the word, Paradise.

Title: 1873. Karie
Content: Karie means Black. While there are tonal variations in culture across the southern multicultural, multi-religious Indian state called Kerala, one thing that remains unchanged is the caste system. Caste is the dangerous villain that creates irreparable damage to the social fabric and ostracizes individuals based on their skin tone. Karie explores the intricacies and power equations in the grim caste system in the form of the dialects and subtle language nuances influenced by caste. The film travels through the village with two men whose mission is to conduct a ritual on behalf of their colleague who works abroad.

Title: 1874. Day Night Game
Content: Day Night Game is a 2014 Malayalam movie directed by Shibu Prabhakar starring Jithan Ramesh, Maqbool Salmaan, Archana Kavi and Bhagath Manuel. The movie is produced by Shyju NP and the music composed by Jinosh Antony.

Title: 1875. Cycle
Content: Two friends get busted for drug possession and the illegal ways they go through to gather money for the bribe.

Title: 1876. Lokanathan I.A.S
Content: Lokanathan, an honest IAS officer from the slums, who is also an auto driver, fights against the criminal activities of a corrupt politician.

Title: 1877. Ormma
Content: Jayakrishnan, an activist who is relentlessly fighting for the cause of nature, marries an orphan girl Rajashree, against the will of his family. Things take a turn when he is killed.

Title: 1879. Nani
Content: After 2005, when worrying statistics were being discussed around relating to the serious nature of atmospheric pollution in Delhi, Devika, noting the severe pulmonary illnesses that were badly affecting her daughter Ammu (Catherine), decides to send her to Kochi in the southern state of Kerala in India. Kochi, at that time, was a city with much less pollution as it had plenty of water bodies and greenery. In her native place, ammu with Deedi who is of tremendous help to her in everything. Ammu, who is in Kochi after some times, finds a new lease of life for herself interacting with even the tiniest creatures in nature. NANI, the film, unveils the mystic matters and realities that strike life as she comes in close contact with nature.

Title: 1880. Parthan Kanda Paralokam
Content: Parthasarathy is loved by all his villagers as he works for the welfare of the people. He falls in love with his rival's daughter, unaware that she has ulterior motives.

Title: 1881. Chilappol Penkutty
Content: A woman recovers with the help of her friends after being sexually assaulted, with the incident being discussed nationally on social media.

Title: 1883. Mera Naam Joker
Content: Pradeep and Sunny, two irresponsible friends, begin a workshop after failing their exams. But they find it difficult to get ahead in life as they prefer to chase women.

Title: 1884. Payyans
Content: The film explores the relationship between a mother and a child. The central character Josy (Jayasurya) is brought up all by his mother Padma (Rohini). Josy's problems start with the return of his father (Lal).

Title: 1885. Keni: Preserving Indigenous Food Culture
Content: "Keni: Preserving Indigenous Food Culture" is a documentary film that captures the visual ethnography of the indigenous food culture and ways of life of the Mullukuruman, a scheduled tribal community who inhabits the Wayanad district of Kerala, a southern Indian state. The tribe cooks a variety of foods that extend beyond the purpose of subsistence and that which is related to life cycle rituals such as pregnancy, childbirth, puberty, marriage and death. The Mullukurumans of Wayanad have been living in the agrarian ecosystem and following their own unique socio-cultural adherences and food habits. The documentary has been conceptualized, scripted and directed by Ms Sukanya G (NIAS CSP) with research guidance from Prof Sangeetha Menon, and a group of talented film crew including State awardees.

Title: 1886. Monsoon
Content: Anas who dreams to become a Film director Meets varsha on a journey. Later they become friends. But later many problems comes. FINALLY varsha helps Anas to Solve the issues and Become his dreams come true

Title: 1887. John Paul Vaathil Thurakkunnu
Content: The movie plot revolves around a village lad who attends an interview in the city and gets drawn into a web of deceit and revenge.

Title: 1888. Ain
Content: This cinema discusses the relationship between individual and society in the background of Muslim Community in Malabar area. Maanu is one who cannot identify his belonging anywhere. Umma (mother) and sister charge him with irresponsibility and his Vavachi(grandfather) is the only one who can understand his tormenting situation. He loves the colour and smell of blood and once he comes to witness a murder, he flees because of fear. The film unravels the story about how Maanu is influenced by the characters that he comes across in life, after that incident.

Title: 1889. Oru Typical Kamukan
Content: Oru Typical Kamukan is an upcoming Indian Malayalam-language romantic thriller film directed by Suhail Shaji and produced under The Next Film Productions featuring Ijaaz Ebrahim in the lead role.

Title: 1890. Kathakali
Content: Kathakali is the traditional dance form of Kerala. In this film, Kathakali is compared with the society. There are many people who have been ejected from the society due to various reasons. Some of these people live on the shores of the Bharathapuzha River. There are people in search of wealth, old people, and physically challenged people and people orphaned by birth. Kathakali depicts the story of a young man who tries to join and create an address within the society. But he fails to do so and returns back to the river Bharatapuzha, whom he considers as his mother, so as to discard all the fabricated deceitful illustrations of the society. The film ends strongly emphasizing the old saying "Kathakali is not meant for the poor & the underprivileged". The background music for the entire movie is designed with instruments used only for Kathakali. This movie is written and directed by a young man who suffers from the perilous disease, Ankylosing spondylytis and he is 60% physically challenged. The film was also produced by differently abled men"all is well"

Title: 1891. Oru Korean Padam
Content: Kishore works as an assistant director and dreams of making him big someday in showbiz. A chance encounter with Eva changes his life forever and the man falls in love.

Title: 1893. Bada Dosth
Content: A honest Police officer join with an underworld don Geevargees/GV when there is no another option against him.But GV tries to kill him in a bomb blast

Title: 1895. Kaliyachan
Content: The only way to become a great Kathakali dancer is to follow your master. Individual excellence is nothing compared to the devotion to the Master, which the protagonist learns too late in life.

Title: 1896. Deadly Affair
Content: Deadly Affair is the story of a married man who commits a deadly mistake of cheating on his wife and the repercussions are disastrous. His lover is sexy, smart, dangerous and she stops at nothing to get what she wants.

Title: 1897. Immini Nalloraal
Content: Jeevan is a huge fan of actress Sneha and when she arrives in his village for a shoot, he thinks that they are married and kidnaps her. Ultimately they fall in love and end up married.

Title: 1898. Saigal Padukayanu
Content: The movie revolves around Chandra Babu, who has a great passion for music which he has inherited from his father.

Title: 1899. Actually
Content: Actually, the Malayalam movie centers around two different incidents. It develops through a group of characters, who in varied ways get involved in these incidents.

Title: 1900. Daivathinte Makan
Content: Sunny, an orphan, and Sonia, a rich heiress, fall in love and wish to get married. However, her father opposes this union due to the difference in their financial and social status.

Title: 1901. Akasthile Paravakal
Content: A man's life is in trouble when he gets infected with rabies. However, a ray of hope strikes through the gloom when a girl enters his life.

Title: 1902. Karma Cafe
Content: A humble man returns from his hard-working job overseas to his hometown in India to run a French Cafe located in a place that clashes with old values and contemporary mindset. He faces unforeseen obstacles every minute of the day due to his inexperience as a restaurateur, yet feels that his optimism is going to pay off in the end. The guests at the cafe bring their own struggles and levity that makes the day worthwhile for the owner and the quirky waiter. Despite the owners' optimism towards his new business, the chances of the cafe surviving another day seem very slim.

Title: 1903. Malsaram
Content: Achamkandam Thommichan's illegitimate son Hamsa resents him and constantly attacks him while he struggles to sort things out. However, an unexpected situation brings the two together.

Title: 1904. Sultan
Content: Sivarajan aka Sultan and Nishita are engaged to each other. Sivarajan comes from a poor family and Nishita from a wealthy one. Will their love last for long?

Title: 1906. Laughing Apartment Near Girinagar
Content: It tells the story of different peoples in a appartment in differrnt cituations on a harthal day

Title: 1908. Sahayathrikakku Snehapoorvam
Content: A jobless couple's relationship is tested when they both compete for the same job and face similar problems in their own families.

Title: 1909. Annum Innum Ennum
Content: A new generation movie that explores relationships and exposes the truth that no matter how committed people might seem to each other, no relationship is perfect.

Title: 1910. Janaki
Content: Janaki showcases the tumultuous life of 12 year old child, who lives in the unsafe openness of the street. Orphaned and abandoned, she goes through all the unpleasant odds until she finds abode at the Tharavad of Sekharan Master, an elderly Gandhian who treats her like his own grandchild. Janaki finds a sense of belonging in the love of Sekharan's family members and the harmony created by the innocent solidarity of children. But the outside world always hunts her down. The death of her protector throws Janaki back to the wretched realities, a life of abuse and exploitation. Janaki is the representative of dejected womanhood, hurt and humiliated.

Title: 1912. Chitrakoodam
Content: Sisters Maya and Malu struggle to make a living after the death of their father. In order to help them, their grandmother goes in search of the perfect grooms for them.

Title: 1913. Marmmajalam
Content: Marma Jalam is a 1994 Indian Tamil movie directed by Sharmili. The film stars Shakeela, Reshma, Neha, Maria, Sindhu, Sharmili, Mumtaz in lead roles. The film had musical score by Sharmili.

Title: 1914. Ponmudipuzhayorathu
Content: Bhaskaran is in love with Snehalatha and wishes to marry her. Snehalatha's father poses a condition in front of him and Bhaskaran has to complete the challenge to marry Snehalatha.

Title: 1915. Sambhu
Content: Meera, A Journalist Hhlps Shambu prove his innocence after he falsely implicated in a Bus arson Massacre case, which happened during a student Strike.

Title: 1916. Dr. Patient
Content: Dr. Ruben Isaac (Jayasurya), a psychiatrist, is loved by the patients and his unique way of handling even the most difficult mental situation is admired by his co-workers. But things go awry when his real identity is revealed.

Title: 1917. Naranathu Thamburan
Content: Ananthan falls in love with Hemalatha, a poor girl. After their marriage, complications arise when the government and his crooked relatives plan to take over the palace unless they produce a child.

Title: 1918. She Taxi
Content: A movie which portrays the role of women in fields men dominate, the movie emphasizes on woman as taxi drivers.

Title: 1921. Amrutham
Content: Gopi, a farmer, looks after his younger brother, Dinesh, a college student. Things take a turn when Gopi marries a Muslim girl.

Title: 1923. Melle
Content: Uma and her father Job live together in Kolkatta. He wants to return to his homeland. After an upsetting experience Uma meets the love of her life. Together they set off to discover their new life together .

Title: 1924. Munnariv
Content: A work-from-home Malayali IT Engineer starts hearing the voice of his daughter from the future, trying to help him change the course of the world.

Title: 1925. Moppala
Content: The life of a Theyyam exponent and his grandson, who is the child of an inter-caste marriage, is topsy-turvy due to caste hierarchy and prejudices. Devanandan, the grandson who is very much passionate about Theyyam, is not allowed to perform the art by the diehard followers of caste systems. So Devanandan leaves the scene wearing the attires and makeup of Theyyam.

Title: 1927. 24 Hrs
Content: An innocent man gets mistaken to be the killer of a mafia don's brother. The don orders the man dead in 24 hours.

Title: 1929. Black Butterfly
Content: Benny, who works at a fuel station secretly falls in love with Reena who often crosses his path. On the other side, Deepak acts like a gentleman to get close to Arathy with bad intentions. A horrendous crime will bring them all together.

Title: 1930. Roopantharam
Content: Eyes are only mere instruments, experiences stored in the mind results in seeing them.

Title: 1931. Mr. Pavanayi 99.99
Content: The movie talks about a villain's attempt to kill a girl and her lover in exchange for money.

Title: 1932. Kayamkulam Kanaran
Content: Ambitious police officer Sathyapalan tries in vain to convince Kanaran, a man with strong political connections, to help him get a promotion. However, one day, an opportunity presents itself.

Title: 1933. Sivapuram
Content: Sivan, a widower who arrives at Sivapuram village looking for a job. He has a small daughter whom he leaves in the care of a nursery teacher, while he is at work. Sivan however falls in love with his daughter's teacher soon, as he finds quite a few similarities between her and his late wife.

Title: 1935. Hello Namasthe
Content: When roommates Madhav and Jerrin bought two adjacent villas and started living with their families, they never thought that their friendship will be affected in any way.

Title: 1938. Fourth River
Content: Inspired from some true political events, Fourth River tells the story of four Naxalite revolutionaries who lived during a chaotic period of the Naxalite movement in India.

Title: 1939. Kaadakalam
Content: Kaadakalam movie speaks about the relation between a tribal boy and his father and the way he teaches his son to live in the forest and love the forest.

Title: 1940. Gaurisankaram
Content: Due to unforeseen circumstances, childhood sweethearts Gauri and Sankaran get separated. However, their bond withstands the test of time and reunites them years later.

Title: 1941. Agninakshathram
Content: Rudra, a little girl, is possessed by supernatural powers, after which she can predict the future. However, after knowing that her life is in trouble, a priest comes to her rescue.

Title: 1944. Keshu
Content: Keshu is a deaf; mute child who stays with his maternal uncle.Being quite mischievous, there are never ending complaints from the villagers.Shalini, a teacher transferred to that village stared living with the family.She encourages him to take up drawing; convinces him to go to school.When he wins an international award for his painting he becomes the darling of the whole village.

Title: 1946. Ee Snehatheerathu
Content: Viswanathan is an idealistic man who is suspicious of Gounder, an evil but kindhearted man. However, his father enjoys Gounder's company and generosity.

Title: 1947. Chila NewGen Nattuvisheshangal
Content: Vinayan, an orphan who hard works to accomplish an identity of his own. His buddy in life Smapath who for all time follow him is the only consolation in his life. Vinayan who dream of a better life has a love affair with Meenakshi, the only daughter of a well-to-do man Nair. Nair is in opposition to her daughter's affair with Vinayan. The film portrays the eventful and exciting moments in the life of Vinayan.

Title: 1948. Penpattanam
Content: Four women, who struggle to make ends meet, find INR 30 lakh and decide to keep it. However, they get in trouble when the police link the money to a murder and start investigating.

Title: 1949. Arani
Content: Arani is a Indian Malayalam film, The Story of this movie is taken from short story written by the legendary writer and director late Sri. P. Padmarajan. Pure love and fantasy is blended in the movie and is a fully packed family entertainer. The movie is blessed with a heart touching lullaby composed by Sabari , and lyrics by V. R. Santhosh.

Title: 1953. Karmayogi
Content: Rudran Gurukkal is the sole male descendant of his family and is haunted by a strange kind of destiny while events unfold around him. Based on Shakespeare's 'Hamlet'.

Title: 1954. Daivam Sakshi
Content: Iqbal returns from Kuwait in hopes of starting a small business in his hometown. He dreams of a simple life supporting his son's dream of becoming an aeronautical engineer. But a series of bad financial decisions change his fate forever.

Title: 1955. Malayali
Content: Madhavan is loved and respected by everyone in the village except his brothers who hate him. Matters get worse after his brothers try to falsely implicate him in an acquaintance's murder case.

Title: 1956. Janaadhipan
Content: Based on the life of a Chief Minister in Kerala who was pitted against an invisible foe and how everyone involved was scheming ruthlessly for their own personal gain.

Title: 1958. Happy Journey
Content: A blind cricketer pursues his dream and tries to make an Indian blind cricket team a reality.

Title: 1959. Veeralipattu
Content: Harinarayanan, a young man who works in Chennai, is in love with Pooja, the daughter of rich parents. However, he and his family are forced to bear the burden of tradition.

Title: 1962. Violin
Content: Angel who lives with her two aunts is very fond of music. When Aby enters their house as a tenant, he and Angel bond over music and although initially hesitant, Angel gives in to Aby's love.

Title: 1963. Duryodhana
Content: Following the disappearances of their loved ones, two brave-hearts - Captain Ram and a youngster named Siva Surya - set out to find them. Their investigations lead them on a journey full of peril and adventure, and trouble looms large as they step closer to the truth.

Title: 1964. SIM: Sorry I'm Mad
Content: When Iyer, a villager, goes in search of the perfect wife by using social media with the help of his friends, his life takes an unexpected turn.

Title: 1965. Njaan Salperu Raman Kutty
Content: Ramankutty, a teacher with good reputation agrees to marry his uncle's daughter. His reputation goes for a toss when he changes his mind and take interest in another cousin.

Title: 1966. Night Duty
Content: Devan is an ineffective police constable. His only son committed suicide and his wife has walked out on him.

Title: 1967. To Noora with Love
Content: Noora, a social activist, falls in love with Shajahan and marries him. However, her health condition soon begins to cause complications in her pregnancy.

Title: 1970. Aazhakadal
Content: Kunjumon returns after spending sixteen years in prison for murdering his father. Upon returning, he finds out that Paulachan was the man who had caused all his misery and the death of his father.

Title: 1971. Autorsha
Content: It deals with the problems and difficulties faced by auto drivers in Kannur when an incident took place

Title: 1972. Oomappenninu Uriyadappayyan
Content: A poor mute man and a rich deaf-mute woman fall in love and they elope as their love is not supported by the woman's family.

Title: 1973. Bibleo
Content: Bibleo is a fanatsy, psychological thriller revolving around the fights between the invisible powers which are the main cause of every action, every birth and death on the earth. Mr. Bibleo is a physics professor doing research on Death and whether at the time of death any gate opens to the next life. But an unexpected event changes his life forever. He doesn't even know that he is becoming a warrior.a warrior of the creator of the universe and saviour of every creature. Now he has only 24 hours time to do the most dangerous task anyone has ever done. That is to defeat the most powerful and beautiful angel Named 'LUCIFER'.

Title: 1974. Idiots
Content: A rich heiress enlists the help of an assassin to create the illusion that she has been murdered so she can put the blame on her boyfriend who ended the relationship with her.

Title: 1976. Last Bench
Content: Rasheed, Joshi, Samkutty and Reji are very naughty school boys who are bad in studies. Their lives take a turn for the better when a teacher tries to mend their ways.

Title: 1978. Valappottukal
Content: Jabbar, a gravedigger, decides to get his young daughter Shabnam married into a rich family. However, her teacher Sajeevan tries to oppose the match.

Title: 1979. Pianist
Content: Manu is an orphan. He spends his spare time as an album composer at Arphas Amar's (Aju Varghese) Amar Recording Studio.

Title: 1980. Athisayangalude Venal
Content: 'The Summer of Miracles' narrates a nine-year old boy's obsession to become invisible, his relentless efforts to achieve that and the consequences of his actions on people around him.

Title: 1981. Swapnasundari
Content: Shanu is a model . He gets one call in his mobile and through phones they get more closer and began to love each other .One day he start to Munnar to meet karishma. During the journey he met lot of problems from Zakaria and team.

Title: 1982. Theetta Rappai
Content: The real-life story of competitive eater Theetta Rappai from Thrissur, Kerala, who could stomach unbelievably enormous amounts of food.

Title: 1984. Heart Beats
Content: A group of spoilt friends from influential families keep troubling their college classmates. However, their lives change when a student commits suicide and they try helping a mysterious woman.

Title: 1985. Ammakkoru Tharattu
Content: Decades ago, Sulakshana and Joseph were in love. Though separated now, the past keeps haunting them and the memories never fade. How mistreatment from her children brings them back together at old age forms the crux of the story

Title: 1986. Kaana Kanmani
Content: A girl along with her parents come to a haunted mansion to celebrate holiday.slowly they understood that her daughter is caught by an evil spirit of a child they aborted

Title: 1987. Punyam Aham
Content: Narayanan lives in a small village with his mother, who separated from his Brahmin father many years ago. He sets out to discover his identity in a society dictated by caste difference.

Title: 1989. Collector
Content: Suresh Gopi, the District Collector of Cochin, has to take heads-on several kingpins who rule the underworld of Cochin. Adithya Menon, a real estate businessman, is a deadly opponent, supported by ACP Revathy and social activist Arundhati. The Lady Mayor, Mohini of Kochi Corporation also behind Rajeev. In this battle between the 'Good' and the 'Evil, Collector needs to win.

Title: 1990. Weeping Boy
Content: The film handles the subject of Anti-Abortion and it's consequences on families and the society as a whole. The story revolves around Sahadevan (Sreenivasan) who is so sensitive that anything can make him cry

Title: 1991. Bhaiyya Bhaiyya
Content: A Malayalam Comedy about togetherness and brotherhood, portraying the importance to a group of people whom we refer to as 'Bengali Babus' in our social life. Babumon (Kunchacko Boban) and Bengali Babu (Biju Menon) have a peculiar relation which dates back to the day the elder one among the two, came to Kerala. The film revolves around a journey to Bengal carrying the mortal remains of a laborer.

Title: 1992. Sarkar Colony
Content: Shivaramakrishnan is a government employee who struggles to make ends meet. In order to earn some quick money, he and his friends start a daycare center, which proves to be even more disastrous.

Title: 1993. Gemini
Content: Vijay Varma and psychologist Anusree have no children and they adopt a baby girl who is 2.5 years old. Gemini grows up as an obedient, smart girl. But drastic change is seen in her behavior and mannerisms, at a particular stage of life.

Title: 1994. Positive
Content: A group of college students form a music troupe. However, their dreams of becoming musicians come to a halt when the main singer of the troupe falls in love with a girl.

Title: 1995. The Divine Touch
Content: The film exposes the conflicts of an academically trained film maker who confronts with certain realities. The film highlights the values of Motherhood above everything else. Devasparsam( The Divine Touch)highlights the fact that the agony of a Film maker makes him matured in the medium.

Title: 1997. Rameshan Oru Peralla
Content: Rameshan is a kind man who never backs out when a fellow human being is in need of help. On the day he begins his new career as a taxi driver, a group of college students board his cab, leading to unexpected consequences, in his life.

Title: 1998. Prakashante Metro
Content: The life of a happy-go-lucky auto driver named Prakashan, which unfolds during his journey from Vytila to Aluva along with a young indigent girl.

Title: 2000. Poppins
Content: An adaptation of the Sahitya Akademi award-winning play 8 Natakangal by Jayaprakash Kuloor. It is centered on man-woman relationships, exploring different aspects of the institution called marriage.

Title: ﻿2001. Thalamelam
Content: A doctor decides to demolish his psychiatric hospital with an aim to start a resort. Later, he struggles to look after his patients, Krishnan and Gopalan.

Title: 2002. Hareendran Oru Nishkalankan?
Content: Hareendran, a software tycoon, runs a successful company with his right-hand man and childhood friend, GK. However, things take an unexpected turn for Hareendran as GK turns out to be a cunning crook.

Title: 2003. Athmakadha
Content: A film about the blind but content father instilling courage in his daughter in the face is oncoming blindness.

Title: 2004. 8½Intercuts- Life and Films of K G George
Content: A documentary on the life and films of veteran filmmaker KG george

Title: 2005. On the Road
Content: On the occasion of their wedding anniversary, a couple embarks on a secluded road trip in Ladakh. However, when the wife's ex-boyfriend appears out of nowhere, he unleashes a series of chaotic events that none of them can control.

Title: 2006. Kisan
Content: Velu, a peasant, teams up with his childhood friend Devan to defeat the evil feudal lord, Balaraman (Devan's Uncle) in a football match to regain his community's rights to work on a farmland.

Title: 2008. Great Depression
Content: A day in the lives of three friends presented over five distinct chapters set from dawn to dusk. They set forth on a journey of emotions, revealing the different shades of human nature and answering life's deepest secrets while not forgetting to celebrate life despite all its chaos. However, death was coming for them and their world, and it wouldn't be just another ordinary day in their lives.

Title: 2010. Kangaroo
Content: A heart-wrenching tale of a man played by Prithviraj, who must find the father of the child he raised as his own.

Title: 2011. Orange Valley
Content: Set in the wilderness of Munnar, depicts the plight of the tea plantation workers, their rebellion under the communist leadership, the consequent trade union strikes of the 90's and the incursion of the revolutionary Naxalite movement.

Title: 2012. Pachakallam
Content: Abhi and Aparna get married against her parents' wish. Their lives turn upside down when Aparna, who is hearing impaired, goes missing.

Title: 2013. Melvilasam Sariyanu
Content: Menon is crazy about art and music and promotes all talented artists. Pushkaran comes to Menon's house and stays with him claiming to be a tabla player. But he has other intentions.

Title: 2015. Tanthra
Content: Kiran wants to make a documentary on tantric practices and pursues Swethamukhi to accompany him to Kerala. When they meet Suryadharman, they discover that Swethamukhi is haunted by an evil spirit.

Title: 2016. Sarkar Dada
Content: After convicted to a murder Mukundan an heir of rich family gets released from prison just to know that all of his belongings are under the control of state government.

Title: 2017. Narendran Makan Jayakanthan Vaka
Content: A man (K Boban) returns to his native village to claim his father's property. But his time in the village is complicated by his parents relatives and friends.

Title: 2019. A Sunday
Content: Events happening in one single day, a Sunday, in the life of two couples who're in extramarital affairs.

Title: 2023. Devayaanam
Content: The movie is an attempt to portray the life of a widow who is obsessed with thanatophobia, the persistent fear of one's own death.

Title: 2024. Chembai: My Discovery of a Legend
Content: The village of Chembai was found to be entirely musically gifted and even a layman enjoyed a classical Karnatic music performance, just as a trained individual would. This quality was found to be attributed to the real gem of the villages Kottai and Chembai, Padma Bhushan Chembai, the Karnatic classical singer who wasn't merely an artiste, but was the man who valued the power of knowledge and music above all. This film is a collection of anecdotes recollected by the disciples of Chembai, an attempt made by the filmmaker to learn about the man who has been the key inspiration behind the Chembai Parthasarathy Music Festival that has been going on for over 100 years now.

Title: 2027. Josettante Hero
Content: Sajan Malyath, the still photographer of a movie, is impressive enough for Josettan, a senior film producer, to consider him as the main protagonist of the movie.

Title: 2028. Seetha Kalyanam
Content: Nimisha realises that she is in love with Sreeni, a colleague she made fun of with her friends. However, Sreeni's mother fixes his marriage with Abhirami, a traditional young lady.

Title: 2029. Priyapettavar
Content: The film revolves around the life of NRI Gopinatha Menon, who returns to his ancestral home and manages to find his roots again.

Title: 2031. Avan Chandiyude Makan
Content: Chandy, an adamant, unsocial father of a Christian family that lives in Central Travancore, is against the new thinking of the new generation in the family.

Title: 2032. Kaviyude Osyath
Content: An estranged late poet leaves behind property in his will for a young man named Abhijith. This leads Abhijith and his family to question the relationship the late poet had with them.

Title: 2034. Onnaman
Content: Ravishankar (Mohanlal) takes over the underworld empire left by his boss/father figure , Bava when he gets killed and helps the poor and needy. He becomes their leader or the "Onnaman" but in the process creates a lot of enemies.

Title: 2037. My Lucky Number is Black
Content: Film featuring the abused, abandoned and isolated childhood stories of a father, two girls, and three men through their childhood memories and moments of terrorist attacks, communal riots, abuse and rape which separated and scattered them from the humane and peaceful life.

Title: 2039. Akkaldhamayile Pennu
Content: Movie narrates the story of three generations of women who have lived in Akkaldama, protagonist Xavi's wife Anges, her daughter Maria and granddaughter - who are the representatives of the times they grew up in.

Title: 2040. Mathai Kuzhappakkaranalla
Content: Mathai (Jayasurya) is an innocent auto driver who unnecessarily interferes into the problems of others with a good intention of solving them. The story is happening on a strike day, when Mathai came to meet his fiancée Bhama. The story revolves around a series of incidents when he tries to solve the problems between Dr. Nandakumar (Mukesh) and his wife Geeta (Lakshmi Gopalaswamy)

Title: 2041. Mathilukal-Love in the time of Corona
Content: The film portrays the loneliness of a failed writer got back home from overseas during the period of pandemic.

Title: 2042. Backpack
Content: The love saga follows two youngsters, Khalil and Daya, who are diagnosed with cancer and with only months to live on earth. Their pallid state brings them together and they fall in love.

Title: 2044. Sundara Purushan
Content: A girl with intellectual disabilities falls in love with a married singer and marries him. Her father poisons his mind against his first wife so that the groom leaves her.

Title: 2045. Snehithan

Some Hindus who are religious fanatics take revenge upon Khader. In return, some fanatical Muslims take steps to retaliate upon Hindus. The sane and peaceful people in both communities become helpless. Mansoor's perception too changes. The money gifted to Mansoor, reading under proverty, by Muslim fanatics is a big lure. Subaida turns panicky and aggrieved upon Mansoor's change of mind. Khader dies in the aftermath of injuries he sustained, With this, the flame of vengeance is stocked bringht in the minds of Muslim fanatics. Subair who was a perpetrator of this attack tries to seek refuge at Subaida's house. But she throws him out. Upon hearing this, Mansoor is furious. He leaves home with a big mission on his shoulders. Subaida comes upon the weapons and fanatical leaflets Mansoor has stored in the cupboard. She turns them over to police. Consequently,the mother is facing the great trial in her life. This is the story, of a daughter and her father who lived for each other, the present generation should learn from. Leaving behind her part-time job and higher studies abroad, Lorraine returns home to take care of her sick 70 year old father Rosario who suffered from dementia. It wasn't easy to understand the frequency and severity of the disease., but with the love and care Rosario was able to regain his memory to a certain extent. Unable to bear his beloved daughter' s life revolving around his sickbed, deep guilt consumed him and decided to take his own life. ..a suicide; he gave himself up to the sea. Lorraine failed to notice him regaining his memories . The thought of her being ignorant of her father's condition gave her sleepless nights. Lorraine thought that from her telephone conversations he must have heard her speaking of her dreams and ambitions , felt guilty and left her. This movie speaks of Lorraine's life and her precious memories she has of her father.
