Content: It is a hundred years since Charlie Chaplin,artist nonpareil,appeared on the silver screen mesmerizing audiences across the globe.His signature mustache and derby hat have left their indelible imprint on the annals of film history.Buddha and Chaplin smile is a film that pays homage to Chaplin at the centennial commemoration of his acting career.The film portrays an Indian comedian Indraguptan,who idolized Chaplin.He believes his life resembles Chaplin and nurtures the desire to depict his hero on the big screen.However,he rules out a blind imitation of the late legend.The narrative revolves around his comic wisdom and quest for true love.The dilemma that ensues is the crux of the story.

Title: 2216. Ideal Couple
Content: Sophy and her husband Nambiar win as the best couple on a reality TV show. But Aashaan, an ex-burglar and his team, make a plan to loot them of the prize money.

Title: 2219. Run Kalyani
Content: A gently beguiling debut feature fiction from Geetha J. A poetic and realist drama about duties, dreams and desires that draws you into the world of Kalyani. Kalyani is a young cook who lives with her ailing aunt and a young man in a rundown agraharam in Trivandrum. Each day is the same as she carries on with her life of duty as a cook and carer. But each day is not the same too. As the romance of poetry ignites a passion, as the stories of other worlds stirs a desire, as sharks close in and death draws near, Run Kalyani builds into an intense crescendo of grief and grit, sorrow and strength.

Title: 2223. Mullassery Madhavan Kutty Nemom P. O.
2225. Alif
Content: The four generations of women in the film are identical sufferers, and when two of them rise in revolt, it speaks for millions of women out there, from all castes and creeds, who will be subjected to a lifetime of desolation and gloom.

Title: 2226. Puthooramputhri Unniyarcha
Content: Unniyarcha proves to be equal to her brother and cousin, both renowned warriors. When her cousin betrays her brother during a duel, Unniyarcha vows to take revenge.

Title: 2227. Sooryan
Content: Son of a famous singer get entangled in a series of crimes.

Title: 2229. Mizhi Thurakku
Content: A Malayalam romantic melodrama directed by Santhosh Souparnika.

Title: 2230. Tourist Home
Content: Ten rooms of a vacation home are checked in by different tourists. After staying there, the lives of the travelers change in unprecedented ways.

Title: 2231. Appooppanthaadi
Content: The film depicts the difference between the life and freedom of children in the present and the past.

Title: 2233. Greetings
Content: Gopan falls in love with Sheethal who moves in upstairs. But Sheethal has other plans on her mind , like trying to reunite the separated couple of Rangaswami Iyengar and Kasthuri.

Title: 2236. Makkana
Content: An orthodox couple has a fit of anger when their daughter flees and marries a man from another religion. The two are conflicted between the love for their daughter and their deep-rooted religious faith.

Title: 2238. Bhadra
Content: Subhadra and her fiance, Jayadevan are killed by a sinister politician, Sebastian Joseph. The vengeful ghost of Subhadra kills Sebastian in retaliation and vows to destroy his entire family.

Title: 2239. Sayahnam
Content: An old man takes pride in his country's progressive scientific temper but disapproves of its experiments with nuclear technology. His ideology is opposed by his son who is a nuclear scientist.

Title: 2240. Deepangal Sakshi
Content: Rishi, a loyal collector works for the welfare of the people. But, he is in trouble when evil politicians and businessmen plot against him.

Title: 2241. Mumbaai Taxi
Content: A group of Police Officers get information that a bomb is going to explode in Mumbai city. Will they be able to save the lives of innocent people?

Title: 2242. Thank You Very Much
Content: Achyut Shankar, a plus two student, wants to be a cricketer, but his father has already chalked out a career in medicine for him. While fighting parental pressure from his strict parents, this young boy gets involved in an incident.

Title: 2244. Omega.exe
Content: A movie about the relationship between 3 software engineers, Sidharth, Avinash and Nishchal. Avinash, unexpectedly reaches Kerala and bonds more with family of Sidharth. With the passage of time, some secrets were disclosed to the them.

Title: 2245. Kanne Madanguka
Content: After an accident, Bhagyanathan's family faces a surprising turn when Karunya's Gulf job reveals a shocking secret. Now, he must confront the painful truth about his dreams for his daughters.

Title: 2246. Neythukaran
Content: It tells the story of a weaver, a supporter of E. M. S. Namboodiripad, who dies the day after his leader dies.

Title: 2247. La Sa Gu
Content: A small government school in a Kerala district experiences a sudden change in its students and teachers as mysterious questions about specific students appear in different spots of the school.

Title: 2252. Pakal
Content: The story revolves around a young and energetic TV reporter Nandakumar, who live up to his ideals and commitments to the society.

Title: 2253. Sukhamayirikkatte
Content: Ravunni Mash is an affable person. He is so concerned about his daughter Sreelakshmi. But when Sreelakshmi grows up, his dreams are shattered. Movie deals with the issues that arise in the lives of people due to different religious beliefs.

Title: 2258. Aval
Content: Aval authentically portrays Prabha's life with a hearing challenge, inspired by a real-life character, resonating with genuine emotion and depth.

Title: 2259. Ekan
Content: A gravedigger detested by the parish. When he falls in love with his childhood flame, all hell breaks loose in the wake of furious opposition from her father.

Title: 2260. Theruvu Nakshatrangal
Content: A young orphan boy, Muthukrishan, manages to escape from a powerful begging mafia. After striving hard for years, he becomes the district collector. The movie shows the plights and hardships Muthukrishnan had to face in his journey and how he, as a collector, helps fellow orphans to escape from the hands of the begging mafia.

Title: 2261. Papas
Content: Lonan's slippers have seen its end, thanks to the wear and tear it has borne over the years. And his father Lazer, a drunkard, is always "too poor" to be able to buy him a new pair.

Title: 2263. Shadow Man
Content: Indian horror-thriller about a trapped man.

Title: 2267. Neelima Nalla Kuttiyanu vs. Chiranjeevi IPS
2269. Kumaranellurile Kulangal
Content: M. Tyude Kumaranellurile Kulangal' traces the journey back home of Jnanpith award winner M.T. Vasudevan Nair. It looks at the pathetic state of his favorite river the Nila, about which the writer has nostalgic childhood memories.

Title: 2270. Bhavum
Content: BHAVUM, winner of the Best Film Award at the 2002 Kerala State Film Awards, captures the struggle of consciousness of a young urban couple upon the arrival of the wife's mysterious sister. Their struggle, seeking to reconcile their desires with various realities and truths, results in the gradual deterioration of their relationship. Their evolving relationship plays out as a metaphor for a society that is growing apart intellectually and emotionally in an environment where the effects of globalization # mainly manifesting in avid consumerism - and the influence of media as a tool for proliferating propaganda have taken root. This irreconcilable wedge precipitates in the gradual disintegration of relationships inevitably resulting in degradation and chaos.

Title: 2271. Orange
Content: Yakobi, a lorry driver, leads a happy life with his wife and daughter. Everything in his life is hunky-dory until his old friend lands on his doorstep.

Title: 2274. Aana Mayil Ottakam
Content: An anthology narrating three unrelated short stories.

Title: 2278. Vakathirivu
Content: The story revolves around certain interesting incidents in the life of an engineering student named Vivek.

Title: 2279. Eval Gopika
Content: A Mumbai based family fixes their daughter's marriage but she realises that the bridegroom is a terrorist. She escapes with her friend Vishnu, but will she be able to survive?

Title: 2282. Kottaram Vaidyan
Content: Bhageerathan is a renowned Ayurvedic doctor in a village. He is in for a shock when he learns that according to his daughter's horoscope her husband will have an unnatural death.

Title: 2283. Ajantha
Content: Ajantha is a 2012 Tamil-language Indianfeature film produced and directed by Rajppa Ravishankar. The film was simultaneously shot in Telugu, Kannada and Malayalamlanguages too with different starcast. In this film, Vinu Mohan / Ramana plays an upcoming musician. After finishing a recording, he is on his way home when he sees an artist creating art on the street and he is stricken with awe. Onlookers are giving the artist a few rupees each but not as much as the artist expected. At this point, it begins to rain and the drawing begins to dissolve as the onlookers disperse. Vinu Mohan / Ramana hands over his entire 'bata' for the day to the artist.

Title: 2285. Isaac Newton S/O Philipose
Content: Isaac is given the condition that he can only marry his girlfriend, Annie, if he passes his SSLC exams. However, things take a turn when another man sets his eyes on Annie.

Title: 2287. Vasanthamaalika
Content: Balakrishnan, a bank employee, tries all possible ways to earn money to buy his family house. He puts himself in trouble when he stays for free in a haunted house to make money.

Title: 2288. Mottitta Mullakal
Content: Mottitta Mullakal is a Malayalam movie starring Joy Mathew and Bijukuttan in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Vinodh Kannol.dra

Title: 2289. Patterns of life: Prana
Content: Patterns of Life - Prana talks about the food habits , cultivation, art form, festivals, beliefs and how the indigenous tribes of western ghats are embracing nature and landscape.

Title: 2290. Changathipoocha
Content: Brothers Sreedharan and Raman are feuding over their ancestral properties. Raman tries to amass all the wealth by making Sreedharan's daughter fall in love with a hired lover.

Title: 2297. Adholokam
Content: A boy starts a journey to find the man who killed his father. He meets the assassin who lives in a forest and befriends him. The assassin eventually develops a brotherly love for the boy. The boy enjoys being his apprentice as a hunter. Their life in the forest becomes more exciting and eventful as there is a special task force entering the killer's abode to eliminate him.

Title: 2298. Mud Maza
Content: it is the first Romantic Sports Musical Entertainerin Malayalam film industry. The film Mud Maza presents a novel experience to the mainstream Malayalam cinema with its theme centred on children and a fresh track of treating it with aptly cast artistes. As the title suggests, the film is on the Malayali juvenile celebration of the game of football - game in the mud - duly integrated with the political undercurrents on the political grounds. The purely idyllic setting in the lap of edenic beauty, spiced with their spirited games, petty quarrels, secret crushes and expressed affairs, life takes a poetic poise in the film. This work will definitely enthrall both the children as well as the grown ups.

Title: 2299. Punaradhivasam
Content: Lack of love sours the relationship between a father and his son. A similar fate is also met by a couple who do not love each other.

Title: 2302. Smart City
Content: Shekharan is a noble gangster and his trusted henchman is Madhvan. When the Kotturan brothers try to plot against Shekharan, Madhavan strives to save his employer from their evil intentions.

Title: 2303. Videsi Nair Swadesi Nair
Content: Vindhyan always reminisces about his childhood infatuation with Neelima who currently resides in America. However, to his discontent, she is in love with another man, Shivpal.

Title: 2305. Saphalam
Content: A story portraying the ardent love of an elderly couple, who hardly withstand their separation, when the wife goes to the United States to help her daughter-in-law.

Title: 2307. Cheriya Kallanum Valiya Policum
Content: Sadasivan comes across a house where the owner, Kumaran, has committed suicide to protect his wife, Soumini. However, what is even stranger is that a man who is visually challenged is always around.

Title: 2308. 21 Months of Hell
Content: In June 25th 1975, Prime Minister of India, Indira Gandhi declared Emergency on the nation which bestowed her the authority to rule by decree, allowing elections to be suspended and civil liberties to be curbed. This resulted in the mass arrests of leaders and activists of opposition who she saw as a threat to her political life. With the introduction of the new law MISA(Maintenance of Internal Security Act), anyone could be arrested without fair trial or evidences. Making use of the political atmosphere and direct orders from the government, the police department exercised their aggression at free will. For the pro-democracy activists, India became a literal hell from the day of declaration of the Emergency until its withdrawal 21 months later. The documentary '21 Months of Hell' explores the ingenious torture method administered by the Police for intimidating political prisoners at that time. With the real life accounts of surviving victims of the torture, the documentary also features reenactments of the torture methods of the Emergency. It also investigates the methodology, immediate effects and long term medical effects of various tortures methods.

Title: 2309. Chasing Days
Content: Jayaraj, a dedicated and skilled police officer, is relentlessly pursuing Sugathan, a notorious criminal who managed to escape from jail. Sugathan's criminal history is marred with violence and he poses a significant threat to innocent lives. As Jayaraj races against time to apprehend Sugathan, the criminal cunningly evades capture at every turn.

Title: 2310. 72 Model
Content: The film moves around the life of a youth named Sajan (Govind Padmasurya) who stumbles upon a fortune in his old-model ambassador car and the stage is set for some unpredictable incidents in his life.

Title: 2313. Mahassar
Content: Mahassar is a crime thriller based feature that goes on a emotional roller-coaster ride with the protagonist and the hunt for a killer.

Title: 2316. Onnumariyathe
Content:
Onnumariyathe (Unknowingly) Synopsis

A middle class family in a village growing into a town. Suku is the Family head. His wife is an extravagant Snobbish Lady. They have two children, a girl of 13 years and a 7 year old boy. Suku earns his living by electrical plumbing work. He struggles much to find income for day-to-day living and goes through much mental agony to fill his purse. Jaleel and Sivan, two of his friends help him to a certain extent in his struggle. He faces family problems due to his migrant labourer Ganeshan, as Suku was not able to understand Ganeshan's intentions. Unexpectedly Suku becomes ill and require an operation. But his wife does not understand his problem or his hard work to up bring the family. She is only concerned about the money in his purse. The climax of the film is the realization of the facts by Manju, his wife. But a bit late.

Onnumariyathe (Unknowingly) Synopsis

A middle class family in a village growing into a town. Suku is the Family head. His wife is an extravagant Snobbish Lady. They have two children, a girl of 13 years and a 7 year old boy. Suku earns his living by electrical plumbing work. He struggles much to find income for day-to-day living and goes through much mental agony to fill his purse. Jaleel and Sivan, two of his friends help him to a certain extent in his struggle. He faces family problems due to his migrant labourer Ganeshan, as Suku was not able to understand Ganeshan's intentions. Unexpectedly Suku becomes ill and require an operation. But his wife does not understand his problem or his hard work to up bring the family. She is only concerned about the money in his purse. The climax of the film is the realization of the facts by Manju, his wife. But a bit late.

Title: 2318. Camel Safari
Content: Its story of a group of friends and a girl feels crush on one of them.

Title: 2319. The Guard
Content: The story in a nutshell is how a poor man, Appukuttan Nair (Kalabhavan Mani) gets a job as a forest guard. His first appointment is in a lonely, isolated dense forest. His predecessor there was one Thomachan, who was supposedly trampled to death by a tusker. Anyhow, Appukuttan takes charge and in the dense forest he is left all alone, save the innumerable animals and birds around him and the frightening sounds of the jungle. But life in the jungle teaches him many things about men and human society and he gets a new perspective to look at things.

Title: 2320. Kanneerinum Madhuram
Content: Kanneerinum Madhuram tells the agonies of a young guy treated to be mad. Krishnanunni becomes alone after he recovers from madness. The story develops when he realizes he is a burden.

Title: 2321. Krishna Kripasagram
Content: Challenging life of an Indian Air Force officer torn between his love for family and his duty towards the nation.

Title: 2323. Vellakkarante Kamuki
Content: Tutu or Tovin Padmanabhan is a Btech candidate. He is a full time alcoholic and today he is a headache for the family and the locals. Mum and dad want to see him have a good life.

Title: 2324. Bharathapuzha
Content: Bharathapuzha is about the lives and struggles of Sugandhi, someone who had kept the doors to the outside world wide open, where and in which she seeks freedom. She enacts several lives in one, yet struggles to find a place of her own in the world of men. She is a river that flows despite everything, and takes in everything in its ebbs and tides. Bharathapuzha is also about the city of Thrissur, the city of cultural expressions, festivities and tiger dance.

Title: 2325. Kadhayile Nayika
Content: Nandini (Urvashi) is a widow running her household on a paltry salary. She also works as a part-time marriage broker and hopes that her brother Siva (Kalabhavan Prajodh) will someday realize his dream of becoming an actor. Shiva anchors an evening show on a local TV channel and often doesn't have enough callers for his phone-in program. Things get complicated when a girl who rings up Shiva is murdered--during the call. Her friend Archana (Roma), the only witness to the murder, seeks Shivas help to bring the culprits before the law.

Title: 2328. Zahir
Content: Woman is an essential part in all walks of life. The trumpet of woman empowerment resounds in all corners of the nation. But no one can hide the social reality that she is still insecure and apprehensive in our world. There emerges a parallel stream of society that considers feminine body as an entity just to satisfy carnal instincts. Here girl is not the only one who is tortured, a small community surrounding her is also being tormented and they are not at all liberated from this predicament. It is the theme that becomes the core of 'Zahir's' content.

Title: 2332. Kerala Paradiso
Content: Five movie buffs racing against time, trying to save the only theatre in the village from being locked down.

Title: 2333. Mazhavillinattam Vare
Content: The life-changing journey of a young Pakistani cricketer and a college student who is an ardent admirer of him.

Title: 2335. Atar Mass 2019
Content: THIS IS A ADVENTURE ACTION COMBINES ROMANTIC REVENGES AND SPACE JOURNEYS AND HIGH (3D) GRAPHICS THAT WILL BLOW YOUR MIND.

Title: 2336. Thakarachenda
Content: The film focuses on a group of slum dwellers who are ignored in the ambitious blueprints of city developers. Slum dweller Chakrapani (Sreenivasan), a disabled beggar, is a small-time moneylender. A drunkard, he spends most of the time quarreling with his mother. He has an eye on Latha (Geethu Mohandas) who lives nearby with her two children though she detests him. Latha, an asthmatic, works as a maid and dreams of a better future for her children. Another woman Vasanthi (Seema G. Nair) also lives in the slum with her two children and a drunkard husband (Manikandan) who keeps on causing endless trouble to her and her children. Meanwhile, the government takes steps to get rid of the slum in order to go on with developmental activities and the slum-dwellers find that they have nowhere to go. Finally, desperation forces Chakrapani and Latha to unite and raise their voice in protest again the ignorance towards their slum.

Title: 2338. Cheriya Cheriya Valiya Karyangal
Content: Release Date-15 November 2019

Title: 2339. Paranju Theeratha Visheshangal
Content: Rajeev and Vijayalakshmi get divorced for petty reasons. However, they realize their love for each other when they are forced to remarry.

Title: 2341. Crocodile Love Story
Content: A Love story being a complete entertainer when a crocodile gets into it. Will be a must watch entertainer.

Title: 2343. Puzhayamma
Content: Puzhayamma is a movie about a friendship between 13 year old 'mazha' and an American journalist Rossa Linda. This kid love river and lives in a Chinese net base and suddenly some unexpected incidents came across.

Title: 2345. One Day
Content: This is a crime investigation story about a missing child.

Title: 2349. Utharaswayamvaram
Content: After a lot of struggles, Prakashan marries his dream girl Uthara. But their marriage doesn't last even for a day, resulting in a major clash between their families.

Title: 2350. Therottam
Content: Sanju, Shiva, Nelson, and Appunny's friendship stands true to the test of time when they all go out of their ways to help Shiva's sister Shivani, who gets caught in an unfortunate incident.

Title: 2351. Lessons
Content: Anthology film showcasing four stories based on loneliness, arrogance, helplessness, and accomplishment. Each slice-of-life story provides a thought-provoking lesson from life.

Title: 2352. Pranyamanithooval
Content: Meera is all set to marry Vinod, but he meets with an accident and dies. Their friend Balu, who loves Meera, becomes a closer aide to her. Eventually Balu and Meera fall in love.

Title: 2355. Swantham Bharya Zindabad
Content: Vettoor Sivankutty marries a beautiful girl who is against his communist ideals. Problems arise between the two when an actor visits their village for a film shooting.

Title: 2360. Karayilekku Oru Kadal Dooram
Content: Anoop Chandran, a famous writer. Prone to seeing future events that turn out to be real, Anoop one days sees his own death in a trance. He decides to write one final novel before death comes visiting.

Title: 2362. Kadha, Samvidhanam Kunchakko
Content: Kunchacko is a millionaire who achieves success through all the wrong ways. When he decides to mend his ways, he realizes that the journey is not as easy as it seems.

Title: 2364. Govindankutty Thirakkilanu
Content: Govindankutty faces several obstacles after he inherits an ancestral property which often results in hilarious situations.

Title: 2367. Green Leaves Yellow Flowers
Content: Kannan is a tribal boy who is a student of a government school near a jungle. He walks to the school daily through the tedious path of the jungle. His pompous classmate, Adityan keeps distance with Kannan. Kannan often becomes the laughingstock of the class. One evening after class, Adityan enquires Kannan whether there is a cave in the jungle on his way to school. When Kannan tells him that there is indeed a cave Adityan expresses his interest to find the treasure left in it by the infamous bandit Rajappan. Although Kannan tried to oppose Adityan's quest at first, he was pursued by the arrogant Adityan. On his quest for treasure through the jungle, Adityan has life-altering adventure.

Title: 2368. Woman with A Movie Camera
Content: A young woman carrying out her own little adventure by documenting her immediate surroundings to further reveal the elemental plights of being.

Title: 2370. Red Shadow
Content: Fourteen year old Daliya and his football coach Anto go missing from the Illikunnu village. Police and locals suspect that Dalia was taken by Anto wearing a mask.

Title: 2371. Swayam: Selfless
Content: The Film outlines the Story of a Mother and her austistic child, revolves around several unpleasant and happy situations.

Title: 2375. Velutha Madhuram
Content: The film Velutha Madhuram has to spreading a positive message and speaking out against the horrible activities of drug gangs that are destroying the lives of young people, Velutha Madhuram has proven to be a competent entertainer.

Title: 2379. Ekantham
Content: Estranged brothers brought together by loneliness.

Title: 2384. Dae! Ingottu nokkiye...
Content: Vettikadu Sivan admires the good deeds of his uncle Sadashivan, who is the Chief Minister of the state. But when he comes to know his true nature, he sets out to destroy his political career.

Title: 2385. Kalippaattakkaaran: Toy Maker
Content: A young toy maker tries to make sense of the impermanence of life that he has been forced to acknowledge through experiences of separation and death.

Title: 2388. Kadhantharam
Content: Rajaram, a writer and an orator has been fondling a dream around his son Sidharth. While the father is ensconced in these thoughts, the son Sidharth perceives such thoughts to be selfish and imprudent and dismisses them with contempt.

Title: 2389. Durga
Content: Durga is a percocious, but peace-loving, college student. He has a group of friends, who he hangs around with. He meets with Gayetri, and falls in love with her. She also seems attracted to him. When they meet at the bus stop, Gayetri refuses to recognize him, and he gets arrested. After his interrogation, he is released, and hates Gayetri and will not have anything to do with her. When he finds out the reason behind Gayetri's refusal to recognize him, both reconcile their differences, and decide to get married. Gayetri's dad, Shivaji Rao, who is a Manager with the local Cinema Hall, does not like Durga, and wants Gayetri to marry someone else, which Gayetri does not agree to. In desperation, Shivaji turns for help to a local gangster and asks him to kill Durga. What Shivaji does not know is Durga is the only son of notorious gangster and criminal don, Ramdas, who will not spare anyone who will even dare to think about harming his son.

Title: 2390. Chinna Dada
Content: Chinna Dada is a revenge thriller.

Title: 2391. Maharaja Talkies
Content: Vimala and her three sisters run a theatre called Maharaja Talkies. They get in trouble when Pappachan, a rich man, forces Vimala to shut down the theatre.

Title: 2395. Dry
Content: Dry chronicles the life of an alcoholic youth and how he struggles to find a job so as to sustain his lifestyle in the city. His mother's love and his goals seem lost when it comes to his affinity for the bottle. Based around the time when Kerala government had banned the sale of alcohol in the state, this movie shows his reciprocal behavior and how he goes about in satiating his obsession. This movie further mirrors the current situations of the youth in Kerala with regards to their afflictions, job hunt experiences and other cultural fallacies.

Title: 2396. Sahapadi 1975
Content: Sahapadi 1975 is an interesting campus love story set against the backdrop of politics

Title: 2400. My Mother's Laptop
Content: Ravi a world-renowned artist in Calcutta who wants to reunite with his mother but is guilty about the way he feels about her.

Title: 2401. Kapila
Content: Sanju Surendran composes a dreamlike and abstract portrait, focusing on the sensorial universe of a hyper-contemporary vestal committed to three thousand-year-old practice.

Title: 2404. Nakshathrangal
Content: Nakshathrangal revolves around a Brahmin family and their customs. The story is filled with twists and turns. How a young boy deals with the problems he faces after his father is paralyzed.The heart-whelming story of a father-son relation shows how the son takes over his father's job.

Title: 2405. Pixelia
Content: A film about Realization and Acceptance. Kumar, a bachelor in his thirties leaves his corporate job in Kochi to become a graphic novelist. He embarks on a new life as an Uber driver in Kochi while working on his graphic novel titled 'Pixelia'. One day a transgender named Mandakini gets into his cab and that day changes Kumar's life forever. Gradually a bonding ensues between Kumar and Mandakini making Kumar realize and come to terms with his queer identity. As they start their new relationship, Kumar gets into deeper conflicts regarding adopting a child, as adoption by queer parents is realistically difficult in a country like India.

Title: 2406. 18 Feet
Content: 18 feet symbolizes the holy distance dalits, the downtrodden, were to ensure for the sanctity of upper castes.

Title: 2409. Crayons
Content: Families from two different socio-economic classes are compared in this movie about childhood and parenting best practices.

Title: 2416. Utharam Parayaathe
Content: The story goes through the lives of two scientists. The story revolves around the memories of a senior scientist who lived the life of a normal person. The story develops through the memories that pass through the son.

Title: 2417. Vellivelichathil
Content: The Plot revolves around the life of Upendran played by John Brittas who falls in love with and wishes to marry a bar dancer, played by Iniya. The lives of NRI Malayalees are portrayed by the other characters in the movie, depicting their daily struggles.

Title: 2418. Ente Hridayathinte Udama
Content: Uma, who works as a teacher, falls in love with Pavithran, a political activist. Tragedy strikes when Pavithran is murdered by his own party men for trying to abolish corruption.

Title: 2419. Ee Nadu Innale Vare
Content: Plappalli Sreedharan, an honest politician, must fight those he thinks are his own, in order to make the truth triumph.

Title: 2420. Pulivaal Pattanam
Content: Veeran, Vasu, Vinu and James are villagers who lead a carefree life. They face many struggles as they go in search of a job in a new city.

Title: 2421. Nayinte hrudayam
Content: In the enigmatic world of "Heart of a Dog," where the boundaries of ethics blur and the unforeseen collides with the realm of possibility, Professor Isac, a controversial eugenicist, embarks on a trans-formative journey. Against the backdrop of a gritty urban landscape, Isac, with a determined gaze, performs a transplantation surgery that defies conventional norms. A street dog becomes the vessel for an organ harvested from a diligent worker, intertwining the destinies of two disparate beings. As the cinematic lens delves into the repercussions of this audacious experiment, Isac finds himself negotiating the uncharted territories of morality and consequence. The once unassuming street dog undergoes a metamorphosis, transcending its canine essence to become a hybrid creature-a dog man. Undeterred by the unexpected outcome, Professor Isac embraces the challenge of adapting to this extraordinary creation. In a clandestine dance with bureaucracy, he masterfully forges documents, bestowing upon the creature the name Vivek. The creature, now more son than experiment, walks the tightrope between humanity and the primal instincts of its former self. "Heart of a Dog" unfolds as a mesmerizing tapestry of stylized visuals and thought-provoking narrative, inviting audiences to question the boundaries of science, morality, and the essence of identity. In this daring cinematic exploration, the blurred lines between man and beast, ethics and experimentation, converge to create a hauntingly beautiful and unsettling tale.

Title: 2429. Nirakazcha
Content: A foreigner comes to the Indian state of Kerala to satisfy his wish of recreating a celebrated maestros paintings and he falls in love with the model that he hired. A tourism oriented film for the southern state.

Title: 2431. Raman

Title: 2435. Ennu Sakshal Daivam

Title: 2436. Fiction
Content: The fine line between fact and fiction is blurred as Kiren, a young writer attempts to spin a yarn out of a true story. He soon realises that, sometimes the truth deserves to be left untouched.

Title: 2438. Padmini
Content: 'Padmini' is a biopic on the life and times of T.K. Padmini, touted as a prospect of Indian art in the 1960s.

Title: 2439. Chila Sankethika Kaaranangalal
Content: Chila Sankethika Kaaranangalal is a Independent Experimental Social Satire Malayalam Film Directed by S.S. Jishnu Dev under the banner of Independent Cinema Box. This is a 78 minutes length experimental feature film only shot inside a car.

Title: 2443. Shakthan Market
Content: A fishmonger at the Shaktan Market in Thrissur, Abdukka leads a contented life with his son Shameer and his adopted son Muthu. Things spiral into a crisis when their sworn enemies Cherookadan and Jose start plotting Abdukka's downfall.

Title: 2445. Sreehalli
Content: Movie is about a village from a bygone era and the naive people who live in it. But with technology finding its way into the village, the villagers find out how things change and not necessarily for the better.

Title: 2446. Swargavaathil
Content: A women forced into prostitution due to circumstances.She further becomes madam of a brothel.

Title: 2447. Vallathol - Lokame Tharavadu
Content: Biography of Vallathol Narayana Menon, the poet from Kerala, India.

Title: 2449. Anchil Oral Arjunan
Content: Sudheendran, who doesn't have a registered job runs his household by doing odd jobs in his village. But chaos strikes when he falls for Sathi, Unni's daughter and his childhood friend.

Title: 2450. In a Land Far Away

Title: 2451. Mohanjadharo Aarappa
Content: The story revolves around three friends who hate lovers. They spend time in mocking and making fun of lovers. But in between one among the three friends falls in love without the knowledge of his friends. During this time they happen to meet a Saint which leads to dramatic changes in their life.

Title: 2454. Unni
Content: Unni is a little boy who lives in a village at Kerala. He belongs to the superior caste of Nairs. His friends Raju, Ramu and Gopi, who go to school with him, belong to the lowest caste of all. The film is the first in the trilogy Life Is All About Friends and deals with the relationship between these children and the discoveries they make together concerning the world about them.

Title: 2455. Achan
Content: An elderly gentleman Major Maman, who has seen better days, but has been left alone develops emotional relationship with a male nurse, Rahithan.

Title: 2456. Makkana
Content: Daughter of a pagan Fled with Those parents were paralyzed. Later To convert to get close to daughter Trying to stop them by reminding them that all religions are one.

Title: 2460. Thaskara Lahala
