Title: 2461. Panthaya Kozhi
Content: Nandagopal (Narain ) lives with his mother (Geetha) and mute sister Maya (Remya Nambeeshan) at the mercy of his uncle (Janaradhanan). They come to know their late father (Lal) bought a bungalow in Kalimuthupalayam, Tamil Nadu. Nandagopal go there to sell the property in order to get over their financial difficulties. But it's not easy to sell the bungalow because Nachiappa Gounder (Rami Reddy), the villain, refuses to vacate the house. In the meanwhile the Nandu falls in love with Chembakam (Pooja). This matter creates other problems. Nandu's friends decide to bring his mother and sister to stay in the house. When his mother comes and sees the house, she is shocked. For there is a story from the past that she remembers and that Nandagopal doesn't know. Finally Nandhu comes to know that all this cruelty of Gounder towards his family was only a part of enmity that roots back in the past. The rest of the movie is about how Nandagopal confronts with the Nachiappa Gounder. The rest of the film is based on these events

Title: 2462. Swanam
Content: As the saying goes, 'The one who has a good friend doesn't need any mirror', Swanam is about Balu, a mischievous student, and Kannan, who is born blind, and how life takes a beautiful turn.

Title: 2463. Qaff Studio Madh One
Content: The biographies of Muhammad the Prophet of Islam and Qutbul Alam CM Muhammad Aboobacker Musliyar a sufi saint from India.

Title: 2464. Nakshathrangal Parayathirunnathu
Content: Two friends, Nandakumar and Shashaankan, are in a desperate need of money. They decide to get their hands on some cash through unfair means.

Title: 2466. Kalivesham
Content: KALIVESHAM - Nalacharitham, the famous Kathakali story has Nala as its protagonist who gets possessed of Kali, the evil character. The text of this play provides a context in which there is interaction of three characters Nala, Kali and Natan (actor) of which Kali has no physical existence. His presence can be manifested only through the Natan (actor). Here when the Kathakali theme makes its renewed passage to the modern theatre it presents to us a thought process which forms the very basis of the art of transformation in theatre. Kalivesham is directed by Pamabhusham Kavlam Narayan Pannikar and for screen by Sanjeev Sharma Ronkel.

Title: 2467. Superstar Santhosh Pandit
Content: This is a Car. Engine out completely.

Title: 2468. Raama Raavanan
Content: Manomi, a Sinhalese orphan, comes to India to meet her guardian, Annadurai. She falls in love with Thiruchelvam, an LTTE commando. But will their love survive

Title: 2473. Aakashathinum Bhoomikkumidayil
Content: A village in northern Kerala where political murders are common. In one such incident, a guy who is mistaken to be someone else is murdered. This unfortunate incident leaves two families stranded.

Title: 2475. Kandethal
Content: Kandethal (Revelation) is a spiritual film deals with, the joys and sorrows of contemporary life to peace and calm in the light of ancient Indian Philosophy. Through personal experience a mother in this film realizes that the reason behind crises in life may not be searched in the exterior world, but in one's own interior world. Here, a mother whose agony on losing her son thinks that the whole children in the world are her own children and overcomes the sadness because of the previous jnana (inherited knowledge) and thus attains bliss.

Title: 2478. Janmam
Content: An orphan grows up in Veerakudi village under a taxi driver who names him Rayyar. He grows up to avenge the death of his parents who were mistaken to be naxalites and were murdered brutally.

Title: 2481. Domestic Dialogues
Content: The film revolves around a middle class Indian Family . Central character Anoop talks with 4 characters in 4 different area in a house. Through these conversations ,the current political condition of the country is revealed

Title: 2484. Shyamaragam
Content: Shyamaragam is a 2020 Indian Malayalam-language musical drama film written by Madambu Kunjukuttan and directed by Sethu Eyyal. It stars Y. Gee. Mahendra, Shanthi Krishna,Santhosh Keezhattoor, Pranav Suresh, Praseetha Uday.

Title: 2485. Colour Balloon
Content: Color Balloon is a drama movie written and directed by Subaash Thiruvilwamala, movie features Tini Tom, Jagadeesh, Vijayakumar, Nandulal, Indrence, Kochupreman, Vinod kovoor, Sunil Sukhada and Praveena in lead role.

Title: 2486. Poka
Content: Revolves around an underworld team lead by a lady who is popularly called as 'Bhabi'. Chain of events happen in their town which affects the lives of people living in the neighborhood. Their life is turned upside down when an unexpected event occur.

Title: 2487. Oru Nakshathramulla Aakasham
Content: The poignant tale of a school teacher in rural Kerala. It is interlaced between her struggles to find children for her school and the journey of a young man from Bangalore, who ventures to the small town to investigate her past love.

Title: 2488. Call from the Other Shore
Content: Maruvili (Call from the Other Shore) is an attempt of a poet-turned-filmmaker to portray the life and poetic idiom of one of his great predecessors, Attoor Ravivarma who is a distinct genius during the Modernist era of Indian poetry. Avoiding the usual descriptive forms, the film evolves through multiple layering of visualizations that includes various landscapes, festivals and journeys connected with Attoor's poetic world, a number of gatherings and conversations of Attoor critics and two generations of poets who are influenced or inspired by him, readings and audio-visual performances of Attoor poems by poets and theatre personalities using diverse styles and devices and so on. Multi-facet visual representations of this 90 minutes' Documentary span from Attoor Ravivarma's early memories to the live recordings of Video Conferences by fellow writers across the globe.

Title: 2489. Sthalam
Content: The destruction of the mangrove forest and the consequences faced by the people living there.

Title: 2491. Njan Shakespeare
Content: The movie is about the emotional turmoil of an actor who played female characters in Shakespeare plays. Drama is the only way he finds to escape from his own conflicts. The actor, who is preparing a new play with his old theatrical friends. One day a person comes into his life. That causes him deep and extreme trouble. No one comes to the aid of an actor who has to live like a criminal without finding a place in society.

Title: 2495. Koottu
Content: Koottu is a Compus love story. Hari (Richard) and Balu (Aravindan) who are students and buddies in a college.

Title: 2497. Pattiyude Divasam
Content: The traditional ruling Lord grants democracy to a rural province. As a token of good will, the Lord gives royal dog Apu to his former obedient servant. Koran and his wife proudly care for the small dog, admired by all the village. But the dog becomes responsible for ironic incidents that result in political confusion.

Title: 2499. When two kiss
Content: An intruder, in his mobile shoots the scene of a pair of lovers hugging on a beach. He tries to blackmail them. The film is around the theme of hegemonic sexual morality's potential to determine the nature of relationships and its intervention in personal relationships. the film does not attempt to tell a story. Three shots of three situations are there.

Title: 2502. Myself Clement
Content: THE STORY REVOLVES AROUND THE CENTRAL CHARACTER CLEMENT ,WHICH IS PLAYED BY THE DEBUTANT GAUTHAM S KUMAR , A NORMAL YOUNG MAN WHOSE LIFE TURNED AROUND AFTER HE HAD A TRAUMATIC EVENT IN HIS HAPPY LIFE.

Title: 2504. Lokha Samastha
Content: The unexpected death of Sarath's father and the later incidents forms the plot of the movie.

Title: 2505. Nilaavu
Content: Nilavu is the soul touching story of an indefinable relationship between two lonely individuals, who meet by chance. The whole film revolves around the strange bond that develops between them and how their relationship evolves.Krishnan Haridas as 'Hari' and Sunita Nedungadi as 'Lakshmi' bring to life the emotional complexities of expatriate life in the Gulf.

Title: 2506. Paulettante Veedu
Content: Paulettan's miserly attitude has its reverberations primarily on his family members. His daughter Sara falls in love with Amal, who leads a lavish lifestyle and Sara's love is a revolt against her father's thrifty behavior.

Title: 2507. Achante Aanmakkal
Content: Madhava Menon, a retired police officer, becomes a victim of political rivalry when he admits to have killed a boy and is imprisoned. His son-in-laws take it upon themselves to prove their father's innocence.

Title: 2511. The Inmates
Content: The Inmates is a story of old school 10th class students settled on different countries, they struck on one situation from that what they faced and how they escaped from the situation.

Title: 2512. Ivy
Content: Anto Simon is a photographer from Kerala, India and Ivy is a Kenyan girl. The movie IVY tells an Indo-Kenyan love story. The entire movie gives us a message Continents never matter. True love never dies.

Title: 2513. Magic Magic 3D
Content: Indrajeet lives with his grandfather, a magician Acharya in Mayapuri. The boy's mother died when he was an infant. Acharya teaches him magic, but never sent him to school for formal education. Indrajeet's father Krishna, who runs a successful Indian channel in the United States, arrives up to take his son for education. Indrajeet refuses to leave his grandfather, but is forcibly sent to New York City via carton. Indrajeet awakens in New York City where he has been brought against his will. He meets his stepmother Deepti, but soon runs away and befriends three run-away orphans and a wonder dog who belongs to Mahesh and Lude, two petty thieves. Meanwhile, Acharya comes to New York City in search of his grandson. Indrajeet gets kidnapped by the thieves, but ultimately Acharya, along with the dog, saves his grandson using all his magic tricks.

Title: 2517. The Gang
Content: In Kovalam, Kerala, a drug racket is run by a foreigner on the beach. However, he manages to carry out his work and not get caught only because of help from the locals and a coast guard.

Title: 2519. Budhiparamaaya Neekkam
Content: Budhiparamaaya Neekkam is a romantic film written and directed by Vinod Narayanan after his acclaimed film "Govindan Kutty thirakilanu". The story of the film was said to be "very much associated with the culture" of Trivandram town.

Title: 2522. The Trail of the Rain Song
2523. Dayom Panthrandum
Content: The film shares several characteristics with the game such as its unpredictability, adventure, thrill - all rolled into one. The film is about a group of youngsters who set out on a mission. They travel far and wide. While four of them are in a car, the 'Boss' of the group is on a bike, alone, as if expecting a pillion rider at any moment. They meet a tribal man who falls in their focus as well as their camera's. The new entrant guides them to new twists and turns. He guides them from the ease and comfort of film making to the harshness of reality which the forest unfolds.

Title: 2524. Vasanthathinte Kanal Vazhikalil
Content: The film revolves around the political unrest in a village and the rise of three communist leaders from the pre-Independence era in Kerala: P. Krishna Pillai, E. M. S. Namboodiripad, and A. K. Gopalan.

Title: 2527. Sinkari Bolona
Content: Jayakrishnan, a peon in a bank, falls in love with Anjali, an accountant in the same bank, and sends anonymous letters appreciating her. But Anjali thinks that the letters are sent by the manager.

Title: 2529. Muppathu Vellikkasu
Content: A Christian film based on the life of Jesus Christ adapted from New Testament in the Bible.

Title: 2531. Ningal Aranaye Kando?
Content: The film interweaves contemporary narratives with an ancient creation myth to explore the effects of a rapidly changing landscape on lives and livelihood. Set in a rich and bio-diverse region in South India, we journey through a land that is witnessing drastic transformation in the name of 'development'. A woman's concern over the disappearance of medicinal plants from the forest, a farmer's commitment to growing indigenous varieties of rice organically and a cash crop cultivator's struggle to survive amidst farmers' suicides, offer fresh insights into shifting relations between people, knowledge systems and environment. As hills flatten, forests disappear and knowledge systems are forgotten, the film reminds us that this diversity could disappear forever, to be replaced by unsustainable alternatives.

Title: 2532. Aalilathoni
Content: It is a beautiful love story of a woman and a young man. This story depicts the life of a divorced, rich woman who accidentally meets a young man and falls in love with him. The boy fulfills her desires of life. And the story ends with the marriage scene of the couple.

Title: 2534. Maniac
Content: Two couples goes missing.

Title: 2536. Vinayapoorvam Vidyadharan
Content: Vidyadharan who is a bank employee and he is a simple at heart. His wife who aspires for an extravagant lifestyle. Her extravagance results in Vidyadharan losing his job.

Title: 2537. Fever...
Content: Mercilessly killing aged parents by the children in a heinous, age old custom called 'Thalaikuthal', is being practiced secretly even now in some villages of Tamil Nadu, India. 'PANI' showcases some practices of this custom in the name of mercy killing for property and money.

Title: 2538. Aparanmar Nagarathil
Content: Nadeshan wakes up from a coma but is unaware that many years have passed. When he decides to make a movie with actors from the yesteryears, his son hires their lookalikes.

Title: 2539. Grihanathan
Content: Wealthy entrepreneur Vishwanathan's life takes an odd turn when his wife takes control of the financial matters and begins running their home.

Title: 2542. Mayakkazhcha
Content: After his granddaughter Aswathi gets affected by a curse inflicted on his family centuries ago, Raja Varma Thamburan goes on a quest to find the prophesied remedy.

Title: 2543. Chempada
Content: revolves around a music troupe of youngsters named 'Red Army'. Headed by its mentor Captain Mukundan Menon, the group's real operations are to loot and kill people who have amassed wealth through wrong means and to cleanse the world of crime and injustice. Manu (Bala), a naive guy from Vagamon and son of a driver working for R. K. Nair, a rich planter, loved Meenakshi (Sreedevika), an innocent girl. But Meenakshi was raped by the planter and his accomplices. Being loyal to the master, Manu's father took the blame upon himself and got arrested. Things took a different turn when his father committed suicide in jail under suspicious circumstances and Meenakshi went missing. Manu then took up arms to avenge R. K. Nair and his men, but was beaten and left badly wounded in a desolate place, where he was found by the troupe members. Manu, who is later inducted into the troupe, gets a new name, Harikrishnan, and becomes active in the troupe's activities. What happens next forms the rest of the movie.

Title: 2549. Careebeyans
Content: Viswanathan, a loyal home minister, sincerely works for the welfare of the people. However, he faces many challenges when he encounters an evil politician, Natarajan.

Title: 2550. Jagapoga
Content: Two bumbling policemen who set out to investigate the disappearance of a revered idol from the local temple create a lot of confusion and get involved in hilarious events.

Title: 2551. Vellathooval
Content: Jiya, a fun loving girl is tired of her conservative family and therefore decides to abscond with her friend Manu. They become good friends but the society misunderstands them.

Title: 2552. Shree Balaji Photo Studio
Content: The life of a photographer and his emotional connect with the studio. How this character tries to update with the digital world and how a particular situation brings a turn in his life.

Title: 2556. Female Unnikrishnan
Content: Unni, who has a feminine voice, gets insulted by everyone in his neighborhood. His life takes a turn when he gets married to a rich girl who is speech-impaired.

Title: 2557. Vettappattikalum Oattakkarum
Content: "I would like to sell my virginity". Seeing this post on the Facebook wall of an ordinary college girl named Sabitha created a momentum in the social sphere of Kerala. Be it politicians, moralists, feminists or activists, everybody got worked up. Even lawyers and gynecologists flooded the field with expert advice. TV channels and police lost their sleep. Investigative journalism on the one hand, guarding performance farce on the other. Amidst all the commotion, Sabita's new announcement that she will publicly auction her virginity in front of the Secretariat has also come out. Mercenary forces lined up on both sides, for and against the sale. Spectators were ready to enjoy the spectacle, police were ready with barricades and water cannons.Judges began preparing judgments in the media rooms. What happens in the anxious hour? Kerala waited with excitement. Violation of personal freedom and privacy has become common in these days. Mutual respect is also gone. Ideology have been reduced to mere words. Today we no longer hesitate to chase the victims and hunt with the hounds. It is in this context that the movie 'Vettapattikalum Ottakarum' is relevant. An unreal subject is recorded as if it were a real event. This completely ignored issue is being taken up by people in different sectors of the society, making it a big topic for discussion. To document this, scenes have been created to mimic the channel debates of the day. Other debatable scenes have also been used. In this film, people's urge to sneak into other's life, including myself, has been approached in a self -critical manner.

Title: 2561. Certain Lives in Twilight
Content: After being diagnosed with a terminal illness, a renowned philosophy professor (and author) decides to refuse palliative care, and heads to a secluded hill station to spend his final days in peace. He is accompanied by his former student and biographer in this journey, with whom he shares a complex relationship. As the disease continues to corrode his body and mind, the professor has to grapple with a memory that eludes him, regrets that haunt him and questions that he is yet to find answers to. Much like the veil of mist shrouding the valley, a great existential crisis envelops him. With the ghosts of his past resurfacing and the present turning into a nightmare, is it too late for him to seek redemption?

Title: 2564. Sword of Liberty
Content: The Sword of Liberty The Life and Death of Velu Thambi Dalawa 'The Sword of Liberty, the Life and Death of Velu Thambi Dalawa' uses an unconventional narrative to recap the story of a legend. Marionettes dance in the shadows and spin the chronicle of an extraordinary personality, a man who fought for his homeland, long before the seeds of nationalism were sown in India. The protagonist, Devaki, journeys from the laid-back, picturesque, Nanjinadu territory, to the distant Kilimanoor Palace, in pursuit of the Dalawa stories she had learnt as a child from her father. Her path crosses those of puppeteers, artists and historians and interweaves indigenous art forms like 'Tholpaavakoothu', the diverse forms of 'Thullal', and 'Villupattu', to narrate prominent anecdotes and little-known snippets from Velu Thambi's life. Touching places significant to his life and death, the film engages the viewer in the unravelling of a saga: a nineteen-year- old confidant of the king, who finally goes on to become one of Travancore's most celebrated leaders. Velu Thambi's initial association and later hostility with the British, his success and failure as a Dalawa, his famous ' Kundara Vilambaram' which called forth the masses to unite against the British, and his self-annihilation, are a few of the many incidents covered in this tribute to Velu Thambi, the immortal hero.

Title: 2565. Njaan Samvidhanam Cheyyum
Content: Krishna Das (Balachandra Menon) is a man who passionately loves movies. It's family story about a father, mother and a daughter.

Title: 2568. Sound of Boot
Content: A couple visits a holiday home for their honeymoon and the woman is found murdered on the following day. Superintendent of Police Siddharth Mahadev (Suresh Gopi) investigates the case and unravels the shocking truth.

Title: 2574. Thanaha
Content: The movie portrays the story of two friends Vishnu and Roy who ends up in the Police service after the death of their fathers. The story begins with a missing culprit and the journey of the two policemen in unraveling the mystery. This is a comedy thriller and a complete family entertainer.

Title: 2575. Thaarakangale Saakshi
Content: The movie tells the story of Jayakumar Narayan, a youngster who has the dream of creating a classic movie. Jayakumar sacrifices his professional and personal life to achieve his passion. Tharakangale Sakshi is a family entertainer with an unexpected climax. The power of human will, accidental adventurous, unconditional love of family and friends is the synopsis of the movie.

Title: 2577. Rakshapurushan
Content: The story of Rakshapurushan revolves around Stephen, an honest man whose life descends into chaos after he loses everything dear to him in the battle against a corrupt system.

Title: 2579. Scent of Cigar
Content: An actor encounters in his life exactly what he was acting on the drama as a character or was it he empathise his character and life

Title: 2581. Rasputin
Content: Sushee falls in head-over-heels in love with Smitha, an escort whom his friend, Rad, introduces him to. However, when Sushee decides to pursue her in another city, he and Rad get in trouble.

Title: 2583. Leader
Content: A family that is into politics faces many challenges as they have to overcome the obstacles thrown by the opposing parties. However, they try their luck to win the election.

Title: 2584. AltCtrlDel
Content: A day in the life of Niyatha, an IT professional in Bengaluru, who decides to get out of her toxic relationship but faces resistance from her partner and a mysterious knife-wielding hitman.

Title: 2590. Kannalan
Content: Kannalan portrays the helplessness and challenges of people who are isolated in society, through the life of a journalist.

Title: 2591. The Red Data Book: An Appendix
Content: The film is a layered examination of the factors, both contemporary and historical, that have led the Adivasi (tribal) communities of Attappady (Kerala, South India) to the verge of extinction. The film focuses on the phenomenon of rising infant mortality to probe the entire range of underlying factors. Is it mainly due to malnutrition, as the State claims? Is it their exclusion from the fruits of so-called development? Is it their refusal to 'modernise'? Or is it our inability to comprehend and preserve their centuries-old harmonious way of life? Have our prescriptive interventions helped? Or have they caused great harm? The film attempts to understand the gamut of 'alienations' responsible - social, cultural, economic and political while gently posing the core question: Is it they who are alienated from the onward march of progress or is it us who are alienated, blinded by the discourse of modernity?

Title: 2592. Koracharithram
Content: It's a corruption model, suspense, psychic thriller movie

Title: 2593. Swantham Malavika
Content: Swantham Malavika is a 2003 Indian Malayalam film, directed by Jagadeesh Chandran and Produced by Prabhettan. The film stars Vijayaraghavan, Manya, Rajan P. Dev, Rajesh Rajan and Menon Gopi in lead roles. The music of the film was composed by Kaithapram.

Title: 2594. Gundert the Man the Language
Content: Gundert- The Man The Language. The film attempts a biographic depiction - the reconstruction of the life and times of Herman Gundert, the famed linguist and publisher; a figure who cannot be discounted while charting the evolution of the cultural history of Kerala. This portraiture is done through the eyes of a sculptor, the vision of an academician and the memories of the descendents of the Gundert family.

Title: 2596. Unnathangalil
Content: Greed towards money, causes dispute between two childhood best friends, resulting in a competition among themselves.

Title: 2600. Perinoru Makan
Content: Harishchandran wants to get his daughter married, but the thought of her leaving the house breaks his heart, so he decides to find a groom who is willing to live in his father-in-law's home after the wedding.

Title: 2602. Orkkuka Vallappozhum
Content: The return journey of an old man into the innocence of his past.

Title: 2603. Swapnangal Pookkunna Kaadu
Content: Adam's journey to a forest where he meets an Angel of Dreams.

Title: 2605. Bhoomiyil Chuvadurachu
Content: The creative self of the Master gets explored through self-reflections, memories and conceptual interventions.

Title: 2606. Mohacheppu
Content: Mohacheppu is a 1989 Indian Malayalam film, directed by P. Chandrasekhar and produced by Sincere Cine Arts. The film stars Sharmily, Sudheer Sukumaran, Hema and V.P. Ramachandran in the lead roles. The music of the film was composed by Rajeev.

Title: 2607. Katti Nrittam
Content: Katti Nrittam also pronounced as Kathi Nrittam meaning the Knife Dance is a melancholic drama of a failed Kathakali Dancer who turns out to be a psychopath killer.

Title: 2609. Aanamuttathe Aangalamar
Content: The members of the influential Aanamuttam Tharavadu come into conflict with each other over the right to hold a festival and be the head of the family.

Title: 2610. Telescope
Content: Some people (Dalit, Muslim, Hindu, officer, revolutionary, teacher, woman, child) end up in a pit. Their fear of death brings them closer. Their innate behaviours reveal often. They can only escape if they bury their prejudices.

Title: 2612. Appu in search of truth
Content: Nine year old Appu has failed in his examination and teacher has asked him to get his father's signature on the answer sheet. As Appu was worried about the solid beating he will get, his friend Jithu advises him to secretly copy his father's signature. Will he?

Title: 2613. Nedumi
Content: When the long craving of a daily wage labor named Sivanesan, becomes the owner of the palm toddy shop. At that time government imposes a law which affects the live hood of sivanesan. The aftermath impacts is the rest of the film.

Title: 2619. Sahodaran Sahadevan
Content: Identical twins Mukundan and Aravindan get married on the same day. Things change when an accident kills one of the brothers and the other one loses his memory.

Title: 2620. Bilathikuzhal
Content: For Kunjambu, Chindan Muthapan is a legendary hero - a figure in his grandmother's fairytales. Chindan is a hunter, the only man in the village who knows how to use an English barrel. As a kid, Kunjambu dreamt about Chindan, where the man with the gun rescued him from his nightmares. When Chindan walked into the forest holding the gun, the young Kunjambu followed him. Even after becoming an adult, Kunjambu remains fascinated with the gun. Then, one day, Kunjambu has to turn in his gun at the local police station, as part of a mandatory requirement during elections - an act that changes his life.

Title: 2623. Calton Towers
Content: Twenty seven year old Rony dies in a Major fire at Calton Towers. As his seventy year old father Bala, with a host of health issues struggles to unravel the mystery behind the fire that caused Rony's death, he discovers a son who is at times deeply disturbing and at times a crusader for the marginalized. A deeper understanding of his son's character - something that eluded him while his son was alive, makes Bala a more resolute being. He progressively slides into his son's shoes.

Title: 2625. Oduvil
Content: A documentary revealing the versatile faces of the legendary actor Oduvil Unnikrishnan from Malayalam film world

Title: 2626. Skia the Dusk of Soul
Content: Suspense thriller horror movie. The truth is revealed. Skia is an edge-of-a-seat thriller with a unique storyline, telling the story of a boy who unlocks and discovers a deadly game of crime.

Title: 2627. Adhinayakavadham
Content: Adhinayakavadham is a political fun thriller. Directed by Dinesh Ganga. Staring Priyesh m pramod, Sreekanth soman, Aneesh Govind, abubacker, vyshnavi, Silpa, Suminraj, bibu ebinezer etc.

Title: 2628. Parinamam
Content: Parinamam tackles the age-old issue of loneliness and redundancy among the aged. In parallel, Balakrishna Marar faces callous treatment from his family after his retirement.

Title: 2629. SnehChakram
Content: Lucky is a cheerful man who is unemployed and recently completed his CA, lives with his sister. His uncle, a friend of Lucky's (late) dad advised him to go to his friend's company for employment with one condition that he must change his modern appearance and thoughts, as his friend doesn't like current modernization and believes that one should follow their cultural aspects and be workaholic. The story twists when his boss sees him in his unique appearance, which is not quite the same as he looks at work. When the boss asks about his appearance somehow, he manages but is stuck into several problems in the day-to-day working environment. The whole story revolves around managing his present job with two distinctive indistinguishable roles.

Title: 2630. Nottam
Content: A well-known Koodiyattam artiste faces the harsh realities of today's world, which offers nothing much to the great ritualistic, classical art form of Kerala.

Title: 2634. The Third Eye of Resistance
Content: A journey through the life of C. Saratchandran who travelled constantly with the camera and cinemas. As someone who pioneered in media activism as part of the little magazine movement during the Emergency, Sarat later on took up the very political duty of documenting the popular struggle movements of Kerala. This film tries to be exactly that, a clear take on the popular risings of not just Kerala, but the whole of India, by exploring and coordinating the history of those who have travelled along with Sarat. Sarat, who remained wide awake in both at the struggle fronts and in his personal relationships; for someone as unconditionally empathetic, the camera was always the third eye for fulfilling his mission; the third eye of resistance.

Title: 2636. Abhirami
Content: 'Abhirami' is a story about a young lady who lives in Dubai working as a nurse. She is very active on social media platforms. She becomes viral after a post on her social media account where she films a video with a famous scientist who was living a secluded life for a while. After the incident, a PR company hires her for a year and she enjoys her sudden celebrity status. She is invited to various events, interviews etc. She becomes a star overnight. Slowly she finds out that she has lost her freedom and is trapped in the grapple of the company. She cannot decide her own affairs without the consent of the company. She suffers huge losses personally too. Her would-be husband becomes distant from her. She is also threatened by the company to pay an enormous amount as compensation if she breaches her contract. She is plunged into depression. She resolves to make a comeback with the help of the same person who featured with her in the viral post. She finally breaks the chain and emerges out of the virtual world to the real world.

Title: 2638. 5 Seeds
Content: The film 5 seeds is about peace. This film revolves around the lives of five children, each film tells different stories. It deals with the conflicts a child's mind suffer and how they recover from the same. The conflict dealt by the first film is much simpler one and as the film progress each film deals with more and more complex conflicts. *Seed 1* The film dealt with the simplest conflict in the entire anthology. The same represent how the simplest conflict is creating an emotional outburst in a child's mind. An innocent lie to her grandmother fills her heart with immense guilt. And the same is easily washed away with a small kiss from her grandmother. *Seed 2* How irresponsible the father maybe, the attachment of child completely depends on the slightest affection he is showing to him. The film shows the necessity of love being expressed. *Seed 3* The film deals with the grief the child suffers on the death of his grandfather. This film deals with much complicated conflict. When the grandfather was alive, both of them had regular quarrel, and one night the child prays for his death. The next day his prayer comes true. How he comes out of the grief is revealed in this film. *Seed 4* The mentally retarded child only knows to love. He wants to keep everything he loves to be safe. It might be the photograph of his dead mother or something that glitters. By keeping them safe, he accrues peace. *Seed 5* The trauma a child may suffer during the separation of parents. And the outburst of happiness when a slight chance of their reunion appears.

Title: 2641. Nagaravadhu
Content: Sukanya enters into politics after she wins over the confidence of a shrewd politician, Narendra Babuji. Though she is shattered, she has certain definite plans and decisions too.

Title: 2642. Bharya Swantham Suhruthu
Content: Zakhariah leads a straightforward life with his wife Molly and their daughter Teena. His life takes a turn when one of his clients Girija Menon gets close to him.

Title: 2645. By Mammali an Indian
Content: Life has become a veritable hell for Mammali, a poor barber in a remote village in Kerala and his daughter in law, Shareefa. It's after his son, Anwar joined IS and was killed while fighting for them, life went topsyturvy for Mammali and Shareefa. Life is not going to be the one they had been used to. Daily visits to the police station, harassment by law enforcers, rejection by friends and relatives, social boycott...- their life has completely changed its course. Actully they are two hapless victims ensnared in the vicious net set by communalism.

Title: 2646. In the Shadow of Mother Tree
2647. Maratha Nadu
Content: Religious intolerance in a small faction results in a communal riot. A Muslim father gets torn apart when his daughter requests him to marry her off to her Hindu lover.

Title: 2650. Anyar
Content: After a failed love affair due to communal tension in Kerala, Raziya takes up an assignment to cover the Gujarat riots. She learns a valuable lesson upon witnessing the communal polarity in the state.

Title: 2654. Virus
Content: The story of lovers, but she is now an HIV positive and her only support is her dear brother. Will she get accepted by her lover?

Title: 2656. The 137 Auditions of Avrahaam Yaakob
Content: Avrahaam Yaakob, is almost 60, but he keeps attending Cinema Auditions. Others think that he is a crazy old man trying to break into films. But, for Avrahaam, every audition is an opportunity to become another human being.

Title: 2657. Oridam
Content: The movie is a quest of a sex worker to find a place for her in the society. She doesn't have a name, and aims of leading a decent life, one that doesn't have anything to do with the flesh trade.

Title: 2658. Jagathi Jagathish in Town
Content: Jagathi and Jagadeesh are brothers, who work as police officers. They encounter small-time criminals who are their long-lost brothers.

Title: 2659. Children of Allah
Content: This feature documentary explores the consequences of the Islamic culture of polygamy on the lives of young boys by observing their daily lives in an orphanage in southern India. The boys, in the absence of a family have formed their own.

Title: 2660. Issacinte Kadhakal
Content: An US based married couple in their 40s, named Sakkariah and Aleena (Tom George and Suvarna Mathew) desperately want to have a baby, but they are unable to have a lasting pregnancy. Aleena had already suffered four miscarriages in the past years. On Dr.Isssac's (Thampy Antony) advice, they decide to look for a surrogate mother to bear Sakkariah's child. Movie is all set to commence shoot on Winter season in USA. The story begins and ends in the Winter time. The four seasons written in the story portrays the different emotions, feelings and the changes of life. First half of the movie is in USA and the second half is in India.

Title: 2661. Karannakaran
Content: Everyone who tries to kill Mitran fails because he somehow always knows when there is any threat to his life. Some people join forces to find his secret. Will they be able to achieve it?

Title: 2665. Chippy
Content: A bunch of school going kids from Thalassery, a coastal area in Kerala, who want to make a short film revolving around their distasteful experiences in life.

Title: 2666. Jalachhayam
Content: Mohan, an art teacher in a city college meets Sadanandan, an ordinary villager, and learning of his aptitude for drawing, teaches him the nuances of modern methods of painting. Mohan buys the paintings of Sadanandan, which, more proficient than that of an amateur, were nevertheless beyond the expectations of Mohan. But, Sadanandan was totally unaware of the philistine attitude of Mohan who uses him for his own benefit. Jalachhayam describes how Sadanandan survives the moment he knows, Mohan, a godfather-like figure to Sadanandan, was cheating him.

Title: 2668. Pravaasam
Content: Govindankutty, a middle-class man, is saddened when he loses his job. Anxious to ensure a stable future for his family, he is forced to make a tough decision.

Title: 2671. Pratheekshayode
Content: Pratheekshayode is the story of Amal (Master Dhananjay) who at a young age had to shoulder great responsibilities, far beyond his understanding or skills when his parents (Mukesh and Lakshmi Sharma) passed away. Left with the burden of taking care of not only himself but also his father's younger sister Anupama (Manasy), who became blind at her prime, Amal has to face challenges not only from Anti Social Elements in the Society but also from his own Government and Legal System whose Child Labour Prohibition Act does not permit him to be there for the only family he has left.

Title: 2673. Ranabhoomi
Content: It is the brave tale of Malabar rebellion, Chandappura combat and the retaliations happened at Pandikkad and neighbouring areas, which were all integral part of the Indian independence movement.

Title: 2675. Pullimaan
Content: Kunjunni, an orphan, and Radha, who makes a living by selling statues of deities, love each other. However, problems arise when her father opposes their relationship.

Title: 2677. Laloorinu Parayanullathu
Content: The documentary narrates about the problems of Municipal Garbage dumping in Laloor, a suburban area in Thrissur Municipal Corporation. The film also reveals the history of the waste dumping in Laloor since the period of Sakthan Thampuran who was the ruler of the Kingdom of Cochin and first violence against the Garbage dumping here.

Title: 2678. Aalokam
Content: An ordinary man belonging to the Kerala lower middle class tries to meet a drama actor to get his idea of drama materialized which is based on five dramatic monologues by the Victorian poet Robert Browning. He finds his alter ego in the actor and envisages the discussions on various aspects of the subject. The actor, who is the conflicting and contrary views in the protagonist himself, points out the possibility of a film in the subject and insists the former on developing it in to a film script. The film ends as a 'tragedy with a difference', in which the creator himself becomes a character in a mind-film, as an introvert person created by societal restraints and capital constraints tries to make a film.

Title: 2681. With Her
Content: 5 Scenes, 5 Shots, 5 Characters

Title: 2684. Trap
Content: Five friends set off for Munnar. One of them dies in an accident there. One of the five accidentally causes his death.They secretly bury him for fear that the four of them will be caught if the incident comes to light.It rains heavily at night when everyone drinks to get rid of its troubles.This time, when they hear a knock on the door and one of them opens the door, they are frightened to see a figure wrapped in mud. They realize that it is John who is buried there. "Trap" is a suspense thriller that will be made later.

Title: 2687. Seetha
Content: (Sivaji) is fond of his sister-in-law (Meera Jasmine). He loves her so much, he wants to be flawless with good character. Though Rajeswari behaves that she is not interested in him, she really loves him. Sivaji has a property dispute with his stepbrother (Subbaraju). In a bid to save a girl (Sangeeta) from being sold by a brothel owner (Anuradha) to Subbaraju, Sivaji pays her money and takes Chintamani with him and keeps her in his outhouse. Sivaji tells her to leave the place the next day, but accidentally seduces Chintamani, after an attack by Subbaraju's men against him. Being an honest boy, Sivaji reveals everything to his father-in-law and urges him to stop the marriage, but the latter refuses to do so. Again, Sivaji innocently reveals the incident to Rajeswari as he doesn't want to deceive her about being pious and flawless. Rajeswari attempts suicide and gets saved by Sivaji. However, Rajeswari refuses to share the marital life with Sivaji. A few days later, her father convinces her and appeals to honor his honesty. Being impressed with his innocence, Rajeswari allows him into the bedroom; as a result she becomes pregnant--as does Chintamani. How does Sivaji manage both his pregnant wives? Does Chintamani come into the life of Rajeswari? Does Rajeswari keep mum on learning Chintamani was also pregnant and Sivaji continued to pamper her? What happens to the property dispute between Sivaji and Subbaraju? How did Subbaraju react against Sivaji? Answers to all these questions form part of the climax.

Title: 2690. Sarcas Circa 2020
Content: After facing failure in almost every venture, Mr. F and Mr. J, two friends from a small town in Kerala embark on an adventurous journey to a nearby city. Mr. F receive a call from a stranger who persuades them to take up and finish a task. The stranger promises upon the completion of the task they will make a fortune putting an end to their drag ordinary lives. Continuous failures in Mr. F's life has allowed him to arrive at his own philosophy and insists that we are living in peculiar times surrounded by samasya (riddles). Those who offer help/work/money, in short, people with power have choices and those who receive have none. Ironically, Mr. F in his personal relationship with Mr. J seems to have forgotten his own philosophy. Leaving no space for agency or autonomy Mr. F drags his innocent and obedient friend (Mr. J) into a huge mess from which three is no going back. Sarcas Circa 2020 is a subjective take on how people with power lay out their connection with the ordinary people in the society and its manifestation in the lives of ordinary people we encounter in streets. Sarcas Circa 2020 captures and explores the experiences of the ordinary people and the uncertainties through which they oscillate between the known and the unknown.

Title: 2691. Cabin
Content: Cabin revolves around Devaraj, a truck driver from Tamilnadu, who gets involved in an unforeseen incident with a family moving to Kerala.

Title: 2694. Hallucia
Content: This film belongs to a psychological-horror genre. It revolves around a young researcher and take the audience through his mental and physical journeys.

Title: 2696. Oath
Content: The film captures the tragic life of a father who has to live with his disabled son and the attitudes of the society.

Title: 2698. Melaprayanam: The Saga of a Drummer
Content: Life of Kalamandalam Unnikrishnan, a significant figure who transformed the use of chenda in Kathakali

Title: 2703. Pappantem Simontem Piller
Content: The film revolves around characters who live and die for its titular characters, Pappan and Simon, infamous quotation leaders who exert control over the city.

Title: 2704. Dry: The Days After...
Content: Dry chronicles the life of an alcoholic youth and how he struggles to find a job so as to sustain his lifestyle in the city. His mother's love and his goals seem lost when it comes to his affinity for the bottle. Based around the time when Kerala government had banned the sale of alcohol in the state, this movie shows his reciprocal behaviour and how he goes about in satiating his obsession. This movie further mirrors the current situations of the youth in Kerala with regards to their afflictions, job hunt experiences and other cultural fallacies.

Title: 2709. Kadal Paranja Katha
Content: Set against the backdrop of a coastal region in Kerala, the film is said to be a social issue drama that addresses the degeneration of a community and a young woman's struggles in the face of it.

Title: 2716. Panchajannyam
Content: 'Ottakalan' Shivan has lost his legs in a fight with local goon Aandavan. Shivan decides to take his revenge when Aandavan kills his dearest friend Shekharan.

Title: 2717. www.Anukutumbam.com
Content: Joji, an orphan, escapes from the orphanage and joins a group of thieves and other small-time crooks. But his life takes a turn when he discovers that he is not an orphan and his name is Sachin.

Title: 2718. Jagala
Content: Jagala is a story of a young Muslim man named Chekku who lived in Eranad during the Mappila Rebellion era of 1920s.

Title: 2722. Balcony
Content: The story is about a girl named Serin , who is transplanted from a village to a city through a marriage. She faces some unusual and strange experiences in her husband's flat.

Title: 2723. Sketch
Content: A leading advocate Parthasarthy Iyer hopes that his son Shiva will become like him. Alas, Shiva ends up as a criminal and is sent to jail for a murder.

Title: 2724. Nisabdham
Content: Story of a mother and daughter through the characters and events they encounter during one day, the difficulties and joys of their life journey are brought by the hard realities which leads the story forward.

Title: 2726. Seeking the Reality of Yoga
Content: This documentary film is about the reality of yoga which is now performed all over the world.Now this film criticizing the yoga and its postures.Now the yoga postures are taken from contortion,drill,circus etc.The yogis who made the yoga has know nothing about the human anatomy ,blood circulation, respiratory system etc. therefore yoga is unscientific and the same time it is a fake one. All over the world there are so many casualties due to yoga.This documentary discussing these aspects and the unscientific nature of the yoga.

Title: 2729. Charitham
Content: Charitham is a story happening in and around a rural Kerala village called Thrikkayi. Thrikkayi has some mysteries and uncertainties along with some myths and politics.

Title: 2730. Kalyana Kurimanam
Content: The Mullassery family runs many businesses. Madhavanunni, the youngest in the family, is not given charge of anything as he is very irresponsible. He decides to fight back and become somebody.

Title: 2732. Jnana Saradhi
Content: Jnana Saradhi casts light on the history of Namboodiri Vidyalayam upper primary school through adv. C. K. Narayanan Namboodiripad. The film brings out a contrast between the ancient and modern educational status of Kerala.

Title: 2734. Sthaayi
Content: Akshay, A 25-year old guy is facing many difficulties in his life due to caste, religion, color, etc. The movie goes through the life of Akshay, who have been staying in the city for seeking jobs.

Title: 2736. B for Apple A for Darwin
2742. Nedumi
Content: When the long craving of a daily wage labor named Sivanesan, becomes the owner of the palm toddy shop. At that time government imposes a law which affects the live hood of sivanesan. The aftermath impacts is the rest of the film.

Title: 2746. Only Sometimes a God
Content: 'ONLY SOMETIMES A GOD'- A documentary seeking to find the relevance behind the existence of an age old ritual art form- 'THEYYAM' performed in India.

Title: 2747. Neelakasham Niraye
Content: Unni, a Hindu, is shocked to learn about the communal riot in his small village when he comes home from abroad. He faces many challenges when he falls in love with a Muslim girl, Amina.

Title: 2754. Goat - The Origin
Content: A planet formed, life emerged, and tales were crafted, but over time, inhabitants blindly believed these stories, leading to senseless actions that endure for decades.

Title: 2756. Rathrimazha
Content: The story takes off on two dance-loving people. The two get to know each other on the internet. They exchange ideas and opinions. Their world-views coincide.

Title: 2758. Kaalppaadukal
Content: Drawing inspiration from a tradition or ritual practiced among the Muslim community in south Kerala, we envisioned this film as a tale of human relationships, the hardships one goes through to provide for family and near ones and also the mortality of human body and memories associated with it. The protagonist is remembered fondly, affectionately, passionately and kindly by his family and friends. Each reminiscence has an imagery of his amputated leg. The film also emphasis on the human will to overcome seemingly impossible life situations where wholeness of human body is reduced but the passion for life continues.

Title: 2776. Kalavallabham
Content: Tiruvalla Sri Vallabha Mahashetram is a temple in the town of Tiruvalla in Pathanamthitta district, estimated to have been built in 59 BC and is one of the oldest and largest places of worship in Kerala. The main deities are Lord Vishnu and the fierce Sudarshanamurthy, meaning the giver of good sight. Lord Vishnu is known here as "Shrivallabhan". The name 'Thiruvalla' is said to be derived from this name. The Thiruvalla Sri Vallabhamaha Temple is one of the 108 Vaishnava shrines sung by the devoted poets of the Azhwars.

Title: 2781. Depth of Darkness (Kaali)
Content: Kaali, A innocent plantation worker yearns to be a mother but is unable to conceive. A series of tragic events lead Kaali to realize divine Mother Goddess is in herself and she rises above all the ill doings to protect innocence of life.

Title: 2786. Krishna Gopalakrishna
Content: Gopalakrishnan hires Gayatri, to write his biography. She learns that Gopalakrishnan had no life of his own. His childhood was ruled by his father, later years by his wife, and then by his sons.

Title: 2788. Amma Marathanalil
Content: The movie "Ammamarathanalil" speaks aloud the emotional bondage of man, nature and the love between mother and son. The protagonist Manu is compelling to stay away from his homeland and seeks asylum in Prakash's house through Ajayan. True to the meaning of his name Prakash's influence enlightens Manu to New discoveries of life and its meaning. Manu gets a new realization of the bliss of Nature and a slow intense fire of love towards nature engulfs him. He is also able to connect to his mother with deep love and understanding. In the bargain of Manu's presence make Prakash to confront a lot of challenges and the subsequent events raises the question whether Prakash would shrivel in the company of Manu. Spectators can perceive this movie as a granny's folklore with lot of fantasies to her granddaughter or a movie which propagates and promotes the significance of loving your environment and Nursing it, and also a movie which narrates the in effects of Urban /Modern culture on the innocent Villagers. The Naked truth of a villager's innocents, corruption of that by urban infringements, the bliss of Mother Nature and it's connect to one's body and soul is amply narrated with good sensible craft of filmmaking.

Title: 2790. Mashi
Content: Agustus Gregor, a probationary rank IPS officer, who left his writing passion for his IPS gets himself entangled in an investigation where the accused is a failed novelist.

Title: 2801. Wind and Rain
Content: The film is based on a true incident which happened in North Kerala. The film has so much social importance in contemporary India

Title: 2809. Bhoomiyude Uppu
Content: Salt of the Earth examines the grand questions of good and evil. Emmanuel is a novice leading a peaceful life in a Capuchin monastery. A television programme triggers questions about God's silence in Emmanuel's mind.

Title: 2813. Mazhanoolkanavu
Content: Varsha, a teacher, struggles to lead a normal life as she is haunted by memories of her lost love, Unni. However, her straightforward behavior earns her the ire of her students and colleagues.

Title: 2817. Bheri
Content: The film tries to speak of the abominable living conditions and exploitation of the tribal community of the region juxtaposing it with the Naxalite movement.
